The Robot I built wasn't supposed to come to life. It just, well... happened. This story of how the Bobot became to be my best creation... or nightmare... I had been working on a powerful Bobot project. I was in charge of the programming of Bobot. However, my little mistake cost a lot of trouble... AND I mean a lot of trouble.             It was the year of  5-12-1989, Cancun, Mexico. I was excited because to day was Bobot's reveal to the public. Unfortunately, I had forgottten to insert the no-evil programming inside of him ! The lack of that programming was going to cause him to go on an evil outrage! So when the power was turned on, Bobot's uproar began! His hammering arms slammed into the ground killing thousands. Even worse, he released an inferno out of his flamethrowers as well, incinerating everything in the process. My colleagues glared at me because I was the one who forgot include the no-evil programming. I chuckled sheepishly. To stop Bobot's thrash, I needed the selfdestruct remote. I raced to the Lab to get it. I pressed the huge, red, button and flares of oil and fire exploded as Bobot was destroyed...             The good news was that Bobot's rampage came to a halt. The bad news was: We had lost Bobot, thousands of people perished, and their was a lot of destruction me and my colleagues had to pay for. I groaned. This was going to take a lifetime's work to pay off the mess Bobot caused...

Mr. Gower                 One perfect day in Boston, Massachusetts a 21 year old-boy named Marcus got a new toy called Mr. Gower. He brought it back to his house and was playing with it in his room. He had to leave for a few weeks so he said bye to Mr. Gower and left. The next day Mr. Gower starts glowing and he is making noises and starts talking. HE IS ALIVE!! He was programmed to work in hospitals, and help doctors and nurses bring medicine to patients. Mr. Gower looks like a small cabinet with wheels. The body is a stack of locked drawers stored with medicine. Nurses and doctors unlock the drawers when medicine is needed for a patient. Mr. Gower can ride elevators, steer through hallways, and move things that get in the way.            This robot is so strong that it could pull 500 pounds. Mr. Gower runs on batteries, so he charges for two hhours and can deliver medicine for twelve hours without stopping. Mr. Gower can talk too. It can say, 'Calling elevator' or 'Your delivery is here.' Mr. Gower works for nurses and doctors and sometimes does their job so they can focus on more important tasks. After a few weeks working at the hospital Marcus comes back in his room to play with Mr. Gower but he was gone. His mom gets the newspaper and Mr. Gower is on the front cover. Marcus llooks at the picture and it looked like Mr. Gower was in the hospital He went in the room Mr. Gower worked at there he was. Marcus yelled, 'Come on Mr. Gower lets go home right now.'             But Mr. Gower couldn't leave. This was his job now and if he left he would leave many disappointed people. Marcus agreed with Mr. Gower and let him stay. Marcus would love to visit Mr. Gower one day. So he drove to visit Mr. Gower every day. When Marcus was old enough he got a job to become a doctor and he got the job! He got to work with Mr. Gower and all the other doctors and nurses. But the best part is that he got to meet snd sometimes play with Mr. Gower at work every day.

It can go up and down the stairs and can make? tight turns, and it can even roll through water.  The robot is small, but it is strong.  Gemini-Scout carries food, water, and other supplies.  It can even drag hurt people to safety.            Wherever it goes, Leo collects information.  For example, it tests the air for gases and then tells when the air is safe. It was another busy, tiring day at the hospital for Mrs. Peterson, a nurse.  She wished desperately that there was a robot that could help her do the job for her as she eyed the dusty lump of metal that had a shape like a robot.  Miraculously, the clump of metal came to life and wheeled itself in front of Mrs. Peterson.  She jumped, and nervously asked, 'Who are you?'           The robot replied, 'I am Mr. Gower, a robot, here to help you do work that nurses and doctors do.'           'Oh, I see.  So there are robots that help around in hospitals.  How convenient!' Mrs. Peterson exclaimed with a smile, now not so suspicious.  She then ordered the robot to finish her duty for the rest of the day.           The next morning, Mrs. Peterson found Mr. Gower in the corner of a room not moving.  She gently shook the robot, but Mr. Gower still did not budge.  At last, Mrs. Peterson decided to finish her shift at the hospital without him.  When she arrived home late at night once again, a thought occurred to her, Doesn't Mr. Gower run on batteries?  Instantly, she was relieved.  She had forgotten that all robots needed to be recharged at the end of the day.  That meant her work load would be cut in half if Mr. Gower worked alongside her every day.            For the next couple of years, everything went smoothly as Mr. Gower worked with Mrs. Peterson at the hospital.  Mrs. Peterson was extremely content because her work was cut in half.  From then on, she lived happily ever after.

It was freezing.  I lay in bed, and I tightened my grip on my soft blanket and opened my eyes.  Something seemed different.  'Is it the cold?' I thought, 'No, it's always cold here in New York.'  I looked around my room.  Through the dim light of the moon, I saw the baby blue color of my walls, my wooden desk, and my robot, Mr. Gower, sleeping on my desk.  'Wait a minute... How can Mr. Gower sleep?  He's not even alive!'  At the sound of my voice, Mr. Gower woke up.  Excitement filled the room.  I jumped up, and ran up to him.                He seemed very happy to see me, and he said in his robotic voice, 'Hello Erin, nice to meet you.'  I was so excited and surprised that no words came out of my mouth.  All I could do was to stare at him, because my kindergarten teacher never told me the robot we made would come alive.                 When words finally came out of my mouth, questions spilled out, 'Hi Mr. Gower.  Why are you alive?  When did you come alive?  Where did you come from? and What...'              Mr. Gower cut me off, 'Please save the questions for tomorrow morning.  Let's go to sleep.  I am really tired.  And with that said, he fell backwards, snoring.  Almost paralyzed, I went back to bed.  I couldn't sleep, but somehow, I soon fell asleep.        The next morning, I woke up, and remembering Mr. Gower, I looked at my desk, but he was'nt there!  Thinking of what my parents would do if they found him, I jumped out of bed and ran downstairs.  Thankfully, I found him peacefully eating a bowl of cereal. 'Would you like to go to the hospital with me, Erin?' he asked.         'Why?' I asked, 'Are you sick?'        'No, I go there everyday to help the doctors and nurses bring medicine to the patients.'        'Cool!  I'll gladly go there with you.'  When we got to the hospital, I saw many doctors and nurses very busy.  However, when they saw Mr. Gower, all of them started calling him.  Mr. Gower went over to put batteries in himself, and started getting busy.  I watched as I sat in the waiting room, and thought, 'Wow, he seems very important here.'  That day, I realized that the future has arrived.

Robots to the Rescue!   by Sophia Parker              Robots can be a big help. They can help in all daily life purposes. Have you ever wish you had someone to help you? Well, robots are now becoming more popular. They can play with you, and even save your life! Robots can go inside a volcano and find craters, send images to the scientists, and tell when the volcano will erupt. Robots also can go inside mineshaft and rescue people or bring food, water, and other supplies. They also help doctors by bringing medicine to the doctors so they can focus on important tasks.       Driving Robots         Have you ever wondered what its like to sit back and relax while you are driving? Well now scientist  are making cars that drive all around and you don't have to touch the steering wheel! They can see much better than humans can see when driving a car. This idea is safer because you don't have to keep your eyes on the road and you can text and call while driving. There have been hundreds of incidents from people dieing or having serious injuries. Scientist think that this is a safer way to drive.       Conclusion           In conclusion I think that having robots all over the world will be a big help. People will have easier life's than they do now. This of course, will happen in the future. So be prepared, it will be a wonderful time!

Robots can do lots of things. Some are remote-controlled. This robot is called Gemini-Scout. It does research and rescue work in mines under the ground. The robot is less than two feet tall and has wheels. It can go up and down stairs and make tight turns, and it can even roll through water. The robot is small, but it is strong. Gemini-Scout collects information. For example, it tests the air for gases and then tells miners when the air is safe.               Another robot has an interesting job. This robot is called Dante 2. It climbs into volcanoes to gather information for scientists. Like a spider, Dante 2 has eight legs. This robot is a very fast climber. It is different from other robots. Talk about fast climber! It can tell scientists whats in the volcanoes, and/or what they do in the inside. Scientists can now study an up-close volcano. Isn't that cool?               Now, this robot is very helpful. It works in hospitals, and it helps doctors and nurses bring medicine to patients. This robot is called Mr. Gower. Mr. Gower looks like a small cabinet on wheels. The body of the robot is a stack of locked drawers that store medicine. Nurses and doctors can unlock the drawers when the medicine is really needed. It can ride elevators, steer though hallways, and move things that get in the way. Not only does it work long days, but Mr. Gower can talk. It has been programmed to say hundreds of phrases. It can say 'Calling elevator' or 'Your delivery is here.' Mr. Gower does work that doctors, pharmasists, and nurses used to do. This allows them to focus on other important tasks.               This robot is also helpful. It picks fruit, and this robot is called an Agribot. Agribots are not yet wisely used, but farmers are very interested in what these robots can do. Because picking a strawberry is different than picking an apple, agribots come in all shapes and sizes. Some even have giant arms that are towed behind trucks. The agribots are like robot farmers. They pick up the fruit, and bring it to the farmer.                Now, the last robot is very, very cool. These robots are called 'Playful Robots.' Robots can, believe it or not, be just like animals, they can even act like them! There is one difference, though. You don't have to take them outside or feed them! Some robots can even play all by themselves. Students in Oregon have created robots that can play hockey or shuffleboard on their own. All year, it takes students hours, and hours to work on robots everyday. The robots can grab the puck, turn, twist, and compete to score. In the final test, the robots must push the puck to the goal without being told what to do.

One Christmas morning, Devyn woke up from a bright flash in front of him. When he opened his eyes it was just his parents taking a picture. 'Merry Christmas', they said. Mom dad i`m 15 now, i can wake up by myself. Come downstairs. Fifteen more minutes please. My parents walked out of my room with a grin.      As i went downstairs I noticed a box about as tall as me it was normal size but tall. I ran the rest of the way down the steps and jumped on the couch.      Can I open it? My parents nodded. I jumped up grabbed the wrapping paper with both of my hands and ripped off the wrapping. It was just a big brown box.      When i opened the large brown box all i saw was a piece of paper and a shovel. My dad asked if I liked it, yes i answered unsuringly.   What is it, I asked. My dad explained there was a story that goes with it that he heard at work. There was some sort of treasure out in the forest of hands.      About three hours later i called my friend Drake to come over and help me find this treasure my dad was talking about. Drake and his girlfriend Natalie both came over to help me find the treasure. We were digging for about five days until finally Drake was digging far away and he yelled 'I found something'!     Natalie and I both ran over to where Drake was and we were digging around the object to try and see what it was. I.. its a robot. We all stared at the seven foot tall robot all dirty and rusty. I called my dad to come bring his truck over and help us lift it out. My dad tied a rope around the robot and then the back of his truck and pulled it out.     As we got home We put him on the floor of the garage, I noticed a green switch. I flicked it up and the whole garage turned blue from the robots eyes. The robot looked around and jumped up, ran into the corner and was blurting out random numbers.      We all freaked out and we tried to calm it down and finally it stopped. We all introduced ourselves trying to calm it down, He also introduced itself. My dad quietly whispered ' is this the treasure? I sure hope not'. The robot heard what my dad said and it said, yes i am the treasure. The robot grabbed its chest and ripped it off, There were about thrity-two apple sized diamonds that fell on to the floor We all fell to our knees and searched thorugh the diamonds. The robot explained that its creator created it to protect the precious diamonds and we all took our share for finding the robot. The robot had left back to his creators grave and layed there for the rest of its life.

Plan:       Intro:   Emmie(a 5 yr. old) loves to play but all she can do is train to go to kindergarden for b-day she gets a robot and it only comes to life when her parents are not home she loves it because it always plays with her thinks its games but the robot teaches her   First:   first alphabet games with prizes competition friends come over   Third:   reading Picture books (make up the words) little easy books normal books   Second:   writing letters(drawing book) cursive block letters   Conclusion:   school comes she already knows everything smart has fun   helps other kids           Writing:          Once upon a time a little girl named Emmie(who hated school and work) had to start preparing for kidergargen. Oh well she thought and went back upstairs.When she came into her room she was even more amazed the robot had come to life. Yay! she thought but little did she know what was going to happen next.          Emmie wanted to play with the robot but he had different plans for her. 'So young lady,' he said 'What shall we start with.' 'Games, games and more games!' she shrieked. 'Ok lets start by calling all your friends and telling them to come over.' The kids didn't even notice that tebahpla was alphabet backwards until Ben said, 'Congrats kidos you all know the alphabet now. Wasn't that fun? But guess who's the smartest... Emmie!' THE ROBOT IS ALIVE!' but of course the parents didn't belive her and just smiled and said, 'We're glad you like is Em.' An went away to work. Emmie skipped up to her room and said, 'So Ben what game are we playing today?' The robot laughed and gave her a book that said gniward srettel(drawing letters) 'Oh that looks fun!' she said. And so she started working on the book when she finished Ben said 'Glad you liked it now you know how to write letters. Now if you liked that do you want to learn how to write fancy letters.' Thanks for the robot,' in cursive, block letters, and regular writing.          On Monday(a week before kindergarden started) Ben told Emmie it was time for her to learn to read of course like always Em started complaining but still decieded to learn to read. The Robot That Came Alive    I was told that my best friend got a remote for her birthday and I went to check it out. When I got too curious and tried to help her brother get away from a robot. I made a terrible mistake.                         On Friday afternoon I was sitting on the back porch of my neighbor's house sipping on a tall glass of lemonade  when I heard a faint, but strange, noise. I looked up to see my best friend, Morgan, standing there. She was holding a remote that looked like it controlled the television set and VCR. I asked her what it controlled and why she had it. she said 'We'll it was my birthday yesterday and my mom gave me the remote but didn't tell me what it controlled. I wanted a new remote for my television because my brother, Jarred, won't stop throwing it on the ground during his temper tantrums over what he wants to watch, but it wouldn't work. I think my mom hid one of my presents in the basement and I'm determined to find it.' 'I didn't know that you had a brother, how old is he?' 'He's six.' she said.                          I told her that I would help her find what it went to, so we walked down the porch stairs and she unlocked the basement door with a spare key. She always keeps it under the door mat that no one else knows about but us. When we got in I didn't know where to look first, all I could see was stacks of Jarred's old toys. I saw strollers with action figures in them, a really small basketball goal and a little basketball to go with it. I thought I saw a little head popping out from behind storage bins and it was him alright. Morgan told him to help us look for what the remote went to and he wouldn't unless we gave him some money. we tricked him by saying that a pennie was worth fifty dollars. He didn't believe us so we gave him a dime and said it was worth ten dollars. Apparently that was more believe able to him.                After a while I got thirsty and Morgan was, too. We went back outside and sat on the swings while I drank the rest of my lemonade. Morgan got a Pepsi and a Mountain Dew and a very tall glass. I was thinking about what she was going to do and she mixed both of them into that really tall glass and put  a candy cherry in for good taste. We had been sitting there for about ten minutes when we heard screaming coming from the basement. A wierd looking robot was holding Jarred by the arm and dangling him over a huge tub full of old action figures. I knew they were his because of the way he looked at them.               I inched closer and closer to the robot until I saw writing on its arm. It said  'My name is Nik if found please return to this address.' and had her address on it. her address was 2431 Cranberry Road.               It came at me and I yelled 'Morgan push the unlock botton on the remote, Aaahhhahahaha.' It dropped Jarred and got on all fours like a dog and made wierd noises that kind of sonded like an electronic bark. she used the remote to make it different animals and the n kept it as a duck.               When we got done playing with it we went in the house to tell her mom what happened. She said that she knew we would find it so she wanted us to go on a little adventure. Since everything was okay I went back to my house and found a remote on my bed with a sticky note on it that said 'You have to find the present or you don't get it.mom. The process started all over again and I had a great time finding the little robot.

'Bolt?' Screamed 12-year-old Allie, trying to find her dog.   'Bolt!' She tried again.  She tapped her foot, figuring out what had happened.  'Alex I know you took Bolt!'   Alex, her older brother came out of a closet, holding the small dog and laughing.   Allie groaned and snatched her dog away.  She ran up to her room and plopped on her unmade bed.   Snap, snap.   'Hello?' Allie called, facing the way she thought the sound was coming from.  She knew it couldn't be Alex, since she just saw him downstairs.   Snap, snap, snap.   'Whatever,' Allie said, deciding to ignore the sound.  After all, they lived in an old house, so it was probably just some creaking floorboards.   Allie burried her face in her pillows and fell asleep.       'Huh?' She croaked about an hour later.  A large figure towered above her.   'Alex, go away!'  She threw her pillow at who she thought was her brother.  But the figure stayed put.   Finally, the large body stepped into the light, where she could finally make out who or what it was.    'Ohmigosh,' she said, stunned.  The figure wasn't her brother at all.  It was a large robot.   'What the heck?!'  She turned away and closed her eyes, thinking it was all a weird dream.   'Oh, don't go!'  A sweet voice pleaded.   Allie turned to face the robot, amazed that it could speak.   'Where did you come from?'  Allie asked quietly.   'Your brother,' the robot replied.   'What?'   'You know how he always creats things?'   'Yeah.'   'Well, he made me about a week ago, but I have no idea how I'm alive.'   'Um, okay.'  Allie said, surprised that her brother could actually be successful. 'What's your name?'   'Oh, I never really thought of that.  Um...'   'It's okay, I'll name you.  How about Mia?'   'Okay!'  Mia replied, cheerful.   'So, um, why did you come in my room?'   'So I could kill you.'   'WHAT?!'  Allie shrieked.   'What, what?'  Mia cocked her head to the side, innocently.   'Nothing, I must be hallucinating, or something.'   'Okay.  Why don't you go back to sleep.  I'm sorry I woke you up.'  Mia sounded sincere.   ''Kay, thanks!'  Allie retrieved her pillow and fell asleep.       While Allie was sleeping, Mia stayed put for a while, making sure Allie was not awake.  After about 10 minutes, Mia tip-toed down the stairs and got a hammer from the cabinet.  Next, she walked back up to Allies room, and fake hit her on the head with the hammer a few time, making sure she knew where to hit.   'Allie?'  Alex yelled from the hall.   Mia didn't seem to hear, because she was continuing to do what she was doing before.   Alex saw Mia, and quickly rushed inside to save his sister.   Knocking the hammer from her hand, he picked Mia up and chucked her out the window.   'ALLIE WAKE UP!'  Alex shrieked.   'WHAT do you want?'  Allie jerked up from her sleep, alert.   'My old invention, a robot, was about to kill you with a hammer!'   'You mean Mia?'   'Whatever.'   'Um, okay, so where is she?'   'I, uh, threw her out the window.'   'Are you insane?!'  Allie rushed to the window to see the robot passed out on the ground.   'Don't do that.  Next time just call the cops.'  Allie insisted.       Together, the called 9-1-1 and told them the details.  The cops seemed skeptical about taking a robot to jail, but finally gave in.  After that day, Alex and Allie tried to never fight again, and created a really strong bond.  Mia was never heard from again, and probably never will be.

It was the beginning of summertime, and all the other kids were outside playing in the warm sun, but not Jimmy. For months, he had been in his garage, working on making a robot. Jimmy's biggest dream was to be tall. Jimmy had always been the shortest kid in school, and he always got picked on for that. It made him furious. So he came up with an idea to make a gigantic robot that could lift him up so he'd feel tall.       Jimmy's dad came in to the garage. 'Hey Jimmy, want to go throw the baseball around with me?'       Jimmy didn't look away from the robot. 'Not now, Dad. Maybe later.'       Jimmy's dad sighed. 'Okay, maybe later...' Jimmy's dad wished Jimmy would come out of the garage sometimes, but he knew how much that robot meant to Jimmy.       Weeks went by, and it was the middle of summer. Finally, one night, Jimmy was so close to finishing his robot. His robot arms and legs could extend just by the touch of a button on his remote controller. Only one step had to be finished, and that was adding the head. Jimmy was tired that night, so he thought he'd do it in the morning.       As Jimmy was walking up the stairs, he heard a loud crash. However, he was so tired that he just ignored it. All night, Jimmy dreamed of what his robot would turn out like. He imagined his robot lifting him up so he could dunk on the basketball hoop, like the other tall boys at school.       The next morning, Jimmy ran downstairs excitedly. When he walked into the garage, he screamed. His mother and father came rushing in. When they saw the big commotion, they gawked at the huge mess of various robot pieces laying around.       Jimmy went and picked up the pieces. He sadly laid them on the work bench, but didn't bother to put it back together. His father took him out for ice cream to make him feel better, but it didn't help.       Jimmy sat on the sidewalk all alone, with his head hung down as he watched his ice cream drip onto the ground. He was too upset to eat. 'Jimmy, what's wrong?' He heard an unfamiliar voice behind him. He turned around to see who it was, and...       It was his robot! He was too shocked and surprised to say anything, so he just stared. His robot came over, picked him up, and spun him around. Jimmy was so happy and surprised! Jimmy and his robot became best friends.

The Muffin Man                  One foggy morning, a plane flew over a valley in California. The plane was experiencing problems. Then the plane went down, like a bird that didn't know how to fly, and crashed. Dust whirled into the air and created it's own sandstorm, then it settled down to rest on the ground where it came from. A small boy who saw the plane ran to the crash site. Out from the plane rolled a piece of machinery the size of person. It rolled until it hit a rock that pushed a button. The machine's lights flickered like firefly, then steadied to solid colors. It appeared to have a head, a body, limbs, and lights on its highest section that resembled a face. It then stood up on two legs. The boy watched in amazement. The machine looked at him. 'I am the Muffin Man,' it said. 'I am a robot.' It didn't talk in the choppy voice you'd think a robot would talk in. It sounded just like a normal person. 'I'm John,' said the boy. The Muffin Man looked at John with its bright, colorful eyes. 'I am a robot that makes muffins. It is my destiny to make delicious muffins.' John thought this was amazing. 'Can you make me a muffin?' John asked. The lights on the Muffin Man's face showing a smile shut off and in the same instant new lights turned on that showed a frown. 'I'm afraid I can't,' he said. 'A couple of my parts had fallen of of the plane in the crash. There are only two but they could be anywhere, and now I will not fulfill my destiny.' John wanted to help the robot. 'What if I help you find the parts?' he said. The Muffin Man smiled and said, 'Really, you would do that?' John said, 'Sure.' 'Okay,' the Muffin Man said. 'Then let's go!' John and the Muffin Man set off to find the missing muffin making parts.                 The first place they went was the city. Enormous skyscrapers towered over John and the Muffin Man. The part could be anywhere. 'I wish I didn't have to walk,' John said. 'Well, why didn't you just say so?' said the Muffin Man, and just like that, he twisted and turned and transformed into a go-cart. 'Get on,' said the Muffin Man.' John got on the brightly colored cart and sped away. They flew through the city on the small cart, but they didn't find any parts. Then John spotted a construction site. 'Let's look in there,' John said, and they sped through the gates. Then there, in the middle of the site, was a piece of machinery. It had words on writing on it that was cut off. ' There,' said the Muffin Man, 'that's one of the pieces. The construction workers must have thought it was for their building.' Then a construction worker saw them. 'Hey, kid, what do you you're doing here?' he said. 'Step on it, Muffin Man!' yelled John. Without hesitation, the Muffin Man accelerated toward the part. John snatched off the ground and the Muffin Man drove up an improvised ramp. They soared over the fence and raced out of the city.                The go-cart stopped at a small shop outside the city and transformed back into the Muffin Man's normal shape. 'That was close,' he said. John nodded. 'Just one more part,' John said. Then he noticed the sign in front of the shop. Muffin Factory, it said. John noticed a big truck pulling into the back of the factory. 'Hmmmm.' John thought about something. 'Follow me,' he said to the Muffin Man, and they followed the truck. Two men started unloading packages. John noted what they took out: muffin mix, blue berries, chocolate chips, vannilla, muffin mixer-wait, muffin mixer. John noticed the mixer had writing on it that looked like it matched up with the writing on the Muffin Man's other part. That was it. 'Muffin Man,' said John, 'transform into a go-cart, I've found the last part.' 'Really?' said the Muffin Man. 'Really,' said John. When the men weren't lokking John snatched the part and ran back to the cart. The Muffin Man immediatly sped away just as the men turned around and realized the part was missing. The go-cart stopped back at John's house and transformed back into the Muffin Man. 'Now let's make some muffins,' said the Muffin Man. He put the parts together and the words spelled, 'Muffin Man.' John pushed a green and the mixer started to turn. John watched as the Muffin Man created creamy and delicious muffins. The Muffin Man shouted with joy. 'YES, I AM FULFILLING MY DESTINY AS THE MUFFIN MAN. WWWWHHHHHHAAAAAAA!' he screamed, and out popped a delicious muffin. John bit into it. It was the most wonderful he had ever tasted. 'We should do this every day,' said John. 'We will,' said the Muffin Man, and they went into John's house for the night.

'What is it?' my friend Lily asked. 'I don't know,' I said. My name is Ashley. My friend Lily and I are at the junk yard. We were trying to find something interesting for our science project. This is interesting but, what is it? 'A metal person!' Lily exclaimed. 'What?' I asked. 'Look there's a head, an arm, and I think that is a foot,' she said. I sighed, 'It's a robot.' It was pretty cool, but how was I going to use it for my science project? Meanwhile, Lily kept rambling on about how she loved anything to do with robots and knew everything about them. 'They can save live you know,' she informed me, 'they save miners trapped in caves, carry off injured people, and even bring medicine to hospital patients!' 'Yes, but can they get me an A+ on my science project?' I wondered out loud.           As soon as I said that, I heard a metallic voice reply, 'Yes.' For a split second I was surprised. 'Stop messing with me Lily!' I scolded. I then turned around. The robot we had found was staring back at me. I nearly fainted! I slowly backed away, in fear that the robot might hurt us somehow. Lily, on the other hand, just kept gaping at the robot. 'What's your name? What type of robot are you? Is it really true that you can help us with our science project?' Lily asked the robot all at once. The robot looked very confused, I know I would have been. 'I am MultiBot.' It said,' I have all the skills of robots such as Gemini-Scout, Dante 2, Mr. Gower, and an agribot.' Lily's jaw hit the floor. 'What else can you do?' asked Lily eagerly. 'As well as working I can also entertain people by singing, dancing, and even playing music,' replied MultiBot.           I have to admit it's fascinating to see this robot but, I just really want to know how it could help me get an A+ on my science project. As if reading my mind, the robot said, 'For your science project, bring me and pretend that you invented me. If they ask how I was invented, I will answer that for you.' This robot is amazing! 'If you can do so much, why are you in a junkyard?' I asked. It didn't reply. I guess it was a sore subject. Do robots even have those? I shook off the thought. The science fair was in a couple of days and this robot was in no shape for presentation.            At my house Lily and I polished, waxed, oiled, and repainted MultiBot. He looked as good as new. The day of the fair, Lily and I fixed up MultiBot one last time and headed to the school where the fair was being held. 'I hope this works Ashley,' said Lily with a shaky voice. I could tell she was nervous, I was too. 'Don't worry Lily,' I whispered. After the judges had viewed all the projects, they went on stage to announce the winner. I crossed my fingers. Everything had went smoothly with our project but I was still very nervous. 'The first place winning team is: Ashley and Lily with their MultiBot invention!' announced a judge. Lily and I cheered as loud as we ever had before. Many other contestants gave us dirty looks but we didn't care. We got an A+ and a gigantic trophy after that. Sadly MultiBot broke after the science fair; Lily and I didn't know why. We were very sad and Lily cried for a week. Lately, in my sketchbooks, I have been designing a new, improved MultiBot. I hope my design is built one day in the future. I know I would see him again someday, I just feel it.

Robots were never even thought possible just over 100 years ago. Zoom to today and you have robots everywhere. Robots that help in the mines, explore vocanoes, are assitants in hospitals, can farm and pick fruit, dance, sing, their is even a robot that is a car that is self piloted. All of this has a huge impact on everyday human life. Some even save lifes in ways you never would've thought possible. You may even think that these robots are miniscule, or non-needed in our enviroment. Some inventors would beg to differ.        Gemini Scout is a robot that helps in the mines. This small robot is cabable of many things. For exapmle, it can collect information, climb stairs and take sharp turns, help hurt miners, and help rescue crews get to the wounded. This robot is small, but strong. Gemini is a remote-controlled robot, and the device to control it is similar to those in a video game. So if you have ever played a video game, than the controls to Gemini will probably be quite familiar.          Dante 2 is a very interesting robot that helps scientists in many ways. Dante is used to navigate volcanoes. It can collect information, find vents and holes in the volcano. The robot can also withstand extreme heat and would go places where scientists never thought could be explored.          Mr. Gower is a medical robot that helps in hospitals. Gower runs on batteries, and can work long days without fatigue. Certain features that this robot has are;   100s of phrases Can deliver medicine Dosen't need to be paid          This Robot would save many lifes and has a very high potential when they and if they are mass produced.           Agribots will also have a big impact on lives. These robots have been programed to farm, harvest, and in some cases, pick fruits. These robots are still prototypes are are being experimented on. However, that didn't stop them from making and growing their own garden.           The Google car is a car that is self-driven, or in other words, dosen't need a person to drive it. This is, again, another robot that has the potential to save lifes. The Google car dosen't text, drink, tire, fatigue, or get distracted whilst driving. The way that it works is the censors on the roof, back, and front of the car will sense where the car is going, and it will generate maps to the passengers while its moving, almost like a GPS. A problem that Google faced was getting this legalized and making a law that these can be on the road. Then, in Nevada, a law was passed saying that these self-driven cars were in fact legal.           As you can see, there are many robots out there that are going to, and may already, have a large impact on our everyday human life. These robots may even end up saving our life someday. Some of these fine inventions may not be available for quite some time, but we can only hope, that the wait will be worth it.

Robots Story       Plan       1.  There are many different kinds of robots   2.  Robots can save lives   3.  Robots can help collect data   4. A paragraph for each robot           Story       Robots are a new way to help people that need it.  Robots can collect data, save lives and much more.  They help scientist, doctors, miners and animals.  Each robot has a different role that is unique.  Some robots can move by themselves and some use a remote.  Some robots can climb volcanoes and some can collect data.  Clearly, There are many different types of robots and roles.        Robots can save lives by helping miners and rescue teams.  The robot that does this is called the 'Gemini-Scout'.  The Gemini-Scout is a remote controlled robot that does search-and-recuse work in mines under ground.  The robot is small and fast.  It is very strong and can carry many supplies for people.  It also has a two way radio to let the trapped miners talk to the rescue team.        Robots can also help humans collect data and go where humans can not. The 'Dante 2' is a great example of that.  The Dante 2 climbs volcanoes to gather information.  It looks for vents, holes or craters and collects information about gasses.  The robot has eight legs (like a spider) to make it easier to climb and get in small spaces.  Now, scientists can collect more information and still stay safe.       Robots can act like doctors too.  'Mr. Gower' is like a nurse in the hospital.  Mr. Gower is like a cabinet on wheels.  Doctors and nurses can store medicine a tools in there and Mr. Gower will bring them what they need when they need it.  Mr. Gower is also very strong and smart.  He can pull up to 500 pounds and ride elevators.  Mr. Gower can even talk.  Mr. Gower is now even helping to save lives.       Robots can even plant and cook. The 'Argibot' can pick fruit and vegetables and plant them too.  Some can move around and some have very long arms.  The Argibot can grow almost anything with no human input at all.  The 'Massachusetts Institute of Technology' is hoping one day the Argribots will become common of farms all over the world.       Clearly, Robots are a very good idea and we should make more.  They would make life easier for not only doctors, miners, scientists, and cooks but for everyone.  With this data and helpfulness they will one day make the world a better place.  They already are starting to.  Clearly, robots are the next generation of everyday life.

'Let's go eat!' yelled Mom. 'But, Mom, I'm sick, remember!' I cried from the couch. Jessica came over earlier to keep me company and knew I wasn't really sick. I was glad she din't say anthing. 'Fine, we will bring you back some egg rolls, stay here and do not go anywhere.' she said sternly as she and Dad walked outside to the car. As soon as door closed, I jumped up mand started yelling, 'Yes, yes, yes!' I and Jessica had planed this whole set up. I was not sick and now we were home alone and able top explore the house. My family had just moved in a few days ago, so we were ready to sneak around.       'Hey Isabel! Why don't we check the basement?' Jessica said. I responded by opening the trap door with a rickety ladder that leads down into the basement. I had to connect the string on the top of the door to the hook on the celing to keep it open. As we climed down, I began to rethink this whole plan. Here we were, climbing down into a small dark undiscovered room at the bottom of my house. I heard a thump when Jess hit the bottom. I fumbed around for a light switch. As it flickered on, I heard another thump. 'What was that?' I whispered. We both looked upward. The door, our only escape, had closed. The string had snapped, and the auto lock looked the door. The day we moved in, my parents had told me to always connect the string to the hook. I guess they hadn't expected the string to break.       We looked around for another door, but that was it. 'Why don't we make a robot?' Jessica said. She was holding up an old robot kit. I looked at the cover. Creat your own mini robot! it screamed in bold red letters. I dumped the contents on the floor. We connected all the pieces. The robot was a small little cube with wheels on the bottom and a control pannel on the top. I pressed one of the three buttons. The robot rolled forward, toward the lader. Sudenly, it started to climb up. It was small, but strong. It pushed it's little arms up and the trapdoor came open. It had been close to an hour since we got trapped, so we sprinted out. 'Can we be friends?' a voice said. We turned and looked at the robot in my hand. 'Yeah, sure.' we said in union. We took the robot upstairs and put him in my room. To this day he still stays in there. He even follows me to school. Eventually, we told my parents, and they joked that they were glad the robot didn't take over the house. We never did find out were the robot kit came from, and we never went back into the basement.

I told him that apparently I could do whatever I wanted to because I owned the stereo.                                                                                                                               Then, he said 'I'm sorry I did not introduce myself, by the way my name is Bob'.'I think you can tell I am not very patient, at all'.'Also you might of noticed that I have some sort of anger issues'.'Will you two girls accept my apology and forgive me for being rude'?We said 'Yes of course we will Bob'. I will never forget that mean yet pretty nice Bob. That was the robot that came alive one day. Maybe I will bring Bob back another day.Also a little tip please do not try this at home.

'We did it Jonathan'. 'We built a robot!' Dr. Callington and his assistant Jonathan, had been working on this robot for months. 'What will we name it?' asked Jonathan. Dr. Callington thought for a moment.'We shall name it KK-3.' 'Lets turn it on.' Jonathan pushed the on button, and KK-3 popped to life. 'What did you program him to do?' Jonathan questioned. 'I programed him to to mix characteristics of animals together. And if anything goes wrong, he has a laser beam on his head.' Dr. Callington replied excitedly.                                                          The next day, business as usual, Jonathan opened the cupboared that KK-3 was stored in.  He got KK-3 out, but it wouldn't work. Jonathan then realized he forgot to turn it on. He got a shock when he pressed the button, and KK-3 fell apart. 'Uhhhh..... Dr. Callington, I think KK-3 is broken.' 'WHAT!? DO YOU KNOW HOW LONG AND HARD WE WORKED ON THIS??!!' 'Yess...bbut' Jonathan started, but then realized Dr. Callington was laughing. 'That's not the real KK-3.' 'I am.'       'Dr. Callington' tore his face off, reavealing the shiny metal head of KK-3. He laughed a truly mechanical laugh, and shot a sigle laser through some science formulas, burning a hole clean through them. 'What ddid yyou ddo wwith Dr. Callingtonn?' Jonathan stammered. 'I put him.... why would I tell you that?' 'Because I helped create you.' 'Fine. He's in the animal testing room. Good luck trying to get there.' The animal testing room was on the other side of the lab, meaning Jonathan would have to go through about 3 doors. He was pretty sure he could outrun the robot, but not the laser. KK-3 shot at random, while Jonathan ran and hid, only to have his hiding place blasted away. He ran for the door. He made it just in time. Since KK-3 didn't have the best aim, it was now shooting down parts of the ceiling. Jonathan had already made it to the ATR, while KK-3 was still getting through the rubble that he caused.       When KK-3 made it to the ATR, Jonathan still hadn't found Dr. Callington.The robot had learned his lesson about shooting things, and now he started to glow. 'What else could KK-3 do?' Jonathan couldn't remember. A hologram of a kangaroo tore away from the actual kangaroo. The same thing happened with a tiger. The holograms got closer and closer. Now Jonathan remembered. KK-3 could mix animals. The holograms collided, and left a new animal, body of a kangaroo, head of a tiger. The tigeroo kicked Jonathan until he was out cold, and then delivered the death bite. Dr. Callington had been killed, vaporized by the laser, so Jonathan could not find him.

Rockey               It was just an ordinary day. No one thought robots where something of our time, however of the future. I'm an inventor and I've been fooling with parts ever since a kid. My long life dream.... to make a robot that comes alive.             I've done drawings  for weeks, looking for the right materials for days, and wondering where to start for years. In my garage this morning I decided to use one of the old blueprints I made yesterday, it was of a robot that was 3 feet tall, and was silver with black wheels to move it around. It was just a box robot.             I decided to go to the junkyard to find some materials. I see old refrigerators, tires, cabinets, stoves, and even some cars. None of it seemed right. Until I walked into a pile of mulch which had a metal box on it that was hollow and silvery. It looked perfect.                                                         1 Hour later               Well I'm back in the garage I snatched a bunch of materials and I've built the entire body so far. I need to put in some wiring and get some help too.   I  called up my brother he says he knows how to wire things well and thinks he can do it for the robot tomorrow.                  Well my brother is here in the same garage with a whole lot of wires that I don't know what thy do. He started stretching cutting and tying things. Sometimes he asked for the red or blue wire or simply grunted about something he was doing. After hours of work he said ' Should work now!' He flipped a switch and not anything.               He went to the store and came back with more wiring and a computer chip thing he placed it in did more wiring and programming turned the switch..... And   nothing. He said he'd come back tomorrow.             I woke up during the night hearing a loud bank of what seemed to be old tools.   Clank Clank! I walked in the garage and there he was the robot we put together.   This was the moment I had been waiting for all my life. I dashed into the house grabbed a phone and dialed my brother up to come over and see now!                He was here in minutes. He told me everything was working perfectly he could walk talk and even  learn new things. We knew we would be famous for the robot we named   Rockey.                                                                        THE END

It was summer break,' Mom,' I yelled,' Can I have my friends come over?'        My mom replied,' Of course you can't Jordan,' (that was my name) This was the start of the reason of why I decided to build a robot (to have a friend all the time that always has time to play with me, since I don't have a sibling) and building a robot was easy to me because I studied all about it, but little did I now that trouble was awaiting me.        The next day, I went to the garage to find some parts because my dad was a mechanic. The second reason I looked in the garage was because the garage was a big room of junk and broken stuff which could go well for the robot. In the garage, I found batteries, the robots head, (which was from a broken toy robot) the robots body, (a not functional paper shredder because I had nothing to use) and the robots legs, (which were also from a broken robot) but no arms. I decided that I should look somewhere else because I couldn't find the arms so through the entire house and found nothing, but I still kept going and I didn't lose hope.        After a while,'That is it, I give up, I looked everywhere,' I thought. Then I remembered the time I got a bunch of claw grabbers as a prize, which was really convenient, but my mom kept it in a cabinet because it was to dangerous and she let nobody use it. That cabinet was in my mom and dad's room so I would have to sneak in and grab two for my robot. When I went in sneakily, I was really lucky that it wasn't locked so I opened the cabinet and I grabbed two cranes, but I was wondering why the cabinet wasn't locked even though the cabinet had a lock and why there were almost no more?        I started to assemble the robot, which I did in my room so no one would notice, which started with the legs. Second, I taped the paper shredder and the head together with the legs to make the robot. Lastly, I put the arms and I realized that the batteries were not needed because there was no where to put it.        Even though it didn't come alive I could imagine if it did, but one second later, it came alive! I couldn't believe my eyes when I saw it moving its arms and legs. It looked different than usual, but it didn't really matter. First, I thought that it was awesome how it could play with me, but I, then, stared panicking because I didn't know what would happen if my parents found out. I looked back at the robot, but to my surprise, the robot was gone!        I went down stairs to find the robot, but it did not take long to find the robot destroying everything! I realized that I should show it how to do stuff that is destructive so it won't destroy everything in my house. I started teaching the robot outside like how not to blast everything in sight and how he shouldn't run in the middle of the street, but the robot did anyway and was lucky that a car didn't come and run over the robot or if the robot pulverized it. after a long time of teaching, the robot learned nothing and I was at another hopeless situation.        Later that day, I saw an army van that stopped at our house and saw my robot. A man came down and asked,' Is that your robot because we are looking for a robot that looks just like that one.' I was worried because this guy looks like he is from the army and I think I am in trouble, but I tried to speak as calmly as I could.        ' This is my robot,' I replied.        ' Does this robot of yours destroy everything it sees?'        ' Yes, it does.'        ' That robot is ours which we trained to destroy everything.'        ' OK, I'll get him out right away sir.' After awhile, I came out with him and I gave him the robot and he said thank you and went away.        I went back home and I realized that the house was a wreck and I heard the garage open. I went up stairs and after a while I heard,' Jordan! Come down!'        'I knew I was going to be in trouble.' I thought.

The story starts the morning McKenzy woke up. She was tested on for week and has gotten a little bit of food and no sleep she was allowed 24 hours of sleep before she starts training.       McKenzy, wake up! Fear wound me up tight. My 'bot was ordering me and I had no choice but to follow its commands. I was on a metal table with a white cloth draped across my body; hooked at the ends. This is what they call a bed? I wondered. Let me getchya caught up on the amazing, wildly fun, and very intresting (aka the worst week of my life!) travels of McKenzy Zyban!       I turned 16 a week ago (yay!) Same week that I was abducted by the Starr minions (could it have waited? no.) Taken to Starr Inc. (would have been a dream come true if I wasn't covered with a black cloth and knocked unconcious) Experimented on (that's just sick!) Got a 'bot brain plungend into mine (yuck!) have been having hallucinations for the past 3 days (One of the mant treats you get when you are sharing a body with a robot) have not slept until now (which I have only 24 hours to do) I'm aching all over (ugh!)   The door to the room opened and a young male walked in with a tray of food and some clothes.        'I managed to snag some clothes and food for you Kenzy,' he said in a low voice. His name was Jalen, I remember that much. As soon as his name came up so did a flash of pictures my robot brain has saved. He had olive skin and dark eyes. He almost never smiles and he cares for me like he did to his little daughter, who abandoned him for Mr. Starr. He still had that depressed look in his eyes.        He unhooked the covers and handed me the clothes. I put on the white tanktop and the white sweatpants and the grey sweatshirt my mother gave to me on my birthday (they let ust keep one thing from home).        I stole a quick glance at Jalen and saw his hunched shoulders. There were tiny gray hairs mixed in with his rich black hair. When he turned to get some of the food I saw that his mouth was turned slightly down. Not that he smiles anyway.        'It will be okay,' I promised, although I don't even have control of my own destiny. I put my hand on his shoulder and gently jerked him around so he was facing me. I looked deep into his eyes like I was finding a portal into his mind. He gave me a small nod and went back to preparing the food.        I slid onto the table and got to work on my shoes. I unlaced the combat boots and frowned when they didn't fit. Would it be a suicide mission to get boots that fit!? I wondered. I slid them on and went to the makeshift bathroom. It had a sink and a mirror. There was a small latch on the wall for the door to the toilet. I went up to the sink and quickly washed last night off my face and watched it rid my face of impurities. One perfect afternoon in Stevenson Ranch, Jeff was riding his bike down the street when suddenly out of the corner of his eye, he saw some silver shining object sticking out of the the ground on the side of the road.Naturally his instinct was to go and investigate, so he did and what he saw made his heart stop... He saw a Gemini Scout robot, the last of its kind. This could be a great discovery if it turned on. So Jeff went home and the next day came back with battery's and put them into the slot on the robots arm.This was the moment of truth, will it turn on or will he be disappointed, and what he saw shocked him...IT TURNED ON! This was a great moment but the question was what was he going to do with it. How was he going to persuade his parents to let him keep him if he wanted to keep him, so that led him to his next question, does he talk.'Hello', Jeff said to the big pile of rusted metal,(only his arm that was sticking out was shiny).And to his surprise a mumble came out of the robot. 'mmmm mmmm,' It was just a mumble, but can it get words out, he tried again,'hello,' said Jeff. And out of nowhere the robot replied,'hello'. Jeff thought that the battery's wont last long so they went home.         'IM HOME', shouted Jeff.The only thing on his mind was persuading his parents to keep the robot, so after hours of arguing and debating he finally got the yes from his parents.And even though that moment was exciting he still had two things on his mind, how do you care for a robot, and the ROBOT POLICE,They hunt down and lock up every robot they see because they think that there bad.         After the hours of researching how to care for a robot it was time to go to sleep, and as he was closing his eyes he heard the most terrifying thing he could hear, the robot police.He knew he couldn't just not answer so when he did they asked him the expected question,'have you seen a robot recently,'   'No', he replied   'Ok well have a good night then'   Jeff thought to himself that that could have gone very bad.         In the morning when Jeff woke up he knew that the robot police would be back soon and he would have to be more prepared. And out of nowhere when he least expects it they were there again and they looked like they had found something, (which they did.) When he went to answer the door scared out of his mind the robot police told him to give up his robot and when he went to go and get him they were shocked by the sight that they saw, they knew how rare it was and replied,'where did you find this robot,'   He replied,'just on the side of the road,'   The officer replied with,'this robot belongs in a museum.'   'why'? Jeff replied with   'this is one of the rarest robots in history'!   Jeff thought to himself, if he should let him go or keep him (not like it was his choice).   The office said,'we are going to take him and put him in a museum'.   So Jeff just went with it and said,'Ok.'   And from that day forward he remembered that he had found one of the best historical finds in his time.

Alive?!!!   'Let's Go, Mom, we're going to be late!', I yelled. It was my 12th birthday and we were going to Jump 51-50. I invited 6 girls from school, including my very best friend, Taylor. When we reached Jump 51-50 I leaped out of the car and greeted everyone there waiting. They all handed me my presents and I was so excited. We all went in and played for 2 and a half hours. Everybodies parents picked them up except for Taylor's, she was coming back to the house with me, to open up all of the presents.       When we walked into the house, having to make 2 trips for the presents we went up into my room. Taylor wanted me to open up her present last. First, I opened up Julia's present, it was a nail polish set. The 5th present was from Emily, it was an itunes giftcard.       'Now the moment we've all been waiting for', Taylor announced. I quickly ripped  up the wrapping and stared at the gift plainly. It was a metal robot.       I didn' t want to make Taylor feel bad so I said 'Thank you'.   'I know you don't like it', Taylor replied.   'I do, I really do', I exclaimed.       'Well, that's not really my gift', Taylor said, 'this is'. I   unwrapped the gift as fast as a cheetah.       'O, MY GOSH!', I screamed. It was 5 tickets to 1 Direction.   I couldn't help my self but squeeze her.       'Ding, Dong', it was Taylor's mom ringing the doorbell. I picked up the robot and placed it on the floor of my closet. I followed Taylor down the stairs and said thank you to Mrs. Valdez, Taylor's mom. Taylor left, and it was already 8:30, so I decided to go to sleep, because it was a long day.    When I woke up I could smell waffles and bacon. It was the first day of summer vacation! When I opened my eyes I saw the robot I had put in my closet the night before.       'Mom', I immeditally yelled. NO ANSWER!!!   'Dad', I screamed. NOTHING AGAIN!!! I jumped out of my bed.       'Good morning, is everything okay'?, questioned the robot. Without answering I ran into Cassidy's bedroom, woke her up and explained what has happened. She hopped out of her bed and sprinted into my room.       'Hello, what do you want'?, Cassidy calmly asked the robot.       'What do you mean, I am Claire's best friend', the robot replied.       'How did you get out of that box?', I said pointing to the floor.       'Easy, I used my scissors', the robot exclaimed.       'What is your name?', Cassidy questioned.       'McKenzie', the robot answered. McKenzie, showed me and Cassidy everything she could do. She was awesome. We played for hours together, because she could make anything I   said appear and tranform into anything.       I ran to the phone, which was ringing, 'Hello mom, you'll never believe this, there is a robot named McKenzie that Taylor gave me for my birthday and it could talk and do everything I tell it to do.'   'Wow, I'll be home in 2 minutes', my mom said sarcastically. I told McKenzie that my mom would be home in a minute. I also told her my mom loved oatmeal raisin cookies, so she got a plate and put a bunch of oatmeal cookies on a plate. When my mom got home McKenzie handed her the plate. My mom wouldn't accept them. Cassidy came down and greeted my mom.   'Claire, may I speak to you in the kitchen?', my mom asked.   I obviously said yes.       'Claire, I want this robot to leave, who knows what it's planning?', my mom said.       'Mom, she is completly harmful, she is so sweet and she is not planning anything', I explained.       'Claire Bridget Johnson, you better listen to me and make this robot leave by next week!', my mom shouted. I stormed away and ran into my room. McKenzie joined me and calmed me down. She gave me some oreos. I told her everything my mom had said, and she understood. I also told her we needed to come up with a plan so my mom would let her stay.   I heard a knocking on my door and said 'Who is it?'       'Cassidy', Cassidy replied. 'Are you really upset', she asked.       'Yeah', I said. She explained to me mom just wants me to be safe. I already knew that. McKenzie left and went down to my mom, she came back in 2 hours and said that she was allowed to stay as long as she wanted to. I had no idea what she said but my mom came up and told me she was sorry. She said McKenzie was a great role model. I agreed with her and we had a group hug. McKenzie gave us all ice-cream.

'Brrriiiinnnnggg!' My alarm clock shouted at me. I quickly shut it off and groggily got out of my comfy twin sized bed. Today was the day. The day I got to work with my father.        'Honey! Go get ready!' My father shouts from downstairs. I lazily made my way to my bathroom and brushed my teeth.        'Circle, circle, circle.' I thought while I moved the brush in a circular motion over my teeth. 'Pancakes are circles. Man...I'm hungry. I want some pancakes.'        When I finished brushing my teeth I got dressed into my white, over the shoulder top, black tights, and my black and white vans. I grabbed my phone and headed downstairs.        'Good morning Roxy.' My mother said while handing me a plate filled with pancakes and some orange juice.        'Good morning mom.' I replied.        'Hurry up and eat because we have to get to my work at 9:00 sharp.' My father exclaimed, chewing on a pancake. I checked the time. '8:45' The clock said in big red letters.        When I was done eating my delicious pancakes, I picked up my phone and headed over to the car where my dad was waiting. He started the car and we drove off.        'So dad, where exactly is you're work? What do you even do?'        'I work across the street from the mall. I make robots and other new inventions.' He replied.        'Robots? You make robots?!' I nearly shouted at him.        'Indeed. They are actually very helpful. They help doctors, explore volcanoes, they can even play with you!'        As I thought about what he said, my mind started to think about the whole 'robot' invention. What do they even look like? I soon started to doze off.        'Roxy, wake up. We are here.' I heard my dad say in a sweet, angelic tone. I stepped out of the car.        'Whoa.' I said as I examined the gigantic building in front of my short, 13 year old body. As i walked closer, it was incredible. The silver tone, the amazing structure, the large glass dome on top. This place was unbelievable. My dads voice soon shot me out of awe.        'Honey, let's go.' He said a few steps ahead of me. As I walked inside a breeze of cold air gushed towards me, making me fall back a little. I gained backed my balanced and continued to walk down the, also, silver hall. We soon reached this large vault with a holographic keypad.         'Whoa.' I repeated. My dad entered the code and the vault door unlocked.        'You seem to be saying that a lot today.' He said with a grin on his face. We walked in to be greeted with chaos. People were running around holding different gismos and gadgets, there were people crowding around a small silver and,what seemed to be, blue figure.        'Mr. Smith we need you're help! Something is wrong!' A bald man shouted at my father.                                                                         My father ran over and started picking up all these tools. I stood there awkwardly and about 30 seconds after, my father finally looked up from his work and saw me.                                                       'Oh. I'm sorry Roxy. Just go to the gadget room and I'll be done in a second.' He pointed to a metal door. I started to walk over, but tripped on a dropped screwdriver.  While I was falling I hit a blue button. I don't think it will do any harm. I stood up and checked my knee. Great, I got a scrape. Oh, just jolly, it's bleeding too! Note the sarcasm. I limped over to the gadget room and saw what looked like a piece of metal. I examined it for about 10 seconds, but it suddenly started freaking out and moving around. I abruptly stepped back and watched it freak out. When it was calmed I walked back up and examined it.                                                                                                'Hello?' I said to it. A dash of fear is my voice.                                  'Hello Earthling. I am HTP-276. And you?' It replied in a robotic, Siri like, tone.                                                                                'Oh. Um. I'm Roxy.' I replied kind of freaked out. It wheeled over to me and observed my scrape.                                                           'I see you have a scrape. I will bandage it.' It bandaged my cut.        'Oh OK. Thanks.' I said.                                                                        'Do you like to shop? We shall go to the mall.' It said. I suddenly liked this robot a lot. I nodded my head in agreement and we went off to the mall.                                                                                                                               When we got back, I was sore. I can't believe my dad didn't notice I was gone. Sadly, it was time to go. I said my goodbyes to everyone and HTP-276. As soon as we got home, I ran to my bed and slept. Today was crazy, but I can't wait to go to my dads work again.

The factory was a disaster, broken fragments of walls and glass all over the place. My anger escaped me as I glared furiously at a rouge robot that was slightly damaged. I channeled all my anger into one last blow to destroy the robot. As rose, laser in my hand, aiming at the robots main controlling system and fired when a large green orb appeared around the robot. The orb deflected my shot shooting it back with an astonishing force that hit me in the chest. I had controll of my conciousness for a second then blacked out hitting the floor with a sickening crack while the stealthy robot snuck in the shadows.                   The year was 2035 where robots did everything. A human, as the robots called them, didnt even have to get off the couch if they wanted to go to bed, a robot would just carry them with padded hands so not to disturb the person they were carrying. Everyone was this lazy except for me. I was 13 and did everything myself and worked out and ran around the neighborhood reguarly. I didnt want to become, for all he money in the world, a fat blubbering walrus like the rest of the people in the world. I wouldn't like not being able to get up on my own and have a robot help me because i wasn't capable. These are the kind of things im against and that is why every morning my robot would try to help me up and I would defy it and make it go away for a while. Not being able to disobey orders, the robot leaves my room in a routine process. Robots were useful for some things like refilling your water bottle if there was no water nearby and I was thirsty. Small reasons like this are the only reason I keep mine around. I don't know why but for some reason I don't trust the mechanical beings.            I stayed fit for years before finnaly deciding I needed a purpose in my life. I didnt need a job because robots could produce however much money ou wanted. I was disgusted by that because I wanted the expirence of having a job and responsibility's. I knew was smart enough. Walking around town one day i saw a peculiar shop that said 'first ever robot run shop' it was called Weapons and Excesories. Mildly curious I walked inside where a robot greeted me and said 'would you like to try the weapon of the day?' 'Sure' I replied since I had nothing better to do. He handed me a small lazer gun that I had never seen before. It fit perfectly in my hand! The robot then took me out to the back of the store where it had a shooting range set up. There were 3 targets: a fake squirell that was 20 yards away, a fake blujay that was 200 yards away and a fake raccoon that was 500 yards away. Before the robot left he handed me a sniper edition of the lazer gun so I could hit the targets that were far away. Taking aim through the scope I focused about a half a centimeter above the raccoons head and fired. I missed! I took aim again a little lower and fired again. I missed again as i watched the aqua blue lazer fly past the raccoons right ear. Out of frustration I took aim directly on he raccoon's head. When I pulled the trigger almost intantly the raccoon exploded into millions of pieces leaving the base were it was held in a fiery inferno. 'Oh.' I said dumbly as i realized that the lazer was so fast that all you had to do was aim right on your target and it would hit. Quickly I took aim with the pistol and destoed the squrriel in a similar way. The pistol fired red lazers that suprisingly hit the squirell and insead of blowing it up melting into a red pool of boiling liquid. I began to take intrest in the robots craftmenship as I suddenly felt a little tired.            Walking back inside the shop the robot asked me if I had liked the test shots. I replied with a weary 'Yes'. 'Ah, you must be a little tired' the robot continued 'what I didn't tell you wasthat the weapon takes as much energy that it does if you were destroying it yourself.'. 'Great' I replied slumping over on a workbench suddenly much more tired than before. 'So for instance, if you had a really piled up amount of anger, hate, resentment, or were just really rested that day you would have more energy to use it'.  he rattled on as I lay doubled over on the bench suddenly feeling sick. 'how many shots did you take' he queried. '4' I replied. I can't tell if robots have suprise in their voice but if there was this was definetly the time I noticed it because the robot 'O my, the most I have taken without running out of energy was 3!' He continued to mutter to himself and I caught little bits and pieces of what he was saying like 'To think that a human could be stronger than a robot!'. A couple seconds later he replied and said 'You should be heading home'. I stopped his attempted motions to push me out the door with a difiant 'Wait!', 'how much do you want for the weapons' I said. The robot turned and returned with the pistol and Sniper versions of the lazer gun and said 'You are the first to come to my store and purchase so I will not charge you in electrobytes. All I want you to do is go home rest and be safe with these extremely dangerous weapons.' 'Okay' I hastily replied as I let my robot carry me home. For once I wasa happy that I had the robot to carry me home and praised him the second I was in my bed and drifted off to sleep.            The next day when I woke I again defied my robot's assistance and climbed out of bed fingering the weapons on my dresser. When I got outside robots were roaming the streets. I jumped in surprise as one pointed a metal finger at me and said 'your doom is coming soon'. That sounded more like a prophecy than a statement and quickly closed the door saying in my room the rest of the day. The next day the robots were still patrolling the srteets and confused asked my robot wat was going on and after he declared that he didn't know I ordered him to get me the highest quality armor at the weapon store. looking through my window at the robots I began to see some of their eyes glowing red hot like embers in a fire. almost insantly my robot returned to my room with a metal chestplate, leggings and a helmet which I quickly slipped on. He also produced 5 half yellow half green bolts of some sort. 'The robot manager at the store said you might need these due to the robot infestation but he said only to use them in dire need.' 'What happened' I asked 'The Director of the RMC, robot manufacturing company, shut down the factory. All of these robots have gone rouge swearing revenge on him if they find him.' 'Thats great' I said loading my lazer sniper with the new bolts. going to the window I took aim at a rouge robot and fired.             At first I thought it did nothing then after a second a shock wave began to progress through the lines of the robots disabling them all one by one. All had been disabled except for one that looked at me. It was larger than the others and had lots of weapons. It fired a rocket while my robot put up a sheild to protect me but got knocked backward into my bedroom wall in the process. I was a little angry that the large robot had  damaged mine. I walked outside with my pistol in hand and turned toward it facing it like it was a quickdraw in the old west movies. I drew, fired and hit the robot in the chest catching it off gaurd and doing a little damage but not melting it. It fired at me slicing through my armor and grazing my arm.I fired again and again until I was low on ammunition. Deciding it was no use I crept back inside. I decided to go around the back of my house and take refuge in someone elses house so the 1 rouge robot would't find me. Creeping along at the pace of a snail I finally reached my destination. As soon as I went through the back door, which I dicovered that was open, my jaw dropped to the ground.            The house was in ruins; bookshelves, doors, clothes,walls to bedrooms, and couches flipped upside down and torn to shreds cluttered the ground. Exploring a little further by going up the ragged stairs I looked around for anything useful or any sign of a human that once lived here. After discovering nothing I went back downstairs to hear a dull 'Thump' 'Thump' in one of the closet doors. I walked up to it for a second drew my weapon and flung the door open. Out fell a lean man that was bound and gagged. Blood dripped across his face as he hit the floor with a cry. Untying him but still keeping my weapon at the ready I noticed a patch on his right shoulder. It read 'Manager of RMC'! Dumbsrtuck I realized that the Robots had attacked this man because he shut down the manufacturing company that was making more robots. Groggily the man began to sit up and mutter something uncomprehendable. About 5 minutes passed before began to make some sense. I heard small parts like 'robots!' and 'no!'. Curious I waited for the man to recover enough to share his story. But as soon as he saw me he jumped back in suprise and hit his head on a table leaving him unconcious again. Not deciding to waste time I went to the window and surveyed the area for the 1 large and actually quite terrifying robot. He was no where in sight until I strained my eyes to see the very corner of the street where he was disapearing around a corner. Eager to see where he was going I started to slip out of the house, but the man was beginning to stir on the floor. Trying one last time I shook his shoulder trying to wake him up and finally he opened his eyes and I held him in place as to not let him hurt himself again. 'Who are you!' he demanded in a deep voice. 'A friend,' I replied 'and all I would like to know is if you have any idea why the robots are attacking and any information on the larger one with glowing eyes.' Yeah' he said 'I know about the big one. He was my robot and friend until I closed the  factory. Actually he may be trying to work the factory himself right now! I had better get over there!'  'No' I responded in a harsh voice 'you are in no condition to be fighting robots right now. But do you know how to destroy him?' 'Just melt his controlling pannel' the man said in a shaky voice. Blood was streaming out of his arm in addition to the small cut he had on his head. Unwillng to leave him like this I searched arond the house until I found what once was a bathroom and looked inside the cabnets until I found a first aid kit with bandages and wrappings. Returning to the room where the man lay unconcious yet again but this time from loss of blood I wrapped up all of his wound until it stopped bleeding and his heart was pumping normally. I pursued the robot with pure fury filled within me for what these robots had done to this man. Finding the factory fairly easy I walked inside to see the one robot in command hunched over a large pannel of buttons looking for the right one to press. Almost as soon as I walked in, weapon drawn, the robot whirled around with frightening speed and fired multiple lazers. Jumping to the side and watching the lazers explode in a shower of sparks on the wall I got up and channeled all my fury into one last blow. Aiming at the robot's controll system I fired. Just before the lazer hit, the robot created a green orb around it that blocked my shot and sent it richocheting back and hit me in the chest. I had conciousness for one second as I saw the robot slink into the shadows and then I blacked out.            Waking some time later to find my body aching I realized that my armor had melted off due to the shot I took at the robot.  Walking was hard for me since the groung seemed to be spinning below my feet so I crawled to where the robot had been when I was knocked out. Finding no trace of him I searched the factory for more clues as to where he went. Around the third bend I came up sucessful as I peered at him. He was at another controll pannel and this time turning gears and pressing buttons which meaned he had figured out the code. From my hiding place I drew my pistol ever so discretly took aim at his controlling pannel and was about to fire when my shoe rubbed against the concrete making a screeching sound. This sent him whirling like a top as he searched the room for me. I realized that I couldn't fail because I had no armor to protect me now. As he circled a corner in the room his controll pannel came into sight. I had little strength left but took aim and fired not heeding the robot at the weapon store's warning about overexerting myself. The lazer found its target and the room exploded with sparks as I backed around the corner to safety where I suddenly felt as if my breath had been taken away and at the last second, when I was sure that I would sufficate, it came back to me. I passed out wanting to do nothing more than sleep. I must have been out for a couple days because when I woke it was raining outside and the streets were deserted.            I quicky ran to the house where I left the man laying on the floor and found him exactly as he was before I left. After contacting the ambulance immediatly, they took him away and said he was going to be fine.  Going home and waching the news revealed that people were begining to come back out of their homes because they were previously hiding from the robots. The news reporter also said 'A heroic kid that was about 13 years old had been seen following the robot that put this town into destruction and destroyed it but we don't know who this kid is or where he lives!'. Good I thought to myself very good I don't think we are going to have any more robot problems for quite some time.
