Finn       Hi. I'm Isabelle. And here's my story about my robot named Finn.   It was in the middle of summer vacation, and I was really bored. I had done all of the things on my Summer Vacation To-Do List. I had already gone fishing, camping, hiking, swimming, I've slept in, went to bed a little later, watched almost all of the funniest videos on the Internet, played with my dog, cleaned my room, and much more. I have checked off every single thing on my list. but as I came down to the bottom of it, there was one thing left.   Make a robot.   And that is what I was going to do.   So then, I had asked my mother if I could go on an 'adventure.'   She then laughed and said, 'Be back before supper.'   Which was of course, 5 hours away. I had plenty of time to find robot parts. So I then grabbed my backpack off of the hook, grabbed my sweatshirt, my hat, and grabbed my bike from the garage. I then put my sweatshirt, my hat, and my backpack on, and I hopped on the bike and pedaled down the hill.   By the time I was at the junkyard, it was only 12:07. I have plenty of time to grab some stuff here, and then go to the store to go get more supplies.   I said hi to the gatekeeper, Rusty, and then pedaled past those creepy chain-link fences. they were all rusty, with barbed wire at the top. That always gives me the creeps. And then there is always the junkyard dogs, Spike and Lolly, but as they look scary, they're really sweet. They just are there to scare away the intruders who try to break in. But only by their looks and teeth bearing.   There were piles and piles of junk piled on top of each other, piling all the way up to the sky. But I don't think I'll need to go that far up to find some parts.   Just then, I saw this beautiful, glittering silver cabinet that was big enough for the body of the robot. That part would be the refrigerator of the robot.   I put that in my pile of supplies that I would need.   I pedaled around some more piles of junk until I saw the best pile yet. It had a go-kart! That will be perfect for the feet!   So then I had Rusty help me pull it out from under the pile of junk. I tried to turn it on. it started making this weird noise, and it wouldn't turn on! I guess I had just gotten my hopes up. But then, as I tried turning it on for the last time, It vroomed to life! Yay! I got so happy that I jumped up and started dancing with joy with Rusty. We danced for a bit more, and then I got back to work and asked Rusty,   'Do you have any small refrigerators?'   'Why yes I do! I just got a load of them this morning.'   What luck I am in right now!   'Could you please show me where they are?' I asked politely.   'Well, sure! So, what are you making anyway?'   'A robot!' I said gleaming with pride.   'Cool!'   'Yeah!'   So he showed me around the junkyard, guiding me where I wanted to go and pick out some parts. I had so far the body of the robot, the head, the refrigeration unit, the feet, and the mechanical arms and hands. Now, all I need is the eyes, nose, and mouth. But I'll pick up some of those at the hardware store.   'Hey Isabelle, do you want me to drop this off at your house?'   'Sure, that would be great!' I said smiling. (And let me note, he is my cousin.)   'Okay.' he agreed.   'I just have to run to the hardware store and grab a few parts. So you can just load all of those things into the garage, okay?'   'Sure thing, Isabelle.'   So I thanked him and said goodbye, and pedaled to the next stop. The hardware store.   I looked down at my watch. 3:02. I better get going if I want to build this robot!   I rode my bike down Main Street, turned the corner, and there I was, at Billy's Hardware Store.   I love it there. It's my favorite place to go to, besides the zoo.   I pushed the door open, and a bell rang overhead.   'Hey Billy.'   'Hey Isabelle. What are you up to today?'   'I'm building a robot!' I gleamed with pride.   'Cool! So what can I get for you?'   'Can I get two small white training wheel cover caps, a small plastic cutter, and a small gear?'   'Sure! Coming right up!' He walked around the counter, and into the small, cluttered back room. He came out with a small brown bag.   'Thanks Billy!'   'You're welcome Isabelle!'   So I stuffed that in my backpack and rode off onto Main Street.   I looked down at my watch. 3:30. Yikes. I have to start building my robot!   I rode into the driveway, and parked my bike into the garage. I found all of my supplies on the garage floor.   It had been chilly all week, but now it was getting hot out. I pulled off my sweatshirt, and grabbed a Popsicle from the freezer. Yummy, it was grape. My favorite.   I had then finished my Popsicle, and grabbed some supplies.   I was going to do a stack and glue method. I grabbed the go-kart, and set that on the floor. I put blocks of wood beside the wheels so it would not roll away. I then put Super Super Glue on the rim of the go-kart, then lifted the cabinet on top of it. Perfect fit! I then got the big pink and zebra striped jewelry box and put glue on the bottom of it, and stuck the box on the cabinet. Then I opened up the cabinet, put glue all around on the inside, and stuck the refrigerator in it. Then I glued the arms on, and made the face by putting the caps on the box for the eyes, the gear for the nose, and I carved out a smile on it's face. It was finally done. I went inside and went to show Mom.   'That is really cool! What is it's name?'   'Hmm. Oh, I know! Finn!'   'What a wonderful name!'   I then made her turn around, and then I pressed his ON switch. She asked what I was doing, and I said, 'Just wait.' And then, the arms of the robot started moving. It was giving her a massage! Nuts, Volts, and Apples       The job of an Agribot is simple and straight forward: harvest the crop when ripe. No sooner. No later. Any robot who doesn't meet this requirement gets transported back to the Institute to be reprogrammed or disassembled. Mistakes are unheard of. Accidents never happen.   That is, until the robots came to life.       It was an ordinary at the ABC Farm, and Farmer Pick A. Lot was taking roll call of all his Agribots. 'Agribot 1a? Ah, there you are. 2b? Check. 3c? Splendid, splendid.'   So it went until he intoned, 'Now Agribots, you know what to do. You need to harvest the first half of the apple orchard. Now I don't want a single wormy apple in a bushel. ABC Farm stands for top quality fruit. Nothing but the best will do, understand?'  Always forgetting that the Agribots didn't talk, he rolled his eyes and huffed. 'Well, don't just stand there! Get a move on it!'       The Agribots rumbled off and started picking the fruit at an incredibly fast rate. They had almost finished the first half, and started to work on the second, when ominously dark storm clouds started to roll in. Thunder boomed, and the wind blew in, making the trees sway and bend under the stress. Rain lashed the trees and pounded madly against the roof of his house. Lightning crackled across the velvety black sky, and it illuminated the entire sky for a split second. Farmed Pick frantically started bellowing to his Agribots to get inside quickly, but his voice was lost in the wind. Without warning, a searing hot rope of lightning arched down and struck the robots with a terrific bang, showering them with sparks and frying the fruit held in the baskets. Farmer Pick yelled in anger and surprise and sprinted to his robots. The fragrant smell of baked apples filled the air, spoiled with a odor of burned rubber. He shouted over the wind, 'Agritbots, are you all right? Oh, what am I saying, they can't talk.' Then the Agribots started to move weakly, and a voice issued from it. 'What happened? Why am I all wet. Who are you?'  Farmer Pick gawked at it. This was impossible, but there it was. So with a whimper and a thump, Farmer Pick keeled over in a dead faint.       So for the next few days, Farmer Pick tried to keep the harvest on schedule. He took roll call, told the robots what to do, and watched them roll off. 'I must be getting old. Robots can't come to life.' But how wrong he was.   First the robots started picking the wrong apples. When he yelled at them to get the job done right, the robots complained, 'No good deed goes unpunished.'   Then when they actually picked the ripe fruit, they started to try to eat it. This resulted in much shouting and upbraiding on the farmer's part, and the Agribots just shuffled around and promised they'd never do it again.   Next they started to play hide and seek in the apple orchard, and Farmer pick had to look for two hours before he actually found them. He turned beetroot red and shrieked, 'That's the last straw! You are the worst robots I have ever had. I quit!' He threw his hat on the ground, stormed off, and drove off in his car to take a lifelong vacation from farming and robots.       Afterwards, the robots successfully ran the farm and prospered with their new job, and remained life long friends with each other. Farmer Pick A. Lot tried to explain what happened to authorities, but gave up after numerous suggestion to get some rest. But he always wondered what had happened to those three rogue robots who came to life.

Ideas-   * Testing out a new robot. Things go horribly wrong.   *Testing out a new robot, the one I said I'd invent if     *Robot being moody about doing whatever people want it to.   *Little bit of both?   Start (paragraphs 1 and 2)- It was the moment I'd been waiting for. After being stuck in the lab for months, I would finally be free! (Intro, explain that the narrator is a robot.)   Paragraph 3- Does job (photographing underwater stuff, rainforests, arctic, desert)   paragraph 4- Meets other robots.   Conclusion?   More paragraphs then the outline formed above might be nessesary.         It was the moment I'd been waiting for. Finally, I would be getting out of the lab and tested. After months of assembling, recallibration, and dozens of examinations and battery changes, I was going to actually do something. My name is Photo Falcon. I was recently programed in a little lab in a place called California. What the place called Earth that's outside the lab is like, I'm not sure. All I know is it's a lot bigger.      I knew it was time when one of the scientists, Maria Crystal, picked up the metal box I've spent a bit too much time in, opened it, and slipped the film into the slot in my side that's supposed to hold film. If not for the fact that nobody had flipped my power switch, I would've been flying all over the place from exicitment. Richard and Bob, two other scientists, grabbed their iPads, two very important electronics plus a metal box like mine and they walked into the glossy silver lab van. Tests outside the lab were always exciting to hear about, but this would be even better because I was with them!     I was about to be tested in a clearing, whatever that is, about five miles away. The ride was short, but very interesting. Many vans, most of which were much smaller then the lab van and of many different colors, drove along the roads with the van, their metal surfaces glittering in the midday sun. Through the window, I saw a large body of water. It was huge! The 'ocean' seemed to go on forever. Sunlight sparkled off the waves. A few weeks ago, I'd been put in a pool to make sure that my clear coat of waterproof plastic actually worked. At the time that had seemed huge, but now that pool looked dinky.     When the van came to a stop, I was lifted out of the trunk and removed from the box. Richard flipped my switch, so  I started my propeller and zoomed into the azure sky. The meadow I was being tested in looked tiny from above, the blanket of grass no bigger then a child's fist. I went swooped down easily, due to my torpedo shape. There was no way I could take any good pictures from this altitude and do what I was supposed to do.     Maria walked over to the second box and I felt my cameras going off. What was she thinking?! She knew any motion would set those off! I was only supposed to use my film on objects that were interesting, not the scientists that I saw every single day.     The lid was pulled off of the box and out hopped a rabbit. Its glossy, cinder colored coat reflected the sky and it leaped forward, ears flopping like a flag on a windy day. Snap! Snap! Snap! I twirled in a circle to allow all eight of my cameras to capture the image. For about half an hour, the rabbit hopped about the meadow and I caught every movement on tape.     When the trio of scientists had gotten a good enough assetment of how I worked (I certainly hope I passed the test! I didn't want to end up a non-functional robot who got set aside or worse, used for scrap metal), Bob pulled out my remote that would make me return to the ground. I descended and they turned off my switch, forcing me to remain immobile while they checked my pictures. Based on the pleased look on their faces, I guessed that they liked the pictures. The rabbit stood motionless now and up close I realized it too was a robot! On the return trip, Maria, Bob, and Richard talked up a storm. Apparently they were testing me and the rabbit and so they were extremly pleased to have gotten double sucess.      The next few months were a blur. I was sent all across the world to photograph all kinds of enviornment, including the warm and wet Great Barrier Reef, the Amazon River (also warm and wet), and a forest somewhere in Europe. Very soon I became so popular replicas of me were made. They all looked identicle to me; sleek, clear torpedo shape. Mini cameras (also clear) on the sides and wings. Airplane wings that could tuck into their sides. Propellers mounted to the back to make it possible to go through air or water.      I met other robots when traveling to other places. Hello, my name is Dr. Montgomery Fortz and I am going to tell you about my true story of the Forzbot that I created myself.     At first, the Forzbot was ment to work in schools as a secretery, but he turned out to be much, much more. It all started on the 29th of October, and I was about to give up on my new invention. But then I had an idea. You see, the problem was that the gears kept on getting stuck together, and no matter how many things I tried- Malsceno, Mandy Handy, the Unstuck. All of those are my inventions- the gears just refused to budge. Then I thought to myself, 'Maybe you should be more practical. If you were not a scientist, what would you use, Montgomery?' and it came to me. Vasteline! How could I have not thought of it before?! So I took out a bottle and slathered it all on it and- wouldn't you know!- the gears start turning and the pullies start pulling and the Fortzbot was more than just a fantacy! But the final resault was beyond astronomical, because next thing you know, he starts talking to me, just like that! I think his actual words were,'Hello sir, how do you do? I am verry sorry to disturb you, but I am new to this town and my car broke down. I need a place to stay for the night. I would hate to impose but...' The Fortzbot- my own invention!- was alive! Not only was he alive, but he thought himself a real person! Of course, I let him stay overnight, and by morning my cheekes hurt from smiling for hours.     And there was even more. The Fortzbot- who called himself Minho- knew everything from cooking to cleaning to working in the lumberyard. As thanks to letting him staying overnight, Minho did all of those things for me and was on his way.     Today, Minho works as a science teacher in Stanford, and has made many things of his own, including a non-toxic toothpaste, published a book: How to Convert to the Metric System for Kids, and read over 3,500 books, almost all on mathematics and engineering.     I know that most of you will not believe my story now, or next year, or ever, but the truth is the truth and will always remail so, whatever you might think.

I was staring at a box I had gotten in the mail.It was very tall, wide, and long. It was probably about 13 feet each way. It was incredibly heavy, and I had no means of moving it. So I went into my garage, grabbed a ladder, and went into my office, got some scissors, and opened it up.         The object inside the box looked as though it were maid out of titanium and iron. I noticed the back part was opened up. There was a window in the front, on about a 70 degree angle. The sides were at about 45 degrees, and the bottom was flat. It had what appeared to be arms. Through the window, I could see what appeared to be controls. I climbed in the back and pressed a little green button. The thing stood up abruptly. On the ceiling, there was a helmet sort of thing. It lowered to the point where I could put it on.          Once I put the helmet on, I could not only control the robot, but I could also see things I wouldn't have, had I been using my eyes. The robot jumped into the air. When it landed again, something caught my eye. It was red. It moved like a snake. It was huge. And fast. Fast and huge. Something else appeared on the screen. It was a radar. Apparently, this robot also had weapons. My right... well, the robot's right hand had a knife in it. I asked myself, 'how do you miss a giant knife in the hand of a robot?,'          Just then, a voice answered my question. It must have been the robot's voice, because last time I checked, humans don't read minds. The robot answered, <You did not see the knife because you were busy wondering why a robot was in your yard. Hello Jake, we have been watching you for a couple years now, and we have decided you are ready>  'For what?! What's going on here?! And who are you?!,'  <You are ready to help us defeat Kalaar, the snake like creature you saw moments ago. As for who am I... It was a warm summer day.  My dad explained to me he wanted the garage cleaned out.  I told him we have to much valuable stuff, and shouldn't get rid of it.  He said 'If you can find something to do with it, we won't have to throw it out'.  I thought for a while and eventually came up with the idea of making a robot.  My dad wished me luck and went inside.  I spent the rest of the day building a robot in the garage.           I took some old bikes completely apart, piece by piece.  The wheels were used as the robots feet, and the handlebars were the two hands.  Next I tore apart the old dirt bike we never used.  I constructed the motor and gears into the mechanism to make the robot move.  Soon after this hard job was done, I reconstructed my electric scooter into the arms and legs. A lawn mower was used for the head and the motor and gears went along with the dirt bike parts.  I took apart a few pairs of roller blades and those were used for looks.              The end product was amazing.  I destroyed two bikes, an electric scooter, a dirt bike, a few pairs of roller blades, and a lawn mower.  It was worth it.  At first I honestly didn't think it would do anything.  I was wrong.  My robot, Scirt Lade, does more than you can  ever imagine.  It plays sports, it cleans, it serves you, it can even cook anything you want.  It does pretty much everything.   I guess my dad wishing me luck did a lot more than I thought.

THE PLANE THAT CHANGED EVERYTHING                        The scenery could not have been better, scarlet purple rays beat down softly on the crowded streets, rich aromas of blooming Daffodils and Tulips sweetened the air, and the sweet low whistle of the morning breeze joined by the constant chirping of the morning birds set the stage for an innovation to take place.                        This, was Kentwood. A town that has been standing under the shadows of its boastly neighbor Grand Rapids for over thirty years. The only thing that keeps the town standing on its feet is the importance it carries as the housing space for the local airport. Gerald R. Ford International Airport. But the town is very inexperienced at innovating, unlike Grand Rapids, the town does not even have a product that bears the phrase 'Invented and made in Kentwood,' but that was all going to change.                        So what was the innovation that had Kentwood's name entombed in the extremely exclusive club of innovative cities? Well, the answer lies at the local airport, where Kevin Roy has worked there for two years on a solar-powered airplane, only thing is, it's not an airplane, its a robot! You don't need a pilot to fly it. All you have to do is communicate with the Air Traffic Control and give the plane verbal intructions. The plane then does the rest.                       It was Monday, a day that most citizens of the area hate. People go back to work, buisness travelers fly out, kids start a new week in school, it is all mayhem on Mondays. But today, Kevin and his new innovation, called 'Innovation one' would take flight to launch a new push for pollution control.                      So now we jourmney into the cockpit of  Innovation one, Kevin is making his final pre-flight checks before take off. He climbs into the cockpit and says 'Engine one start, Engine one generator and battery on.' The plane responds and in a matter of seconds the engine on the left wing is gently humming in the morning breeze and Kevin can see that electricity is clearly flowing from the battery to the electric motor in the engine. He then says 'Engine two start, Engine two generator and battery on.' Again the plane responds as planned as soon both engines were humming gently while Kevin awaited commands from the Air Traffic Control.                     'Nero one five five niner Mike increase speed to zero two zero knots and proceed to runway two six left.' the controller chimes over the radio, with a rather urgent tone. Kevin repeats the directions to the plane and the plane gently starts rolling forward, takes a left, and rolls down the taxiway to runway two six left. While rolling, Kevin instructs, 'Solar Panels on Engines one and two report active.' The plane responds by switching the power fromt the batteries to the solar panels mounted on the wings. By the time he reaches two six left, his anxiety of if the plane will fly puzzles his mind, and he almost misses the controller saying, 'Nero one five five niner Mike cleared to line up runway two six left.' Kevin repeats the directions as said and the plane lines up on the runway.                        Kevin's urgency to take off is on the brink when the controller says, 'Nero one five five niner Mike wind two six zero at five knots runway two six left, cleared for take off.' With some enthusiasm but urgency. Kevin repeats the directions as stated and the plane starts to roll down the runway at ever increasing speed. All this while, Kevin is leaning back in his seat, staring at the runway before him, when the speed indicator reaches one one zero knots, the speed he wants, he says, 'Rotate and climb to three thousand feet.' The plane lifts up and...

The Cookerama       Many, many years ago there lived a man named Richard Hast. Richard was a very intelligent man, who loved to invent things. When Richard was just a little boy he always told everyone he knew that one day he would become an inventor. As he got older his love for inventing got stronger. When he was only 12 years old, Richard designed a robot rocket called the Shooter 9000. Sadly Richards robot rocket failed. But, did Richard give up, No. When Richard turned 14 his parents got him a whole set of robot parts that his dad had found at the dump. Richard was so excited that that night he decided to go down to the basement(where his lab was) and started to design a robot called Mr. Gower. Mr. Gower was designed to work in hospitals all around the world. This robot looked like a small cabinet on wheels that was used to store medicines locked up in the cabinet. Mr. Gower was a great idea, but something went wrong. Richard's dog Leroy found the robot on his desk one day. Leroy pushed the robot off of his desk with his tail, and the robot fell faster then a meteor coming towards earth. When Richard found the shattered pieces of not only his robot, but his heart. He began to cry. He cried and moaned until there was no more tears left inside of him. He thought he should give up. So, he put all of his inventions in the garbage. Then one day when his dad was getting ready to get in his car, he saw all of the robot parts in the trash. He grabbed all of the parts and headed towards Richards lab. When he got down in the basement he put all of the parts on Richard desk and wrote Richard a thoughtful note. it said, ' Richard, good things don't just come. You have to work hard and all the pieces will come together.' Underneath that it said, ' You can do anything you set your mind to.' Love Dad. The next day Richard went down to his lab. He saw the parts and the note. He smiled. I will make the best invention this world has ever seen! He yelled. For days and days he worked on his next invention, when finally after one whole month Richard proudly said, 'It's done!'Richard had designed a robot with the latest technology. It was called, The Cookerama. The Cookerama had a tall steel made body with long hair as yellow as the sun. It had spatulas for hands and an apron as blue as the sea. The Cookerama was designed to cook any meal you asked it to in under ten minutes. The Cookerama used the latest technology to prepare the most delicious meals ever! Richard decided to take his amazing invention to The House of Inventions. While he was in the car he could feel his heart beating. He could not believe that his dream was about to come true.When he got to the House of Inventions, he was automatically entered in the best invention contest. The winner of the contest would get five hundred dollars and a picture of themselves and there invention in the hall of inventions! Richard was very nervous because he was worried about his competition. The judges were deciding who would be the winner. He could feel the sweat dripping down his face. Then the announcer was going up to the podium to announce the winner. Richard was shaking. 'We are so lucky to have such amazing inventors this year. All of your inventions are brilliant, but remember, we can only choose one.' Richard now was shaking because his journey into inventoring was about to begin or end. ' The winner of the competition, Worlds best inventor, is... Richard Hast! ' Oh my gosh!' Richard said. 'I don't know what to say!' Everyone screamed in the audience. But, the scream that was the loudest of all, was his dads. 'I knew you could do it Richard!' He was a world sensation! He even got to be on the news! 'Is there anything you would like to say Richard?' The reporter said. No, nothing much just one thing. Thank you Dad! I couldn't have done it without you!

Once there was a boy who was an only child. The boy was named Steven. And though he didn't have siblings, he had his only friend Rusty, Stevens dog, who he played with every day. Rusty was Stevens best and dearest friend he had ever had. But one day, Steven and Rusty were outside playing ball. Steven had over thrown the ball and Rusty did an amazing leap for it, but the ball rolled into the street. Rusty didn't see it coming, but Steven did. A speeding car came out of no where when Rusty had came out into the street to get the ball. Steven came running to save his dog, when he tripped over a tree root and couldn't get up.                  'It all happened so quickly,' Steven told his mom at the vet. 'I know son, but you have to stay strong for Rusty. Okay?' Stevens mom told him. 'Okay, Steven replied. Soon after, the vet came and talked to Steven. 'Rusty is very lucky. If he didn't glance over to where the car was, he would have been killed.' 'If he could have been killed and is luck and is safe how come I can't take him home?' Steven said angrily. 'Because he is still in bed shape and he will have to stay here a while,' the vet answered softly. 'But I-,' Steven tried to say. 'Then when can we take him home?' Stevens mom asked quickly before her son could say anything more. 'I don't know yet. He might have to stay here for a while or-,' the doctor said before looking at Steven. 'May I speak to you separately Miss Jenkins?' 'Of course,' she replied quickly. ' Rusty might have to be put down if he isn't responding well to the treatment,' 'Oh no!' Miss Jenkins said. They walked back to Steven who couldn't here the conversation. 'Thank You for giving us the low down on Rusty,' Miss Jenkins said. 'You're welcome. Please come back to check up on him anytime.' the doctor said. 'Thank You. We will,' Miss Jenkins said as her and Steven left.                  The ride home wasn't pleasent. Seven couldn't keep his emotions down. He cried the whole way home.                  A few weeks later, Steven and Ms Jenkins were at the vet saying their good-byes to Rusty. 'I'm sorry we have to put him down, but you know it wouldn't be right to let him live in pain any more,' Ms. Jenkins said. 'I know,' Steven said softly. While leaving the vet, Steven said, 'I wish we were in the future and I could get a robot so he would never die.' 'I know son,' Ms. Jenkins said.                  The next morning, Steven woke up to a big surprise. 'Here is your new robot!' Ms. Jenkins yelled. 'You actually found one!' they were both yelling now. 'Yes I no how said you were yesterday and I didn't like it, so here it is!' Ms. Jenkins said. 'Lets open it!' Steven said.                  The rest of Stevens day was a totally bust. The robot was just a toy a didn't talk or any thing.'I'm so sorry Steven,' it's okay mom. You didn't know the robot was just a piece of junk,' Steven went to bed that night and wished the robot was a real robot.                  The next morning, Steven woke up to his robot cooking breakfast with his mom. 'What in the world!' Steven screamed. 'Your wish came true Steven!' 'I know! I finally have the last thing I wanted before my childhood ends!'                  Steven went on with his life with his robot who had come to life. Sadly, Stevens robot grew to old to fix when Steven was an adult, but Steven didn't become sad like he did with his Rusty. He began his new life with a family.

Dreams Can Come True                     In the beginning I believed much in robots. I always wanted to see one in person or maybe even try to make one. I, to be exact would like to invent the most coolest robot EVER! It would be fun, but if everything comes out wrong. The creation would be ruined and nobody would appreciate my horrible work.                  Fist of all my name is Kimberly Marquez. I enjoyed everything about robots, their figure, the size, and everything else of it. I wanted to build a robot, so I asked my friends to help me out. It was one sunny Saturday my friends and I were coming up with what my robot was going to be like . 'My robot is going to look just like a normal person, but can turn small into a computer ' I told them. They agreed and gathered a lot of materials to start building.                  We stayed up almost all night trying to work out our invention. It was 10:30 p.m. my friends stayed for a sleep over to start right in the morning. Starting tomorrow we needed to have at least half of the robot done. We worked and worked on it, but we just couldn't understand what to do first. It was 7:00 a.m. There was a morning chill, and the sun was out. I came to think that everything was just a bad thought and just stop everything. 'You guys I think we should just, forget about the robot,' I said. They gave me a confusing look. One of them said sadly, ' Why should we forget about it, we have almost half of the robot.' I just shook me head no.                 The next day was Monday, a school day. I was walking down the hall when I noticed a black and purple paper laying on the floor. It said ' STARTING WEDNESDAY WE ARE HAVING A SCIENCE CLASS', ' THIS SCIENCE CLASS WILL BE A COMPETITIVE CHALLENGE AGAINST OTHER STUDENT FROM DIFFERENT SCHOOLS' ,' IN AFTER SCHOOL  WE WILL HAVE A PRESENTATION FOR BUILDING YOUR OWN ROBOT' ,' STUDENTS ITS AN OPPORTUNITY, SO PLEASE ANYONE IS WELCOME.' I was happy to know there is now an opportunity for me to make my robot.                 I saw my friends coming my way really excited, 'Kim did you hear ', one said, 'You can make your own robot now.' Happily I said, ' I know you want to come with me and make one, it will be fun. They nodded yes.Two days passed , its Wednesday the classroom is empty. Then my friends and the rest of the students come in. A man starts a presentation, then after 30 minutes have past he tells us we will be stating our robots this day.  Mr. Jonson the teacher gave us really different materials to use more differ than the ones we used at home. He gives us instructions on how to start. We actually did make a robot this time and it did not take that long 4 hours straight. Now we were all ready to go to the competition this Saturday.                We arrived at the museum Academy Of Science. 'This place is crowded' I said. We stopped at a ticket stand a man asked for our ticket, 'Ticket Please.' Mr. Jonson gave him our tickets. We entered in an enormous room with different robots everywhere. Another tall man walked to the microphone . He said to get our robots ready to start the competition. Our small robot competed with a lot of other robots. Although it was not at all how I wanted mine, our special robot won the competition! All of us we proud that our robot actually did come alive I thought it wouldn't work but it did. And now you see many dreams do come true but you just have to struggle though some obstacles to get to that dream. That was the most amazing experience I ever had.

Jimmy Cambell, he was alone one afternoon and decided to build a robot. Not expecting it to work, Jimmy set his robot aside so that he could look at him. Scout, he named him. One day while Jimmy was at school, scout came alive. Jimmy returned to find scout missing. He was freaking out! A missing robot! He lied down on his bed and slept. He was awoken to the sound of rustling papers. He looked and there was scout, looking through his school-work. 'Scout?!' Jimmy asked amazed. 'Yes of course Jimmy' scout responded in a robotic voice. Jimmy thought to himself, Oh My Gosh!!I've created a talking robot!         Later that night, Jimmy tested out what else scout had the ability to do. He was quite intelligent. He understood Jimmy speaking to him, he performed tasks like feeding the dog, taking out the trash, and putting the dishes away.Jimmy was excited about all the possiblities and great adventures this robot was able to have.While Jimmy was sleeping, Scout had a change of mind of what his 'master' would make him do. Scout was turning evil.        That next morning, Jimmy woke to Scout yelling, and throwing papers everywhere. 'Scout! Scout! Scout what is going on?' Scout looked angrily at Jimmy, beady red eyes, a robotic grimace. 'You are NOT my master!You do NOT control me!' Scout then proceeded to break Jimmy's door and rush downstairs. Jimmy had created a mess he needed to clean up. 'Awwww man!' Jimmy uttered under his breath. 'great'. By then scout was already down the street screaming his little robot head off.        Jimmy chases after him, in his footed pajamas, with a teddy bear in his arms. He was so frightened. 'Scout?' 'Scooouuutt???' Jimmy continuously called out. 'Where is that dang robot?' Just then scout leaped up out of the bushes and tackled Jimmy, 'Scout? SCOUT?! woah...woah! Dude chill out!' Jimmy was able to wrestle the robot off of himself and onto the ground. 'You are not my master! Puny human!' Scout yelled out furiously. 'I created you, didn't I?' Jimmy thought, 'So, yeah, that DOES make me your master!'         Later that day, Jimmy was able to disable Scout, 'You were a good friend to start with, but this had to happen.' Jimmy was heartbroken, but he understood this was the right thing to do. Jimmy's mother, called him faintly, her voice getting louder. 'Jimmy? Jimmy wake up sweetie!' Jimmy popped out ogf bed. 'Oh my gosh! Thank goodness it was only a dream! Whew!' Jimmy's mother was confused,' What happened sweetie?' Jimmy replied to her, 'I'd be glad to tell you over some nice, warm, robot-free breakfast.'

Robo, The Amazing Robot       'It's done! My beautiful creation is finally done!' Dr. Shea, a scientist, exclaims.       'You mean Robo is done?' Dr. Shea's assistant asks.       'He sure is made perfectly!' Dr. Shea pats the robot's arm.   'Let's go out and celebrate.' He says with a huge smile.       The two of them leave the robot, unattended, and go out to eat some pizza. When they come back, they both walk to Robo's room. The two of them examine him while they sip their sodas.       'Didn't I leave Robo over on that side?' Asks Dr. Shea.       'Hmm, but you don't think Robo could've moved himself, do you?'       'Ha ha, of course not!' Dr. Shea forces out a fake, little laugh.       Mr. Shea and his trustworthy assistant work on their other creation, a robot used to do all your homework correctly. When suddenly they hear a loud noise!       Crash! Boom! Robo falls off his bed. Clink, clink, clink, clink.        'Shea, w-whats that n-noise?' Asks Shea's assistant, Marx.       'Oh, Marx! Always scared about everything. It's probably just somethings that fell!'       The two of them walk over to the noise. They see Robo walking!       'Greetings, masters.' Robo says. Clink, clink! He keeps walking towards them.       'Sh-Shea, w-what's, h-how!?' Marx whispers as he gets behind Dr. Shea.       'Robo? You can walk! You can talk! How? My goodness! This is a miracle! This is just amazing!'       'Thank you master for creating me. You are the reason I'm alive. Father, Shea.' Robo stops a couples inches away from Dr. Shea.       'Call me doctor. Come lets get some tests done.' Dr. Shea says to Robo. Then he turns around and leads Marx and Robo into a testing room. 'Marx, this is amazing!' He keeps on talking about how it's a miracle.       After the tests Shea, Marx and Robo had a press meeting where all of America was amazed. After Robo's life saving skills training was over, Robo became a hero!       Robo is still out there saving lives of the ones in danger. Thank Robo for spending his life in selfless service to our world.       10 years later Marx and Dr. Shea were, yes, famous and very rich. The homework robot didn't work, but creating Robo was great enough. The two got married to kind, caring women and settled into big mansions with beautiful families while Robo spent his life saving all of America. America's safety is in Robo's hand.

Once upon a time, in a village, known today as Germany, there was a crazy old man who wanted to be the world's best scientist, just like his father. Everyone said he couldn't do it, which made him try harder, which made him go crazy.  On the day of his 85th birthday, he bought himself a tool box and a bucket full of metal. He went back to his home, and got to work on a new invention that would help people all over the world.                       He worked for five years straight. The only time he stopped was to eat for 10 minutes and sleep for 2 hours then it was back to work.  After he completed his work he named his creation Quicky Stevey.  He combined all the abilities of his fathers inventions.  It could help miners underground like the Gemini Scout.  It could climb into volcanoes for research, like the Dante 2.  Also it can bring people medicine when they needed it.  The robot can do all these things by just the push of a button.  It was operated   by a remote control.                   The next morning he took his invention to the center of town where everyone could see him.  'Go away old man,' one man said.  'You are too old to be like your father. Just give up and retire all ready.'                 'Just listen to me. My father invented three robots that can help everyone, but wouldn't buying three robots be more expensive than buying just one.  Which why I took all my father's research and combined it into one.  Behold the Quicky Stevey.  With just one push of a button the Quicky Stevey can tend to any trouble you might be in.  Have a report due on volcanoes for school, know problem just push the volcano button on the remote and it find you your research in 1 days time.  Anything my father invented is right here in the palm of your hand and you don't even need the robot, just buy the remote.  Here's the best part, sell my father's robots back to me and your remote will be 100% free.'              'You are just wasting our time' said the man again. 'Do you honestly think we will buy your invention when w already paid for it.  And how do we know you will give us our money back when your father through it into a volcano for safe keeping.  Hey everyone, let's beat this thing to peices.'  That is when everyone tore the robot to the ground with their bare hands.             He tried and tried again but he ended up with the same resultes for the next 12 years of his life.  At his funreal a little girl walked up his tombstone, placed a flower on the ground, and said with a soft voice,  'I liked your invention.'

Helping Hands (Robots)     Once upon a time there was a fifteen year old boy that always wanted a robot. There was also a little note left behind it said,'Son your mom and I have to go to a funeral, but we bought you a robot to keep you company and help you do some stuff around the house.' The boy went to sleep.         When the boy woke up he stated to build his robot. When he finished he was really thirsty so he went to go drink some water. When he came back he saw the robot cleaning his room. He was astonished again. 'What are you doing?' asked the boy. In the robot's response it said,'Well as you can see I am a robot that loves to help clean and do stuff around the house!!!' The robot helped the boy paint the house, clean the inside of his house, and the robot helped him out washing the car(s). The robot was really smart and decided to teach the boy about math and some other things you need to learn in order to graduate from high school and get a good scolership.         After a couple of hours the boy was begining to think he was as smart as Albert Einstien. The robot was happy that he could help him out. After all of that was over the robot and the boy went outside. The robot showed him his really cool tricks that he knew how to do. When the robot was finishing up his cool tricks the boy suggested that they should play catch, soccer, tennis, volleyball, or even football. They both got really tired and decided to go and take a nap. It was twelve o'clock midnight (12:00a.m.) the robot took the kid/boy upstairs into his room and fell asleep again.         It was morning and the boy woke up and heard a car door slaming in his parkway/driveway. After that he heard the sound of a key entering a keyhole in the door down stairs. When he went to go look it was his parents'. He rushed down the stairs to give them a big hug because he really missed them a lot. His parents brought him a piece of chocolate cake. They lived hapily ever after.                                                 THE END

Wow. My friends and my eyes were glued onto what looked like a big gold tin can. But we were worng. As my friends and I took deciphering steps twoards the gold object our eyes were saucers. My best friend Syd was just slipping the lead in our slow motion walking twoards the gold object. She has long brown flowing hair with eyes that are as green as a fresh meadow. Bella was behind her with an uncertain look on her face, with her lucious blond hair and her eyes that look like the fresh sea. While Brandon with his black as night scruffy hair to his intriguing eyes, I was in the back. I have ginger flowing hair with eyes the color of a four leaf clover.                As we got close enough to touch the gold paint that was on the immense object Brandon and I went around the back to inspect this odd looking shape. All of a sudden my lazer sharp vision saw a door in the back of the object. We were all looking for some parts for our robot because my dad was holding the robot wars in 2 days! As Brandon and I near the back door Brandon uses his strongest arm to try and pry open the door. As my squeaky voice slices through the air calling for Syd and Bella to come around back they reply with lower voices saying 'ok'. Finally Brandon prys open the rusty door of the object and we all take tiny steps into the dark room. It seems like forever walking into a dark room because none of us can make out what is in this room. It felt like 4 hours until we could find a switch in this historical room. But when the lights came on it felt like I had just woken up from drifting into sleep. As our not so ready eyes ajust to the light we finally agree that the object we were in came to life at one point. The reason we new that was because we found an oil deposit that was at its last drip of oil. If we wanted to enter the robot wars my dad was holding we would need a robot and I was starting to think that we just found our solution. 'Look!' Bella said a control switch! We removed the cob webs from the buttons and found out that this object really could move! All of us in unison run out of the room and spead up so we could see the front of the object.                Low and behold we could see eyes! Brandon, Bella, Syd, and I went up to the object and tried to feel out if they were apart of the object... and they were! All we needed to do was get about 50 gallons of oil and this thing would be ready to start up! My feelings about this object were clear now. This robot had been here for about over 45 years and no one had ever come to fix it! We needed to find that oil and find it quick. We don't want anyone else to come and find our robot.                We were 2 minutes from home and I was thankful. Today has been a long day and I just wanted to get home. Finally at the foot of our doorstep, (My friends lived with me because my dad was a foster dad) so we all went inside. My dad was a negotionable dad he was always there for all of us but sometimes he could get a bit anry. He sent us all to bed and in about 1 minute I was fast asleep.            When I woke up I felt eyes staring at me. I finally got my hazy vision clearer and thats right, Brandon, Bella and Syd were starring at me. 'What are you guys doing?!' 'I exclaimed. Don't you guys know I need my space from you guys sometimes and I dont need you guys looking at me the whole morning.' 'Fine'. Said Brandon we were just waiting for you to wake up so we could go get that oil today. (We didn't go to school since we didn't have any schools around us to go to.) As I hop out of bed I rub my eyes and get dressed we had a big day today. We were building our robot todady! I got on my not so clean cloths because we would be working on the robot and head down stairs. I didn't even need to have breakfast because I was in the motion and ready to go. Brandon, Bella, Syd, and I go out the front door without even saying good bye to dad and head to the department store. With our allouences we were sure to have enough money for 50 gallons of oil. We were out and out of the department store with the oil head down to the robot and start working on it. With our oil we filled up the HUGE oil tank and the pannel of buttons lit up. It was up and working. Almost done and we would have this working like a charm. We would keep the gold paint on since we all liked it. And finally the robot was up and running. It turned on and stood up to its full potential. We would name it Sibor. Brandon, Bella, Syd and I did an amazing job on Sibor and we were really wishing that dad would love it. He will love it. Sibor will be a feirce contendor at the robot wars. I was so proud of our work on this great robot. And he will be remembered forever.

Helpful Robots                  Robots are important to everyone. They can accomplish goals that humans can not do. Some things that they can do include working in farms, helping miners stuck underground, and exploring volcanoes.               Robots that help in farms are also known as agribots. All over the country, they help farmers pick fruits and vegetables in the farm. The size and shape of the agribot depends on the type of crop. In some places, robots can also determine if the fruit is ripe or not. If a plant is dry. these robots can water them. Agribots are very useful in farms.               Gemini-Scouts, robots who work underground, are very short. This size helps them go through mines to rescue the miners stuck underground. A Gemini-Scout can go on stairs, make sharp turns, roll through water, and even carry supplies. Gemini-Scouts can also can tell if the surrounding gases are poisonous or safe. This helps the miners a lot. These kinds of robots can also sense where robots are by using their thermal camera.               Robots that explore volcanoes, also know as Dante 2, can go into active volcanoes. These robots can withstand high temperatures. While these robots collect information, the scientists can study a volcano while they remain safe in their laboratories.               I think that robots are an important part of our lives. I also think that they can help collect information and save people. Robots may even become part of our everyday lives in the future.

The first time the 'thing' spoke to me I was stunned. Speechless. You couldn't blame me though. For one, the 'thing' was at least three heads taller than me! And the only word I can think of to describe its voice is strange-it didn't even sound real. At first, I was terrified. I thought the thing was going to hurt me to be honest, but when the 'thing' spoke to me in its scratchy-robotic voice and told me that it was a robot that used to be a search-and-rescue robot that worked in mines to help find and save injured miners, I had a change of heart. The robot then started to tell me the story of one of his last missions when he was sent into a fallen mineshaft to try to help save a trapped miner who was on the verge of death.       'I was being oiled down when I first overheard mission control telling my controller, Luke, that my mission was official. I was going to attempt to find a trapped miner named Benjerman Stewart.       'Alright then', Luke grunted as he picked me up, 'lets get you loaded into the copter.'       Because we were on stand-by for the mission, it didn't take us long to get to the copters landing site at the mine. They then unloaded me and made sure that my controls were adjusted and then they sent me in.       They first thing I saw inside the mine was rock. Lots of rock. My data sensors told me that the rock was a type of granite, but I disregarded it and started on my search for Benjerman Stewart.       I wedged my way through countless nooks and crannies, looked through my thermal camera for hours, and then I finally found him. Benjerman was not in good shape at all. He was badly hurt from the mine collapse and was either unconscious or dead, I couldn't tell. But either way I dragged him back to the entrance to the mine where there was a medical crew waiting. I could see the medical team working feverishly on Benjerman. And before I knew it, Luke was loading me back into the copter. The last thing I heard before the copter flew away was 'we have a pulse' from the medical crew that was working on Benjerman Stewart.'

Today is the day! I think to myself. I walk into the school proudly and go into my first class. The computer turns. 'Hello class,' our online teacher says. 'Today is the day that you will be turning in your 10,000 word essay on your robot pet.' I glance around the room, everyone seemed excited to turn their paper in. 'Kassie,' she says loudly. 'May I have your paper?' I look over at my friends and insert my paper into the scanner. As I sit the teacher says 'Kassie will you please go down to the boiler room and get me the screw driver?' I turn surprised and say yes.                                                                       The boiler room is very old and dusty. I slowly walk around finding the tool box easily. I explore the room trying to figure out why I was sent down here. I hear a bang coming from the far corner I haven't checked. I walk over to the corner. 'Hello?' I say. No one answers. Another bang. 'Hello!' I say again. Suddenly a robot comes swiftly around the corner and gets the tool bow and brings it over. It's  whispering something while it searches the box.I walk over to it and ask if i can have a screw driver. It happily gives it to me and follows me up the stairs and into the classroom.   When I walk in the class is discussing an issue of some sort.'What's happening?' I ask. 'Nothing of interest.' the teacher says to me. The robot rolls in. 'Where in the world did you get that, Kassie?' I explain about my experience and how I found the robot. He became our class pet and since I found him I got to take him home for a day. The days wore on and we named our robot pet Andre. Everyone got to take him home for a day by the end of the year. The next year our old teacher video chatted with us daily and showed us how Andre was doing.

Lia stared longingly at the door enclosing the large robot that had entranced her for years. She always hoped that she would someday be able to see it.   When Lia was seven, her father had taken her to his job at the Factory. His job had always seemed boring at that point; all he ever did was work with machines. And when you lived in the year 2143, where you saw machines every day, your dad had the most boring job in the history of jobs.   But then Lia saw the small neon green door that stood out in the sea of black paint and white lab coats and silver-gray machines.   Neon green was her favorite color.   'Daddy, what's that?' Lia had asked in an adorably inquisitive tone.   Her father had smiled.'That, Lia, is the prototype of-'   'What's a prototype?'   'I'll explain later. It is the prototype of a cyborg that looks and acts like a human.'   'Can I see?'   'Maybe when you're older.'   Lia had sighed. 'Okay, Daddy.'   Now Lia was sixteen, and visiting the Factory with her IPod 300 blaring music into the earphones. She strolled down the hall to the neon green door.   There was no handle on the door, but there was a keypad.   Lia bit her lip. She didn't remember this...   She stuffed her IPod in her bag and typed in PROTOTYPE.   The door didn't open.   She tried CYBORG.   No.   ROBOT.   No.   Then she remembered Ms. Spark teaching her about robots 100 years ago.   'Class,' Ms. Spark had chirped, 'today we will be learning about agribots. In 2043, agribots were used to pick fruit on farms. They had sensors so that they could know what the plant needs.'   Yes! That could be the password!   Lia grinned and typed in AGRIBOT.   Ding!   The door opened, and Lia raced inside.   Inside a small cylindrical sleeping pod lined with pillows, a boy lay inside. Lia's only clue that he was a robot was the small wire protruding from his ear.   Lia pressed the button that opened the pod, and the robot opened his eyes.

There was once a boy that could never find anything interesting to do. Whenever he started to do something he got bored of it. He even got bored when he played with his little toy robot, which could make noises when you pressed a button on his back.But that was all about to change.                         One day the boy was in his room when suddenly, without pressing the button, the robot said,'Why are you so sad.' The boy ran and hid under his blankets. He was scared out of his mind. The robot said, 'Why are you scared. I'm not going to hurt you.' So, the boy slowly climbed out of bed, keeping his eyes on the robot the entire time. 'I know you get bored a lot,' said the robot,'and I'm here to help. I'm going to give you the best day ever!'. The boy got really excited and couldn't wait for the day to get started.                     At first they just got to know each other. The boy introduced himself and said his name was Kyle. The robot's name was Play-Bot 9000. Play-Bot 9000 said he also had other friends like HRP-4c, who can sing and dance, and Gemini-Scout, who helps trapped miners.'Cool.' said Kyle, 'So when can we play?' 'Right now if you want. Let's go.'                     The first thing they did was play outside. Kyle had never realized playing outside could be this much fun, especially since he had a real friend now. His friends at school could never come to his house because of their parents being busy.So, he had no one to play with until today. They played football, soccer, and Play-Bot 9000 even taught him how to play kickball because they did not have that at his school. They played outside for two hours and then they went inside.                     Next, Kyle showed Play-Bot 9000 how to play video games. He got the hang of it quickly and because Kyle had competition, he did not zoom threw the game. He had to go up against a real player, not just computer controlled players. So now, Kyle had a reason to play, not just because he was bored, but because he had a friend to play with him.                     Finally, after they ate, they played with other toys. They set up a large battlefield of toys that would fight for the castle in the middle of the room. Play-Bot 9000 called it King of the Hill.They had many battles between the good and bad teams, each one a little different from the last. Eventually, the good team captured the castle and all was good in the land. Kyle discovered that playing with friends was better than playing alone.So they kept playing until Play-Bot 9000 said he had to go. Kyle wanted him to stay, but he couldn't and said he would come back and play another day, but right now he had to go. So, he changed back into a toy and the boy set him on his dresser, promising that he would play with it everyday, waiting until Play-Bot 9000 came back to play with him again.

(2): Combat Bot; This particular model can stand a Rocket Launcher Blasting onto it. With an Iron layer, It could punch through a wall! It is also designed to carry all types of weaponry.       (3):Human Bot; The HUMAN Bot is the most complex bot. Since it is designed to copy all of human abilities, it proved quite a challenge. The Tester Robot                'Johnny make sure that testing robot is still there and in its safe.' I said,'We need it for our next experiment.' 'On it.' He said, as if I asked him to meet the president. Once he left the room, I heard a scream. It was Johnny's.            I jumped when i heard the scream and ran towards Johnny. 'He-he's gone,' he said. 'Well where is he Johnny?' Boom! We both turned around and ran back to the lab. Once we got there, we saw him, the tester, just walking around. 'Hello Mia and Johnny,' he said,'How are you?''Tester?' I asked.'Come sit so we can check you out,' I said. He walked over and climbed up the table and sat on it, without any problems. Johnny and i checked him all over for about thirty minutes now. 'It seems that he's been asleep for about two years now, by the looks of his battery,' Johnny informed me.            Over the past days, Johnny and I taught Tester how to help scientists in several different ways. He learned how to build machines, mix chemicals, and invent new items. 'Mia, I've heard you and Johnny made a machine,' my boss said. 'It's a Robot and his name is Tester,'' I corrected him. 'Well what ever it is, I got a deal on him, and I'm taking him away.' ''Sir, he's not ready to be taken away from us; he just woke up from whatever he was in that safe for.' 'Mia i need him!' 'Sir, please dont take him; he could be very useful here.' 'I'm sorry Mia, i would keep him if i could, but i made a deal with a friend and he wants it.' Johnny Steve's taking  him away and selling him. ''We cant let him do that,' said Johnny with a look on his face that told me that it wasn't good.            This is the first time I've ever thought about taking an experiment, and the last; when we went to get Tester, he was gone. 'He's gone!' i screamed. Johnny and I frantically searched all over for him. Steve was standing in the doorway. 'Do you have him?' I asked Steve. 'Yes i do, and he's going with me.' He yanked Tester's arm and i knew he shouldn't have. Right then, Tester's arm was broken off. I knew he shouldnt take him because he was a tester not the real thing; then i knew we just lost the biggest experiment we've ever had to have a asuccess.                                                 THE END

One day I was sitting on my bed using the newest Dog robot. On the box it said that it played the best songs and made faces. But it really didnt do anything at all. I was watching it, waiting for it to do something. After another ten minutes I decided to go outside and play basketball.            'Emma! Time for dinner.' My mom yelled from the kitchen window. I groaned and told her I'll be in soon. When I came in the door my mom was sitting at the table waiting for me. I washed my hands and sat down to join her. We ate our dinner in silence. My mom broke the silence by asking, 'How is your new robot?' She gave it to me for my birthday so I didnt want to let her down by saying that it doesnt work. 'It's great! I am so glad that I got it!' But my mom knows me too well and frowns. I look down at my mashed potatos that dont look very appetizing anymore. 'Mom I dont feel too good. Can I head up stairs?' My mom tried to conceal her concern but I saw it peeking out a bit. I took my plate to the sink and went to bed.            When I woke up the next morning I saw my dog robot sitting in my chair. Hmm, thats funny I thought I put it away last night. Oh well, I thought. But this time I put him in a box and shoved the box under my dirty laundry. 'That should do it.' I exclaimed  cheerfully. I had just remembered that I was having a sleepover with my best friend, Ellie tonight. I got dressed and ready for school. I was so happy that I didnt even scold my mom for putting a note in my lunch bag. Soon enough I was out the door yelling bye to my mom as a walked to meet Ellie at the bus stop. But for some reason I heard foot steps behind me. I whipped around and found my dog robot following me to school. I screamed and ran toward Ellie. 'Whats wrong?' She cried. To petrified to speak I pointed toward the robot which was now calling my name. His eyes had turned red and one of his paws fell off. It looked like a dog robot zombie! The bus arrived just in time and we left the robot standing there and off to school we went. I couldnt stop thinking about it.            Ellie and I were walking home from school and talking about what we should do when we got to my house. We agreed to investigate the dog robot and find out whats wrong with it. Ellie has the same robot and hers works perfectly fine. When we arrived at my house I walked in the front door and saw my mom tried to a chair. The robot was standing on the table next to her laughing. My first instinct was to untie my mom. Ellies first instinct was to tackle the robot and she did just that. In the blink of an eye the robot was in a head lock and my mom was free and ready to fight. I wanted to explain to my mom that that was why I didnt like it but she saw the look on my face and seemed to understand. We tied up the robot and smashed it with a sludge hammer. It was fun. Once the robot was smashed and crushed we went out to the bon fire pit and threw the robot into the flames. He was nothing but ashes.            After the burning, Ellie and I went inside to watch a movie. We had popcorn and had a great time. At around eleven o'clock we went outside to see the burnt robot again. We buried the ashes and pretended to have a funeral for it. We laughed and laughed and vowed to never get a toy robot again. You can never be sure of which robots will come to life.

Hospital Visit              My best friend, Olivia Anderson was really important to me, and knowing that she was really sick at the hospital made me depressed. I remember all the good times we had. Every second I thought about her made me even sadder. All of this was just a shock. This just couldn't be happening. Tears started running down my face... it came out faster and faster. I had to let it out. It was very rare to see me cry but right now I was very mad at myself.  Why didn't I see that she felt awful? Why didn't she tell me? Did she want to keep it a secret? Questions were being asked in my head, but I had no answer. Thinking of this made me have a brilliant idea, Why don't I go visit her???             'Bye mom,' I yelled from my front door.             'Do you have everything sweetie?' My mom asked.             'Yes mom I do. We've been over this like a billion times,' I replied.          I was walking to the hospital because it was only a couple blocks away. Since I'm so tall I can get away with looking like I'm twenty even though I was fifteen. It felt so good to breathe the fresh air of spring. I could hear the birds sing, flowers were blooming, and summer was on it's way!           'Hi do you happen to know what room Olivia Anderson is in?' I asked the front desk lady.            'No, let me look it up.... Hmm...Here it is, she is in room 69,' the lady said.            'Thank you sooo much,' I said.         A lady in the room let me in. Olivia was so surprised I came, she jumped out of her bed to give me a hug. I was so happy that she was happy! Olivia loved the flowers that I gave her. She said it reminded her of her grandma. By the time I caught her up with all the drama at school the lady had left.         Suddenly a robot came and said, 'Olivia, you need to take you medicine,' the robot said while holding the medicine in his hand. I was so shocked and confused. Did the robot just talk? How did he know her name? Olivia was just sitting there like nothing weird was happening.        Once the robot left I asked Olivia, 'Was that just a robot?'        'Yes,' she replied.        'That's so cool,' I said.        'Do you want me to call him,' Olivia asked.        'Yes,' I answered excitedly.        The robot came right as we were done calling him. We asked him so many questions that he told us he might die. The robot played games with us and told us his secrets. Did you know the robot has families in Australia? We did crafts like painting small pots with water colors from Olivia's sister Mia. The robot was so awesome! He could change colors and randomly play music.        Then some thing awful happened! The lady came back saying I had to go! I was so upset. I didn't want to leave Olivia alone at the hospital. I cried saying:'I don't want to go, I don't want to go, I don't want to go, I don't want to go.'        I woke up in the morning.       'Phew I'm glad that was just a dream,' I said to no one in particular.       I smelled bacon and pancakes and jumped out of my bed.

One time when I was building a toy robot, it came to life! I was blown away because it was only meant to talk and be a toy, but it just started moving around and doing jobs for me. I couldn't even believe myself because, I never meant for that to happen, but it just did!            It was one week ago when it happened. I went to the Home Depot and bought some supplies for it. Just metal, batteries, wood, and some wires. I came back home and started to build it. After I was done building it, I turned it on. And that's when it all happened. It came to life.            I didn't want to show or talk about it to anyone, but a couple nights later it made a loud noise when I was training it in my bedroom. Both my parents rushed in asking what it was, and then it came out from under my bed. They both freaked out and asked where I got it from, so I told them everything that happened. They were both so proud of me. I thought when they found out I'd be in trouble and they'd force me to throw it away.            The next day at school was crazy. Everybody was psyched out of their minds. This was because my robot, Henry, followed me to school. It was the middle of science class when it busted down the door. You could seriously hear the screaming from a mile away. All you could here was 'AAAHHHHH' or 'NO IT'S THE END!' That last one was my best friend by the way, but getting off topic. It was crazy! The principal rushed in and almost passed out. I was so mad at Henry I was almost going to take it apart when I got home. He or should I say 'it' stayed in my locker the rest of the day.            When I got home it made me a glass of lemonade, like that was going to make everything better. This was possibly the worst day of my life so far. But the next day I locked him in my room and the only thought that processed through my mind was 'If he knocks down my bedroom door today, who knows what trouble I'll get into?' Nobody would look at me in school, but apparently I won an award for best robot. I didn't even see a contest sign-up sheet.            The next day was the best and worst day of my life. I found out a science laboratory wanted to test out my robot! It could only do chores though. It could only lift 50 pounds, and didn't have anything for easy storage, so they declined it. I heard something called the Gemini-Scout made it or whatever. Couldn't have been that better than mine.            That same day though I discovered it could dance and play sports like basketball, soccer, and kickball. He has powerful legs so the kicking part could have something to do with that. The saddest part though, one day I was playing basketball with it and his batteries went out. I immediately ran to the closest store I know has batteries and bought some. I came back home and saw that he was missing. That was the last time I ever saw Henry.

I went back outside slowly and carefully because i had no idea what he was capable of.                                                                    I slowly walked up to him and he turned around and said 'hello I am Roberto your new helper'. I screamed and ran back inside. I then told my mom but I told her not to let anybody take him away. I told her I wanted to see what he was like. I slowly went back outside and walked slowly close to it again and said 'hi' in a really stuttering way. I asked him what he was and he said a robot from Mars to help me with my chores and homework. I told him to follow me into my house and he did and sure was he fast! I asked him what he liked to eat and he said 'robots don't eat'. We then went upstairs and he helped me do my homework. I was so happy that i had a new friend to help me around the house. But then he told me a week later he had to leave back to his home planet on Mars. He promised me he would be back.          A year later he returned and help me do my chores again but only for a week just like last time. I wish he could stay longer but oddly he has school on Mars just like we do on Earth! Isn't that just weird. He said that they learn bout the history on Mars and their presidents. I asked him who the president on Mars was and he said his father was. that would be so cool to have your dad be the president. We shared stories about school. He said he loved school! I told him I don't so much. But he reminded me that without it you wouldn't know how to count and use proper grammar.         It came to the day when i had to say goodbye once again but he told me he would always be here this very week every year to help me with anything. I told him thank you for everything he has done for me and he waved goodbye to me with his 3 fingered hand and got on his spaceship with the rest of his family.
