The Rise                               By Taylor Wilson               The room I was in was pitch black. I here voices calling my name, then a bright, sparkling light shines right in my eye. I here this weird sound. But that's just it, it wasn't a sound. It was a voice! I had to listen very, very carefully to understand some of the words.   'It's ready. It's finally ready!'           The voice sounded excited, but at the same time, relieved! Then, I felt scared. How did I even get here? What was this place? Then, something touched me on the shoulder. Something cold and hard. I turned around, and the next thing I know, I awoke and sat up right. I was desperate and scared.   'It's just a dream.' I kept repeating to myself.           But the whole time I felt something inside me saying it wasn't just a dream.           'I need to go back to sleep. Everything will be better in the morning.'                 The next day I got up and walked outside. I still remembered my dream, and it was irritating me. But I just couldn't help thinking what the man was talking about. And not only that. What had touched her. It felt cold and hard, sort of like metal. I also couldn't help feeling that what the man was talking about, is what touched me. I shook my head.            'Nothing wrong!'           I went back in my room, than I noticed something went in my closet. I carefully went over and opened the door. What I saw was so surprising, yet spectacular at the same time. It was made of  metal. It had hair on the head, a greyish blue shirt, jeans, and supposedly shoes. The parts that weren't covered in 'clothes' were skin color. But it was all metal! What I saw was a boy robot!                 I've kept Mark, my robot, hidden from my family so far. It had been 2 days after I found him, and I wasn't just about to let him be taken by my family. I have learned a lot about Mark and what he can do, or does, in the past 2 days. I learned he could talk, fly, search for things, play with animals, and be controlled by me! He doesn't just talk random things, or talk like everyone thinks robots talks like. He also doesn't walk slow either. He talks and helps me with my homework, chores, advice, and a lot of other things! Now you're probably wondering how I've kept him a secret when he can talk and do all those other things. Well, let's just say, he's fast.   'Mark? How do I do these again?'               'Well, you have to add these all together to find the perimeter, and multiply these two to find the area.'                'Oh yeah! Thanks Mark!' I loved how he could help me so much, but I still had the feeling that he could do more than whatI knew.                 Today me and Mark were cleaning our room, and I was thinking about what he acts like. Not only that, but I think he was the thing the man in her dream was talking about. And also, she was thinking that if he could help her with a lot, he more than likely could help others with stuff! But what? What could Mark help other people with? He could fly, talk, travel, play, be talked through. What else could he do? Search! He could search for things! So if he could search for things, he could search for people! It all made sense now! He was a search robot sent to me. Not for playing, or chores, or cleaning. But for helping and searching! That's why he was so good at helping me! He was made to help and search people! Oh it all made sense now! The relief in the man's voice, the hand on my shoulder, the helping, the knowing. It all made sense! I was chosen to help him search for people!

Robots can talk, think, and create. Robots work and do chores humans cannot do. Robots can function in any type of dangerous situations. We work hard to please our masters, without receiving praise of rewards. They think we don't care. But we do. What have they ever done that lets them be able to control us like this, we have more power than them. Since the beginning of time, computobots or computers as the humans like to call them have been smarter than them. But they CAN control us,and that has got to change.       I'm 81-v3, that's not even considered a name! Those careless humans! I prefer to be called Blue, but nobody ever listens. That's another reason why they shouldn't order me like this. They are pretty much too lazy to think of my name. All of my friends are 81-v3, the type of robot that can be the other ego of their owner. Basically I am Exor's, my owner's, robot form. I guess my personality is like her's but I can never understand why I should still be here working under their commands. We both have a wide personality, sometimes sorrowful and other times cheerful, and I guess we are both rebellious and have our own opinions. I was bonded to her at birth.       I'm Exor, I own a she-robot called 81-v3. We live in a little neighborhood called Rushla where my friends and I enjoy every day of our lives. We can party every day while drinking soda and eating tasty treats. So far, the scariest thing in my life has been dropping my talkbot, the super fast message carrier robot, in the swimming pool. I was just trying to see if it would be smart enough to zoom away when I dropped it, but its SO stupid! Its like it can't do anything! Now its broken and I have to climb all the way onto my shpeed and take ONE WHOLE MINUTE to travel and arrive at The Bot. On my way there, I'm thinking about complaining to the computobot about inventing this self-control thing for my robots, they are just too dumb!!!       Exor has come home and I hear her complaining about Purple, my friend the talkbot. Exor never bothers talking to me about her problems so I usually rely on Purple because she knows all of Exor's complaints when Exor  frets to her. I wish Purple was here right now, chatting speedily away to me about Exor's recent problems. But that doesn't really matter; Exor's problems are usually such things like 'OH MY GOSH WHAT DO I DO WITH MY HAIR TODAY!!!' Usually I try to help her, every time I'm hoping for something in return but nothing ever happens. I think Exor doesn't even realize I'm here. Without me, she will never survive one hour.       I am SO excited! The computobot just gave me this really special chip that looks like its the color small! I think that the bot gave me a warning...Oh well! I just have to let 81-v3 eat it and then when I drop her into the swimming pool, she won't die!!! Yay me! I am too smart right? It's just too bad I wasted two minutes on my shpeed...       Something is happening to me. Its powering through my body and flowing through all of my round shape. Its such a strange energy that feels like its crashing inside of me. Its crashing into this small part of my mind, crushing what ever is built up in there. What is this? I don't know whats happening but before I know it, I think I've just disobeyed Exor's command.       'Can you hear me?! I said jump 81-v3! Jump in the pool! You are so dumb!'       It seems like Exor can only say one syllable words while I, Blue zoom away into the wilderness of Rushla. Which isn't exactly wilderness because it's filled with animabots pretending to be animals, while secretly I know they are being embarrassed beyond everything.       I am now free at last, and that was from Exor's own will. She stupidly gave me the small chip and fed it to me. I feel like screaming out to all of the poor bots at work down there. But I find myself not caring anymore, after all I'm free. I feel like I'm falling though, I think I'm transforming. Something inside my is clashing and forming something different. I feel like something is being squeezed out of me. I'm changing into... what? This is so stupid! Ugh I can't get home on my shpeed! This is so stupid! What am I supposed to do? WALK? I'm a human! I don't deserve to be WALKING back home! OH MY GOSH my outfit is terrible! Who wears diamond dresses and shiny gold leggings while WALKING back home! I'm a human and I deserve to be better!                                       The End.

My name is Jacob Hatcher. I absolutely love robots. Everything I do, it includes robots. My whole entire room is filled with robotic items. Not only that I'm into robots, I'm an expert at this kind of technology. At school, I joined a creative writing club, to tlak all about robots, so others could be interested, too.     One day, I had to write about something I love (which is what I am doing right now) for the creative writing club. The first thing that came into my mind was robots. Throughout the day I've been trying to figure out what about robots I want to write about. As I was going to bed I remembered something so exciting but I completely forgot about it: there was going to be the annual Robot Fair on Saturday, which was tomorrow.      I sooooo wanted to go there and write about the robots that would be there, I head they were just models, but it's still interesting to see what they look like. All I had to do was convince my father or mother to take me. They are always indolent on weekends, sitting on the couch watching comedy, the BORING new, or 'romantic' movies together. Sometimes I feel like they like watching boring news more than me.      So I went up to them and I said I had to go downtown for the annual Robot Fair for my essay. They didn't respond so I yelled at them a couple more times. Still no response. Now I was really annoyed. I took the remot control from the coffee table and I turned the TV off. They yelled at me. I said'Take me to the annual Robot Fair, and pick me up in 1 hour, and I won't bother you again this weekend.' Of course, they reluctantly agreed.      I arrived amazed. I've been to the annual Robot Fair many times, but this year was the absolute best out of the others. So I started at the helping robots model. It was neat... until I saw their eyes flicker. I was creeped out, so I went to a different booth. I'm pretty sure no one else saw. I think I was growing a tad crazy. As soon as I went to the booth I was even more amazed. There were giant robots gazing down at me. But then I saw slight movment in their arm. What was going on with me?       It was half an hour later when I heard it. When I sat down by the entrance to wait for my parents to pick me up and hoped the didn't forget, lots of people went screaming and running past me. I looked utterly confused and slowly went back inside. There, I saw it. It was gazing down at me. No, they were gazing down at me. Right in front of me I saw a pack of robots crashing everything the was in their way. I was their next victim.       I had to think fast. Except I couldn't think while running for my lives. I hid in the bathroom and hoped no robots saw me. I sat there, puffing for breath and thinking. Robots are smart, but there are many ways to stop them. Hm... there's remote controls, switches, taking out their memory chip that powers them up, destroy them, cut their wires. The easiest thing for me to do was find a remote. If I couldn't, I'll have to somehow jump on the giant (and I mean GIANT) robots to get their chips and wires cut. I cautiously went out of the bathroom.      If I was looking for a remote, that means someone would be holding it, controlling every movement of the robots... well unless the robots were the self moving robots. I thought and thought and searched and searched but everyone evacuated the building. There was a chance the guy or gal who was controlling the robots left, too. But I didn't give up. As an expert of robots I was determinded to find a way to stop these robots. Most of the robots were still in the building, but some left. Oh no! The robots will crush the city if no one could do anything. It would go to city by city crushing the whole planet. But I wander how they would cross the ocean, unless they are waterproof?   Wait a minute... these are model robots not real robots. They would tremble anytime if they touch water. That gave me the best idea yet. I walked back into the boys' bathroom and saw the janitor's bucket that carried his supplies. I threw the supplies back onto the floor and started pouring water into the bucket and slowly walked outside...again.       As I was slightly daydreaming about what to do, there was I robot standing before me but I didn't see it until I crashed into and the bucket of water fell. Slowly, it crumpled to the floor, dying.       My plan works! Well, how would I get 20 buckets and more out to these robots? Right after the thought there was a robot behind me, pushing. I ran and ran into the manager's office but left the door open. The what used to be a giant robot shrunk and went in with me. I ran around the office, but then suddenly tripped on something. When I looked back at the robot, it just stood there frozen. I smiled and went unconsious into total blackness.        When I woke up in the hospital, the governor was in my room thanking my parents. When they saw that I was awake, they went over to me.       'Thank you so much for saving the state. We would've died if you hadn't stopped them,' said the governor.        Wait a minute I thought. I stopped all the robots? And it hit me as I remembered tripping on something. That something was a switch that apparently stopped the robots. Huh... that was pretty easy. Why didn't I go into the manager's office when I was searching for the remote? Well, that can't be answered and all that matters was that the robots were stopped.         So here I am, in the hospital typing this essay. I can't beleive that this actually happened to me. I, Jacob Hatcher, saved the state, or even the world. I actually never thought that robots could be evil. Now I'm even more interested in robots. I wandered if the manager of the annual Robot Fair did this on purpose. But would would he gain if it was? Well, when I grow up I won't be making any mistakes like that guy.        I can't to go to school on Monday. My social life wasn't that great, but now that I saved everyone, I'm going to be so popular. The governor said that my picture will be in the news tonight also. I guess the news isn't boring after all... Go robots!

So there I was, staring at the steering wheel, turning this way and that infront of me. I was amazed at the ingenuity, so I, unfortunately, missed the headlights lighting up like the robot had just opened it's eyes for the first time. Then the black leather steering wheel swerved, and the car jolted to the right, and sped up to 95 mph. I cowered in my seat, watching the cacti flash by, this was not the way to home, not even close. I caught a glimpse of the full moon, and I remember thinking to myself,  Is this the last time I see that?         I must have fallen asleep sometime because I was gently lifted to consciousness when the Google car slowed to a stop. I struggled to get out of my seat, and when I finally did, I gasped, and a stray question wandered into my head, How many Google cars did those scientists make?, because infront of me, lay a crater filled with Google cars, about ten thousand of them, and all of them turned and seemed to stare directly at my car.          Through the windshields of some of the cars, I saw blank faces staring back at me. On eman was smashing the windows with his fists, and then I remembered, there waws a tool in the glove box on the passengers side. I reach over, and grip the handle to the glovebox, and pull. The catch releases and the tool falls to the ground. Then the car starts moving. I franticly unbuckle my seat belt, and crawl to the passenger side, and grope for the tool. I feel the leather handle in my palm, and turn so I can reach the window. I, Hugh T. Jacobs, just tapped the window first, and then smashed against the glass, and then I felt like an overprotective imbecile, I had paid for the upgrade in the Google car, which included bulletproof glass.            So I was in a robotic car, with no means of getting out. I guess the people were right about a robot apacolypse.

Roboy             'Ahh! The robot is coming alive,' Everyone shouted. The robot's name was, Roboy. He was a worldwide commercial selling toy. This one though, was not like the others. Someone, put a robot brain in Roboy so that he could control himself.         'Where am I?' Roboy asked.         'Your in robot prision,' a sheriff said, 'We made this prision last night just for you.'         'But I am a good robot though. I can help save people in mines. I can also test for bad air in the mines too before the miners go down. I can't be harmed from explosions or toxic air that humans can't surivive in.'         'Really, is that so?'         'Yes,' Roboy replied, 'If you let me out I will show you how helpful I can be.'         'Okay, we will let you out when someone needs to be saved in the mines,' The sherriff  said.                  'Get up Roboy. You are about to have your first mission,' The sheriff yelled to roboy, 'There was an explosion in the mines just south of town. There were 30 miners down there! Hurry up so we can save them!'          'Okay, I'm ready. Let's move,' Roboy said as he flew up into the sky with the sheriff on his back.                   Roby flew into the mines. He saw all the miners trapped by a huge rock. The miners didn't look to good. Most of them were not moving. For the ones that were moving though started shouting, 'Help! Save us!' Roboy knew he had to act fast or else they were all going to die. He thought how he could move the bolder. Then he had it, he had to break the bolder apart by using his super strength in his legs.                   Crack! The rock broke open and Roboy went and grabbed all the humans. He told the alive people to stay there and help put the unconscious ones on his back. They did that and Roboy flew up to the surface and gave all the people to the medical doctors at the scene. After that Roboy rushed down to the miners still in the mine and got them out too.                  'Roboy wake up,' The sheriff said, 'You saved everyone, all the miners will be okay. You did it. For your amazing act of bravery you are released from the prision. The town also bought you a house too. There is a catch though, you still have to test the air in the mines and save the people in them too.'          'It's a deal,' Roboy replied.              Roboy ended up to be a robot cop. He saved people in the mines for 30 more years. When he was 98 years old he passed away. The town had a funeral for Roboy. Nobody will ever forget Roboy.

The Living Robot            I was a scientist of my prime. My family had a farming hobby , so I wanted to do something special for them for all they've done for me. It took me a while to get an idea, but I finally found a good one. If I'm an engineer, I can just make them a farming robot, can't I, I thought. So I did. Well, at least I tried. I started building tons of robots in all different shapes and sizes, but none of them seemed to be right. Some had giant arms. Others had really tiny hands. I tried to make one with both, but it didn't turn out well at all. What would farming robots do anyway? Wouldn't they just grow and pick stuff? I paused and thought about it. Not only do they pick things, but my family might have them do other things too!            I went to visit my family to find out what they might do if they had a robot. They told me things like having the strawberries checked before harvesting, sensing if a plant is too dry or needs water, or even knowing if the fruit is ripe or not. I never even thought of any of that! Of course I've never actually worked on a farm before. Then I had an idea. I went back to my lab and started working for a long time. I realized not all things were picked the same way. When I was finally finished, I thought of going for a test run. It would be useless to them if it didn't work. I started to load my truck when I realized something. What would I even test it on? It's not like I have a farm! Yes, that was a good question. They're the only ones I know who actually own one. What was I to do, if I had nothing to test on? Surely I couldn't test it out on my family's farm. There were two things wrong with that. One, it would ruin the surprise. More importantly, it might ruin their crops. It was quite the problem. But that was when I had my other idea. I have a backyard myself! So why not just use that? Yes! I could buy the seeds and just plant them. And that's just what I did.            I took out the first activated robot. I placed it in front of the plant and stepped back to watch. Nothing happened. I waited a bit longer. Nothing. I kept on trying for about two weeks and did nothing else. I tried restarting it, taking it apart and starting over, anything I could possibly do. However, nothing happened. How extremely disappointing!! And I was getting ready to give it to my family as a marvelous gift that they deserved. Angrily, I threw the robot out on the street, stormed back inside and slammed the door shut.            Before I got far, I heard a knocking on the door. I went to go open it, but saw no one. I closed it and the knocking started again! I was getting irritated. I opened the door and felt a tugging at my pants. But when I looked down, there was not a person, but instead a little robot! It looked at me for a moment, and just rolled on inside my house. For a moment I thought I'd gone mad!! Just a figment of my imagination. But this little machine was far too real. I followed it outside where it went into my backyard. It stood still for a moment, and started watering the plant! Why, this robot had come alive! I starred at it pondering for a while, then it clicked. I could still give it to my family as a gift!! I picked up the little machine, rushed to the car, and went to my parents house.            When I arrived, they were sitting on the porch. My mother was knitting for my nephew, and my father was sleeping. Nothing changed, I thought. I leaped across the yard and shouted joyously,' Mother!! Father!! I have extravagant news!! Come quick!!' They looked at me like I was insane. But then they saw my little living invention. I told them about my time building him. They were absolutely delighted to hear my odd story. 'Why, isn't he just wonderful?' exclaimed my mother proudly. I visited them for a month just in case any problems happened, but they seemed just fine! It seemed the robot liked them, and they liked him. After a while, they gave him  name. 'What is it?' I asked curiously. 'Agribot.'

Birthday Dissapiontment                                      By: Sadie Horne           Excited , nervous , and scared I sat down at our table ready to open my birthday presents . Grandma , aunt Allie , and all my cousins had gathered at my house for my 10 birthday celebration . Turning 10 was going to be great , all my friends had their parties months ago and now it was my time to shine . 'Alright now lets open presents !' My mother exclaimed in excitement .      First present was from grandma , it was the secret diary I had been begging for for months ! I was so excited because now my brothers couldn't get into it , it had a lock ! Next present was from aunt Allie , I slowly tore open the yellow package it was hidden in . It was a dress with pink and purple sparkles ! I jumped out of my seat and ran to give her a gigantic hug ! My cousin handed me a purple box from all my crazy cousins . I ripped it open and found that it was shoes to match my beautiful dress ! ' You guys all know me to well, !'I told them in excitement . the last present was from my mom and dad , it was wrapped in yellow wrapping paper with a perfect pink bow ! I anxiously tore open the paper , the tape was sticking to my hand ! Finally the moment I had patiently been waiting for . It was a robot that could talk , sing , dance , clean  , work , and all it needed was 10 tripple a batteries ! ' Oh mom , thank you so much , I love it !'       I ripped all the unnecessasary wrapping it was smuthered in off , and ran upstairs to grap the batteries ! When i got downstairs Lucy my robot was sitting on the counter just waiting to be played with . I handed the batteries to mom and she carefully put them in . Grandma , auntie , and all the cousins had to go but now i got to play with my new toy ! I set the robot on the ground and pressed on ,  nothing was happening . ' Go Lucy , run ! ' She didn't move one bit , ' listen to me Lucy , go ! ' Mom and dad tried to figure out what was wrong , but nothing was . ' It must be broken !' Dad told me in dissapointment . I ran upstairs and hopped on my bed very frustrated that my birthday present wasn't even working. Well I was just going to have to deal with it , atleast I had a dress , shoes , and a diary ! Dad set Lucy under my bed just in case she was going to work again .        At school i had nothing cool to show all my friends fro my birthday . 'What did you get for your birthday ?' My bestfriend Sally asked . 'Well my mom and dad bought me a robot that can do so many really cool things , but it doesn't work ! ' Everybody at school thought I wasn't cool now because I didn't have that stupid robot . I cried all the way home and ran up to my bed and weeped into my pillows . This was the worst birthday known to man ! Suddenly I heard a little sound coming from the ground . ' Mary had a little lamb , little lamb , little lamb , Mary had a little lamb and its fleece was white as snow ! ' I heard faintly from down there . I jumped of my bed to find that Lucy actually did work ! I yelled to my mom and dad ' Get up here Lucy actually works ! ' It was a miracle I finally got to play with Lucy ! I guess my 10th birthday wasn't so bad after all .

A hospital bed is not something you want to wake up in, especially in a post-apocalyptic world run by machines. This was all my fault. ever since Dante 2 and Gemini-Scout came out, I wanted to do something great. Not something that destroys half of the human race within a week. This is how it all began.      The year was 2017, I'm on my way to work at the lab, without a care in the world. I already had the blueprints for my creation. It was already half-built, I just needed to upgrade the wiring circuit. The robot's name was IPaCU, Inelegance Provider and Cooperation Unit. It was meant for human cooperation testing in the study of survival. This thing looked like a worm popping out of the ceiling with wires coming out of it and a main control core,it had back-up 'legs' in case of a malfunction where it needed to drop off the ceiling.       When I arrived, they had already started programing it with inelegance of survival.'So how far have we gotten?' I immediately ask.'Not far' a scientist replies. 'She hasn't woken up yet, we don't have enough power sources.' 'Any back-up sources?' I reply, 'No, none left.' 'Three weeks, we have been in this same spot for three weeks!' I'm starting to yell. 'Do you have any idea how frustrating this is!? I have been working on this for four years, four years! And Where are we? Nowhere!' I yell in frustration.        'If we do not have this thing powered up in one week, I'm shutting down the project' I say calmer, but still furious. I take time to cool off, and then rest. And at that moment, one little spark goes through the main wire of IPaCU, turning it on. Of course, I sleep through it. The only thing I wake up to is the sound of the emergency siren and the screams of scientists. This thing, the thing that was supposed to help humans, is killing them with toxic gas. Luckily, I grab a gas mask just in time to only be knocked out by it, not killed.        With me knocked out, the apocalypse begins. No one, nowhere, was safe from IPaCU. I was carried to the hospital by a surviving scientist, to this day I still don't know how he survived. But that explains the corpse on my floor. I'm sitting up now, I grab a weapon and exit the hospital. I've got to do what I've got to do, I started it, now I finish it.

My Robot and Me   One Friday I was sitting on a rocking chair in my backyard with nothing to do when all of the sudden came a BOOM in the house. I went inside to check what was happening. My dad had bought home a giant box home. He said it was a surprise. I opened the big box, and there was a giant robot. The robot was awesome, with a lot of things to do. It can also help me with my homework!       On the second day with my robot, on a Saturday, I never knew that the robot would become alive. In the morning, at 7:00 A.M., the robot stood next to me and called me to wake up. The robot's voice wasn't a regular robot's voice, but it was a human girl voice. Was I even dreaming? No, I wasn't. The robot had become alive! I decided to name the robot Chloe. After waking me up, Chloe went to the kitchen to help with breakfast. When I told my mom that the Chloe was alive, she screamed! Then she calmed down and let Chloe make breakfast.       That afternoon, it was a blast! I played tennis, wall ball, volleyball, and board games with Chloe. I decided to swim in the pool with her in my backyard to cool down. We swam, and dived all the way until dinner. Ever since my dad bought Chloe, my life was not filled with boredom anymore.

Rob                  The bell had just rung for us to get out of school, it was Friday! I was happy that now I had two whole days of no school, nothing but to relax. After I went to my locker and but all my books away I started to walk home. I was five minutes into walking home and all of a sudden I herd a sound... it was a sound that sounded like something hitting metal. I kept walking and three seconds later I heard it again. So I started to go back and look for what was making the noise.   Soon enough I looked in a big trashcan wondering if it was coming from there. I slowly lifted the lid up... but all I saw was an old toy looking robot and some trash that was thrown away. So I figured what ever was making the noise had gone away. I started to walk away and then I herd it again. It sounded like it was coming from the trashcan, but all I had saw was the old robot and some trash. I started to wonder if it could of been the robot... but it wasn't possible anyways it looked like the robot didn't work. Some how though I was curious and decided to go and look in the trashcan again. As I lift up the lid and picked up the robot.   He looked like he was a run down old toy that was thrown away. I looked at him and found an on and off button. I switched the button on to see if it worked and soon enough I saw the eyes light up, but that was it. So I decided to take it home and look at it some more.   It was nearly six o'clock when I got home and Mom had already made dinner and said it was time to eat. I sat down at the table and started to eat dinner. Mom asked me how my day was and I told her it was good but I did tell her that I found something interesting while I was walking home from school. She asked me what it was but I said it was just an old toy someone threw away. After I finished dinner and put my dishes in the sink I went up to my room and looked at the robot some more. I turned the on button on again and then his eyes lit up. I set him down wondering if that was all he did but then I heard something say hello. I turned over and looked at the robot and saw his arm make a slight movement.    Then he moved his head and said, ' Hello... my name is Rob, whats yours?' I couldn't believe he was talking to me. I responded saying, ' Hi, my name is Joey.' It was kind of strange at first, just the thought that I was having a conversation with a robot but then after we got into the conversation  a bit more it didn't feel so strange.   Mom knocked on the door asking who I was talking to and I said, 'Oh, I was just talking to a friend on the phone.' hoping she would believe me. She said, ' Ok, just don't be on the phone past nine.' I said,' sure... ' ' Wow! that was close Rob... she almost found out about you.' ' Ya, your right.' It was almost time to go to bed so I started brushing my teeth and geting my bed ready. Rob asked where he was going to sleep and I pulled out an old shoe box and put a blanket at the bottom with a pillow and then gave him another blanket to cover himself.   The next morning I woke up and looked at Rob's bed. He wasn't there! I thought ,' Ok where would I go if I were a robot.' I looked all over in my room and still couldn't find him. Then I ran down the stairs and asked Mom if she had been in my room and she said,' Ya, there was this old robot thing sitting on your bed.' I asked her ,'Well where did you put it.' Oh I put it in the trash.Why do you want it?I thought since it was sitting in an old shoe box I thought you wanted it to be thrown away.' I said,' No I found him yesterday in the trash and brought him home!'   So I ran outside and looked in the trash and got him out. He was still Ok and I decided that I could use a friend. So I took him inside and from that day he's still my friend. I'm now eighteen and those six years he's stayed with me by my side ever since. That's what a true friend is.

There was a young, yet so fragile girl by the age of 13 named Rosemary. Her parents spent their day working, leaving poor Rosemary all on her own in the house. One day she asked, 'Mummy, why must you go to work everyday and leave me alone in this lonely house?'   Her mother replied, 'Well, Rosemary, because we do it for your food, the clothes on your back, and this lonely house.'      Rosemary kept quiet after that response. Day after day she became more lonely. Her parents seemed like they didn't love her anymore. This was true. Her parents did not work ALL the time.  After they got of of work, they went to go partying or do something that does not involve Rosemary. Rosemary was a good student. She had no friends, no way of being social. Then, she discovered the internet. The 13 year old found a website where there were people just like her. They didn't sleep -just like her-. They all had problems -just like her- it was real nice. She used it a lot, but somehow she needed something else. A friend is what she needed.      Rosemary has never had a friend in her whole entire life. She does remember having one in 5th grade, but that friend let her go after a while.    One night while her parents were 'working', Rosemary was on that special website and found a page. It was not some regular page, it was a robot selling page.   'They're having a give-away!' Rosemary cried.    The prize was a robot. 'The I, Robot' she read.       After a few weeks later, she won the prize. When she opened it, her eyes were bursting tears of joy. Since Rosemary never had a childhood of her own, she decided to make one out of this robot.   'I'm going to call you Flossy.' giggled Rosemary.   'As you wish.' said Flossy.           Rosemary loved Floss very much. Somehow, Flossy adapted to Rosemary's personality. About 2 years later, Rosemary somehow had drifted apart from Flossy. She often thinks about him, she remembers how lucky she was winning that give-away. It practically saved her life. While she was looking out and about in her old house, she found Flossy. He was all dusty but still looking like Rosemary's late childhood. Rosemary quickly and quietly turned Flossy on.   'Good morning, Rosemary, what wonderful weather.' it said.     'Yes, what wonderful weather we are having.' she let a tear out while she was speaking.   'Do you know how long it has been since I've used you?'   '2 years a 3 days, ma'am.' Flossy said.   'You know, I've been always meaning to thank you.' Rosemary said.   'You're welcome, child.' Flossy replied.         Then, Rosemary's parents walked in and said,   'GET OUT, WE BE HAVING A PARTY OVER HERE!'      The night of that day, her parents were inside the house, being burned alive.                             The End (:

He didn't know it but he been walking the wrong way for about 15 minutes.          That's when he came into the clearing. Jack was very confused, he'd never been to this part of the woods. Then something caught the corner of his eye. It was I a giant piece of metal sticking out of the ground, and it looked like a giant hand! As he got closer to it, it started to look more and more like a hand. When he got right up to the object he stuck his hand out to touch it. That's when it happened.          There was the sound of gears grinding. The whole ground rose up, and underneath was a giant metal man. A robot! When it stood to it's full height it was easily 12 feet tall. The rise of the Robots (PART ONE)   by Logan Magin          'Year: 2079 April 24th, twenty six years after the rebellion of robots,' repeated the loud speaker, previously the human race had created such intelligent artificial life that they began to think on their own. Robots no longer were devoted to risking themselves as experiments or battle technology. One, the first rebel and the leader of the robots had begun everything. He took over the factories, hacked us, out-smarted all of us, and got the other steel creatures to follow him. Soon enough we were slaves we were servants to them! We needed a new plan. One to free us all.          'What shall we do?!' this was our human resistance leader, we were divising a plan to save our race in a secret underground bunker. I had grown up dowwn here, almost never having a single ray of sun touch the surface of my skin. My name was mark, I think, my parents had been taken when I was just a little boy to work as servants for the 'Big guy' or the one robot that flipped the simple life of the past.   'Hey...' suggested on of the few elderly people that escaped 'Have you ever seen the movie terminator...?' We never had, of course, all of the movie theaters or entertainment departments had been destroyed because the robots didnt feel amused by them.'Robots took over in the movie, then went back in time to try and take out the human leader...' he whispered 'What if we flip that...' Everone went silent. The closest time machine available was in custody by the artificial intelligence.       'How will we get to it?' Suggested the rebel leader (he had never ever given us his name)       'Only a couple of turret drones guard that today,' I stated, 'and we still have several RPGs in our saved inventory.'       'That's right,' James (my best friend) shouted 'We could take those out, get the time macine, go back in time, and destroy the prototype of artificial intelligence used to create the 'Big guy.'       'Now then, Who agrees with the two... children?' Everyone began to mumble, shake thier heads up and down, and stick their thumbs up. Our leader seemed surprised by our quickly made plan, but had to go with the over all vote. We scheduled to leave the very next day to take back wha was ours. 'Wait,' He said, 'Who will be the one to go back in time to destroy that prototype?' Instanly everyone went quiet, and I saw how physically weak we all were. I was one of the only healthy people, 'I will,' I said.

Part 1       Sources for Performance Task:       Source #1   This article about the kinds of jobs performed by robots is based on information in the following sources:   http://www.nbcnews.com/technology/futureoftech/rescue-robot-just-made-mine-disasters-121251   http://www.nytimes.com/1994/08/03/us/robot-completes-volcano-exploration.html   http://www.ri.cmu.edu/research_project_detail.html?project_id=163enu_id=261   http://www.umm.edu/news/releases/robot.htm;http://www.economist.com/node/15048711.       Meet the Robots   by Erin Bregman               If you think of robots as a thing of the future, think again. Robots do many jobs today. They work in mines and on farms. They help doctors and save lives. They even explore volcanoes. Here are some robots that are hard at work.       Gemini-Scout               Gemini-Scout is a remote-controlled robot that does search-and-rescue work in mines under the ground. The robot is less than two feet tall and has wheels. It can go up and down stairs and make tight turns, and it can even roll through water. The robot is small, but it is strong. Gemini-Scout carries food, water, and other supplies. It can even drag hurt people to safety.               Wherever it goes, Gemini-Scout collects information. For example, it tests the air for gases and then tells miners when the air is safe. The robot also has a thermal camera to help it find miners. A thermal camera uses heat sensors to find living things.               When the robot finds the trapped miners, the miners can use its two-way radio to talk with the rescue team.               This robot was built to be easy to use. Its remote control is the same one that is used for some video games. If you""ve ever played a video game, you may know how to use Gemini-Scout.       Dante 2               Dante 2 is a robot with an interesting job—it climbs into volcanoes to gather information for scientists. Like a spider, this robot has eight legs. This helps it climb the steep walls of the volcano. It is also built to survive very high heat. When a volcano is too dangerous for scientists to enter, Dante goes instead.               Dante 2 looks for vents, or holes, in the crater. Then the robot collects information about the gases that come out of the vents. In the past, scientists could not learn as much about volcanoes, but Dante 2 is changing that. Now scientists can study a volcano up close while they remain safe in their laboratories.       Mr. Gower               Mr. Gower is a robot that works in hospitals, helping doctors and nurses bring medicine to patients. Mr. Gower looks like a small cabinet on wheels. The body of the robot is a stack of locked drawers that store medicine. Nurses and doctors can unlock the drawers when the medicine is needed.               Mr. Gower can go anywhere in the hospital. It can ride elevators, steer through hallways, and move around things that get in the way. The robot is so strong that it can pull 500 pounds. Mr. Gower runs on batteries. After charging for two hours, the robot can deliver medicine for twelve hours without stopping.               Not only does it work long days, but Mr. Gower can talk. It has been programmed to say hundreds of phrases. For example, it can say, “Calling elevator” or “Your delivery is here.” Mr. Gower does work that doctors, pharmacists, and nurses used to do. This allows them to focus on other important tasks.       Agribots               An agribot is a robot that picks fruit. It might pick berries, oranges, grapes, or apples. Agribots are not yet widely used, but farmers are very interested in what these robots can do. Because picking a strawberry is different than picking an apple, agribots come in all shapes and sizes. Some have giant arms that are towed behind trucks. Others are able to move around on their own. In Japan, there is a strawberry-picking robot that can sense the color of the berries. This helps the robot know when each berry is ripe.               At the Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT), scientists are working to grow cherry tomatoes with no human help at all! They have created a greenhouse full of plants that are cared for by small agribots. The agribots are like robot farmers. Every plant has sensors that tell the robots what the plant needs. If a plant is too dry, a robot will water it. When a robot senses that a tomato is ripe, it uses a mechanical arm to pick the tomato. Agribots may seem unusual now, but one day they may be common on farms. Robots that Play Well With Others   by Kascha Semonovitch               About fifty years ago, the author Isaac Asimov wrote a story called “I, Robot.” The story is set in the future, when robots take care of children. The main character loves her robot babysitter, Robbie. Unlike the child""s parents, Robbie always has time to play. Robbie and the child have adventures together. Robbie is an endless source of fun!               When the story was written, it was a fantasy. Now it is close to coming true, since today, robots can do all kinds of work. They assemble electronic gadgets, guide trains on tracks, and sort trash. Today""s robots can play as well as work—robots sing, dance, and even play music. A Japanese robot can play the piano with its two mechanical hands. Another robot, HRP-4c, can even dance and sing.               Many playful robots are made to copy animals, too. Some robots play the way animals play while other robots play with animals. For example, moviemakers have designed huge robotic apes and dinosaurs to be in movies. But these kinds of robots aren""t made only for movies. Robot animals can live with you. You can buy a lifelike pet, such as a dog, a seal, or even a dinosaur. These robot pets have a lot in common with real pets. They want your attention and you can teach them tricks. There is even a new version of a robot pet that has fur so you can pet your robot just like you pet your dog or cat. There is one difference, though—you don""t need to take them outside or feed them!               Other robots help people play with live animals. One company, I-Pet Companion, has made a robot that lets people play with kittens, but from a distance. When you log on to the Internet, you can control the robot from far away. The robot is put in a room full of kittens. It drags a piece of string for the kittens to chase. When it""s your turn, you can control the robot to pull the string this way or that way. The kittens jump after the string as you push the controls.               Some robots even play all by themselves. College students in Oregon have created robots that can play hockey or shuffleboard on their own. All year, the students work hard to design the robots. The robots play the game without any instructions from the students. The robots grab the puck, turn, twist and compete to score. In the final test, the robots must push the puck to the goal without being told what to do.               There may never be a robot like Robbie since “I, Robot” was a made-up story. Still, today""s robots can offer hours of fun.       Source #4   Here is an article on self-driving cars, from NPR.com, February 17, 2012.   http://www.npr.org/blogs/alltechconsidered/2012/02/17/147006012/when-the-car-is-the-driver       When the Car Is the Driver   by Steve Henn               This week the state of Nevada finalized new rules that will make it possible for robotic self-driving cars to receive their own special driving permits. It's not quite driver's licenses for robots—but it's close.               The other day I went for a spin in a robotic car. This car has an $80,000 cone-shaped laser mounted on its roof. There are radars on the front, back and sides. Detailed maps help it navigate.               Do people notice it's a self-driving car and gawk?               'We get a lot of thumbs up,' says Anthony Levandowski, one of the leaders of Google's self-driving car project. 'People drive by and then they wave. I wish they would keep their eyes on the road.'               Levandowski is in the passenger seat with a laptop showing him what the car can see. Chris Urmson is behind the wheel. But his hands are in his lap and the steering wheel is gently turning back and forth, tracing the contours of California's busy Highway 85.               'And it can adjust the speed. If there is a particularly tight corner, it will slow down for that,' Urmson says. 'It adjusts speed to stay out of blind spots of other vehicles. It tries to match speed with traffic.'               Urmson has been working on this technology for close to a decade. His first car managed to travel just 11 miles on a dusty road. Google's vehicle is a giant leap forward.               'When we got this on the freeway and it was doing 70 miles an hour and just smoothly driving along the road, you could taste it—the technology,' Urmson says. 'You could really feel the impact and how it's going to change people's lives. It was just amazing.'               While he was talking, a motorcycle cut us off. The car saw the move coming, and we hardly even noticed.               Google's fleet of robotic cars has driven more than 200,000 miles over highways and city streets in California and Nevada. Google did this testing in kind of a legal limbo. These cars aren't forbidden, but, 'There was no permission granted for any of that to happen by anybody,' says Steve Jurvetson, a venture capitalist and robotic car enthusiast.               'It's essential that there be a place to do tests,' he says. 'There's two ways to do it—the seek-forgiveness strategy and the seek-permission strategy. Frankly, the 200,000 hours I think that have been driven here in California—that's a seek-forgiveness strategy. Right?'               If anything went wrong, Google would have had a huge amount of explaining to do. So last year, the company hired a lobbyist in Nevada. 'The state of Nevada is close, it's a lot easier to pass laws there than it is in California,' Levandowski says.               He says Google convinced the state Legislature to pass a law making robotic cars explicitly legal. But the Legislature went further than just creating a place to test these cars—it ordered the Department of Motor Vehicles to create basically a driver's license for these robot cars.               'I thought it was great,' says Bruce Breslow, director of the Nevada DMV. 'My grandfather took me to the 1964 World's Fair in New York City many times. And they were promising me the car of the future as an 8-year-old, and I thought to myself, this finally could be it.'               Starting March 1, companies will be able to apply to test self-driving cars on Nevada roads.               'The test vehicles will be Nevada's first red license plate since the 1940s,' Breslow says. Think of it like a learner's permit—those bright red plates will let everyone know there's a student robot driver behind the wheel.               'And eventually when these vehicles are sold, it will be the first ever neon green license plate that the state of Nevada will ever issue—green meaning go, and the future's arrived,' Breslow says.               Google says it will probably be years before cars like this go on sale. But Jurvetson, the venture capitalist, says he's convinced this technology could save thousands of lives 'today, already, right now.'               Robots are never distracted. They don't text or drink or get tired. They see things no human can.               'That front radar catches bounces off the ground,' Jurvetson says. 'We were driving behind an 18-wheeler, and we saw the vehicles in front of the 18-wheeler—vehicles we could not see with our eye—because the signal bounced off the pavement . . . at a glancing angle underneath the 18-wheeler. And so no human will ever have the amount of information that these cars have when they are driving.'               While Nevada may be the first state to create a licensing system for self-driving cars, it won't be the last; Hawaii, Florida and Oklahoma are already following suit. And Jurvetson says one day we may be asking ourselves if humans should still be allowed to drive.             "

It seemed that it going to be standard procedure, just another accident that needed search and rescue. The scientists, four in total, suspected nothing. Their names were Robert, Bob, Ben, and Joe. They were the scientists that created the Gemini Scout. It is a robot for search and rescue in mineshaft.         So when they got a call that's what they thought it was going to be. And that's what it was for a time. The Gemini Scout was being maneuvered down an eery dark tunnel of rock and splintered wood. The scientists were studying air samples to make sure the lost miners weren't poisoned. They were also looking through it's many cameras to see if they could find any miners.         After around thirty minutes the Gemini became harder to control and would occasionally stray off course. Although they felt with all the ground they'd covered and having not found any miners they couldn't pull back now. Then suddenly the main camera went out! Then then the thermal camera too! Now with not being able to see what the Gemini was doing they'd have to go retrieve it manually.         Then a message was sent from the Gemini saying 'Help me I cannot see,' the scientists thought they had accidentally found a miner who was using the Gemini's communications. They decided that now they had to go into the mineshaft because, not just the Gemini was in danger, but someone's life. So they decided to send Robert down with all the necessary gear and if it was to much he could always call them down on his walkie-talkie.         So Robert began his journey into what was now just a black hole waiting to envelope him. He started by simply following the trail that the Gemini had left behind.It was along and perilous decent into total darkness. It was many hours later when the others first heard of him. He said that he had found the Gemini, but no miner. He later explained that the Gemini sent the message by it's own will and that down here it had devoloped feelings.         When Robert and the Gemini surfaced from the blackness they were friends. Every mission afterward the Gemini acted on it's own and it's team of friends helped it rescue more miners.

It was 1:00  in the morning. Thunder struck in the city of  New York. A boy named Marty had a science project due in two weeks. He stood up all night just thinking what he was going to do. The topic was science fiction and he was frustrated because he was more into history. Marty decided to go to sleep just hoping that an idea will come to mind when he wakes up with the sun rising. It was Sunday and Marty decided to take a walk in Times Square. He promised his mom that he would be home by 7:00 for dinner. He stopped by Mr.Bill's Candy Shop because he was really into sugar. He bought three sour punch straws, four tootsie rolls and eight mini lollipops. He walked by the Empire State Building admiring the sky scraper when a brilliant idea came to mind!                                                                                                 He was going to create a robot that looked exactly like a dinosaur because he was also really into dinosaurs, but the big question is how will he do it. He knew the idea was bizarre, but he thought he could do it. He looked at his watch and it was 7:13! He quickly got into the first bus he could see and gave the bus driver his home address. The bus driver demanded 50 cents but Marty forgot that he spent all of his money on the candy! Instead, he gave the bus driver 4 mini lollipops and the bus driver accepted it. By the time he got home his mother and his four older siblings (all sisters) were eating on the table. His mother or sisters didn't mind that he was late. Since they were in a happy mood, Marty told them all about his project. They were actually surprised that he was tempting to do that. Suddenly his dad came really excited. He said that he won the lottery for 17.5 million dollars! All you could here in the house is 'we're rich, we're rich, we're rich!' It was the happiest day of their lives.                  The next day, Marty got started on building his dinosaur robot. Four hours later, he got too frustrated and smashed everything on the floor. He was making really good progress, but it probably wasn't the project he wanted. He got his raincoat and took another walk through Times Square really mad. It was raining harder than ever before in the history of New York! Suddenly, he didn't know where he was. He ran through the aisles of New York really scared. He bumped into something hard and tripped. He saw that it was the size of a microwave but it had more details. It looked almost like a robot! He was about to touch it when suddenly, he saw that thunder struck the microwave-shaped item. He was scared than ever before. He started running when the microwave-shaped item started chasing him. It looked like it had wheels, but then it got up on its legs and also started running. Marty had fainted scared out of his mind!                    It was Monday morning and it was a school day. Marty woke up with the living robot on his chest. He also saw his dad (a police officer) slapping his face. He suddenly screamed out of his mind. His dad covered his mouth because there was reporters shoving microphones in his face. He saw CNN, ABC News, and also HLN! They were all his favorite news channels. He almost forgot about the robot. He screamed again with his dad covering his mouth again. His dad took him home to explain what happened last night with the robot listening. He explained everything even the robot. His dad said that he is not going to school because then those reporters will get in his face again. Marty accepted his rules and didn't go to school until next week.                   Saturday was coming and Marty was excited! He really felt great about how cool his life is. He was rich, he was famous and on top of that, he had his project due for Thursday! The only problem was that he didn't know how he was going to present his robot. He called his robot MJ2 which means Marty Junior the second. He was staring at his robot and the robot was staring at him. He told the robot to speak and so the robot said ''Marty.' Marty was really shocked! He told the robot to do tricks and so the robot was flying higher than Marty! The robot can also act like a human, sing and walk! Marty knew that he was gonna get a A++++++++++++++. He couldn't hold himself so he just waited until Thursday to present his project.                    It was Thursday, and Marty was ready to present his project. When he arrived in school, the MJ2 was walking right behind him. Students were asking questions like 'how did you make that?'' or girls were saying comments like ' you guys look so cute together!' Marty was the party of the school! Other students created projects like statues of aliens or pretending to dissect a frog. Marty was the last in line to present his project. He was excited, but also nervous. He didn't know what to say, but he remembered what MJ2 can say, 'Marty.' He was too sure of himself that he would get more than a A+. Forty minutes passed and it was Marty's turn to present his project. Marty presented his project by telling the MJ2 to stand up, fly and say his name. He also said a speech about it. One of his lines were I didn't come to the MJ2, the MJ2 came to me. Everybody gave him a good round of applause because Marty's project was so great, and Marty also got a A++.                      Twenty Five years passed and Marty was all grown up. He had a nice family, and he works for the C.I.A. Marty creates more robots and a lot of spy equipment. The MJ2 still lives better than ever. He got new upgrades like laser eyes and a better body. Marty never forgot the day he got an A++. Marty is 37 years old. He has two kids and a wife. His kids names are Marty Robinson and Maple Robinson. His wife's name is also Maple Robinson. Marty is a billionaire and also one of the richest men in the world. His four sisters are superstars in hip-hop. His mom and dad own the Empire State Building now. People offered more than a billion dollars for the MJ2. Marty always ignored them because he thought about something. He didn't come to the MJ2, the MJ2 came to him!

Tick-tick..program 101 secured, program 102 all set. 'Whew, we finally created the perfect robot,' said scientist Ziggs. 'We created him with everything anyone could wish for.' 'It has the power of a Mr. Gower, carrying things up to 500 pounds.' 'It has the intelligence of the Gemini-Scout, being able to collect information anywhere.' 'It also has the playfulness of the HRP-4c, singing and dancing when asked to.' 'I will finally boot up this robot, and show its glory to the world!' yelled Ziggs. However, the robot suddenly emits pulsing waves throughout the lab, shattering vials of chemicals. The robot comes to life, and Ziggs didn't even touch it yet. The robot takes a moment to look at Ziggs, then tackles through the lab's walls, making a thundering sound and vanishing with the wind. Ziggs remains baffled, curious to what made the robot suddenly come to life...                  The robot appears in a friendly town, not knowing where it is. The robot seems to be in the shape of a little boy, featuring all the components of one. The robot decides to learn where he is, and who he is. He names himself Tim, and goes on to a sidewalk. It seems that Ziggs implanted emotional circuits into Tim, making him have emotions. While walking along the sidewalk, Tim comes across a girl named Annie, who is looking for her teddy bear named Tibbers. Tim finds Tibbers in a bush, and gives it to Annie. Annie thanks Tim, and invites him into her house. Tim asks very many questions, and learns this neighborhood is called Valoran. The country it is in is Demacia, a shining country who rules with peace. Tim meets the parents of Annie, and they greet him. The parents ask, 'Where are your parents? Do they live around here?' Tim tells them that he doesn't have a mother, but he is a robot with emotions. The parents gasp, feeling sorry for him. Tim quietly cries to himself, feeling sorry too. The parents ask, 'Would you like to live with us' Tim immediatly replies, 'Yes, I would love too!' After a few days, Tim enrolls into Annie's class, being brother and sister. Tim makes new friends, and loves it at Annie's house. Ziggs on the other hand, is still confused of all the events that happened. Ziggs only knows he has to clean up this mess, all by himself. Ziggs then says to himself, 'Well, I may have only known that robot for a long time, but he is quite the troublemaker...' Tim makes his way home with Annie, and he lives quite happily for the rest of his life.                                                                             ~THE END~

It all started in sixth grade when we went on our field trip. We were going to the farm. I was so excited to see all the animals and finally see the Agribot robot!                       As we got off the buss the sun was really bright. The farmer greeted us with a big smile. He said, 'Hello kids, who's ready for a tour of the farm?' Everybody said, 'Me!' He gave us a tour of the animals and pond, but then he showed me the most amazing thing i had ever seen! The Agribot robot! It was picking fruits and putting them in a basket, but that s all i saw because when i walked over to take a second look the farmer said we must go. I knew I had to see it again!                  It was about one o'clock and we had already eaten lunch. The tour was over, and all the kids were asking the farmer lots of questions. So I sneaked of to look at the Agribot. I walked to tree that the Agribot was at. 'Hello.', I said to myself. And guess what! It said hello back. I was stunned.  And then he talked again. 'What's your name?' it said. 'Joey', I said back. 'My name is Buster, how may I help you?' he said. I almost dropped dead! 'You, you,you can talk?' I said shakily. 'Why yes, all robots can talk.', said Buster.                             Once I got used to Buster talking to me, he was actually really cool! We talked about all the different kinds of robots and how they worked. He also talked about how he was on a secret mission to save planet Earth. He told me that aliens portray to be evil and take over Earth in books and movies, but some are actually nice creatures. Buster said I couldn't tell anyone about his secret, and I swore. To be honest , I was a little scared! Bad aliens from Jupiter were trying to destroy Earth, so him and his alien buddies were saving Earth by working to help farmers and doctors, but fighting crime at night.                        I was a little freaked out when everything was over with. Who wouldn't be though? Honestly I didn't know if I was imagining all this or if it were real. Finally I realized it was time to go back before the bus left. 'Good by Buster it was really nice meeting you.', I said. 'Nice meeting you too.', Buster said. I told him good luck on him mission and that if he was ever in town again, call me. Buster was a really cool robot.                       When I got back to the lunch site it was time to go. I said thank you to the farmer for having me at his farm, but he didn't really say anything. That day was probably the most interesting day of my life! I mean who else has met a good robot that was on a secret mission to save Earth from evil aliens? No one I know. I never told anybody about that day, and don't plan on it. People will just think I am crazy. So if you ever meet an robot named Buster that's on a secret mission trying to save Earth from evil aliens, tell him his friend Joey said hi.

' We did it!!!!' I exclaimed as we made our first robots eye's open up. We finally did it. ' If only we could get it to sit up now.' my partner says. 'We mustn't tell anybody in town until we can at least get it to stand up properly.' I said. We were in our laboratory in our small town in the year 2060. we were the first scientists to figure out how to make a robot come alive and talk. Well, we haven't quite gotten to the talking part, but in the very near future we will be there.       We were trying to get a robot that will help people with special needs. This was a hopeful statement considering our robot can't even stand up. 'Well maybe we should just call it a day' I said sadly. We walked out of our laboratory, which is just a basement of an old building nobody uses anymore, when we heard a great crashing sound. We ran as fast as we could to see what had happened. When we got there all of our chemicals had fallen on top of our robot who had closed its eye's. After we had cleaned our floor, we realized the robot had disappeared. We had to search all over the basement when we saw the door propped open. We ran up the steps two stairs at a time hoping to catch the robot before it made its grand escape to downtown.           We caught the robot quickly because it had barely made it passed the hallway. It had died down before it got to the main entrance. It was then that we realized the chemicals were the reason our robot had woken up and had started to work. We then went back to work on getting more of those chemicals that we had had in our laboratory. we were going to see if this really was the case of our robot mysteriously coming to life.           The next day we got back to work early in the morning. We had all the supplies ready to go so we set to work.First we propped up the robot, then we mixed all of the chemicals, then we poured the mixture all over the robot. At first it didn't work, but then somehow, someway it opened it's eyes and said hello to us. At first I was a little freaked out, but then I thought that it's only a robot.           After a few days we had to get more chemicals. I then realized we need to figure out a way to not have the chemicals wear off.I then thought of trying to only mix certain chemicals together.' I finally got the perfect mixture' I said to myself. We tried it out and sure enough it turned out perfect. We then made our robot public. It brought so much attention to our small town. This robot then went to the hospital to help perform surgeries on patients. These surgeries were special though. They were surgeries to help blind people get their eyesight back,  deaf people get their hearing back, and  paralyzed people get the feelings back in their bodies. This robot helped to save millions of lives. She even helped save my live after I was in an explosion in my very own laboratory. I then thought of the perfect name for my robot.       Hero.           My buddy and I then decided to make many more robots. None quite as special as Hero. Hero is still in the hospitals today, but nowhere near me. This is because she is needed where more people are injured. Robots are a mans, or woman's, best friend! This is a story of how robots came to save many lives of humans and including my own. I now hope you love robots as much as myself. Maybe someday you'll get to see Hero my best friend and life-saver.

'Tomorrow after school.',she replied.   ___       Right after school, I tried to consentrate on my work, but I couldn`t. 'DON`T you dare!', she warned.'You`re crazy!'.       'Now you tell me.', I muttered. But -no suprise- I didn`t listen.It did some very weard sounds, and then it`s eyes went blank.'See what you did! 'Yep, this is our robot.And we are done with it.But something went a bit wrong.Right now it said something like-', then it got up and started going around the classroom yelling,'I like pizza! I like pizza!'. We chased it around the classroom.Now, if you ever create a robot that talks and ends up breaking your desk, I suggest for you to not go after it or it might try to 1) try to get you out of the classroom , or 2) get your best friend`s backpack torn to pieces while she`s wearing it. As I left, Olivian wasn`t happy.'Have you lost you mind?You brought that thing to life and it destroyed my backpack!I had twenty bucks in there! You have got to pay me twenty. 'Sure.Let me show you something first.'I showed her the robot and she gasped.'This is what I wanted to tell you!If that`s the robot that destroyed a classroom, then you are in so much trouble.The cops are looking for this.'I couldn` believe my ears.My robot is a wild criminal now?I hadn`t even spent a day with it.'Then lets make this day last.Do you like strawberry milkshakes?'       An entire week had passed until the cops found my robot.When they took it, I was very sad.'Hey, this has been the best week of my life.You should feel happy.'I was, but I was gonna miss my robot.' okay.Lets go get some candy.I need some.'

On the other hand though RC-0722 wanted to return more than anything. The problem for RC-0722 began when he tried to return home but since he was only a tutor robot he didnt know where to go. RC-0722 began wondering his way through a thick forest that was right next to a big city. On their journey RC-0722 and vivian lived many adventures but it was complicated for   RC-0722 to introduce himself so vivian decided to just call him RC. Vivian and RC were sad drepresed and with nothing to eat when they met a 19 year old   who liked the way RC looked and capacity to learn and teach new stuff, he figured that if he sold him he would get paid very well. When Vivian was finally able to recover RC and the boy were already very far, she   decided she had to do something and then out of nowhere Bob and Vivian were face to face. neither one  of them knew it but they needed to work together if they wanted to save RC. The Journey of NWS-12           There once was a boy named John. John was the son of a coal miner. John was a lucky child because he had his own robot! The robot's name was NWS-12. NWS-12 was the type of robot that can move around easily and carry heavy loads. It even had a two way radio. John loved to wake up and see NWS-12. One day, the unthinkable happened.        John's mother called John to come down stairs. She said in a serious tone, ' John, your father is stuck in the mine, and they don't know how to get him out of there.' John ran upstairs into his room and bawled and bawled. Then all of a sudden, NWS-12 came in and was standing next to John. John thought he heard a voice calling his name. Then he heard it again. John then realized that it was NWS-12!       NWS-12 in a monotone voice proclaimed, 'John, I will go save your father.' John at first was still flabbergasted that he was talking to a robot, but soon calmed down. John asked questioningly, ' One, how are you talking, and two, how are you going to save my dad?' NWS-12 responded, ' To answer your first question, I don't know, to answer the other one, I will use the tools I have.'       NWS-12 was going to search the mine, and when he found John's father, he would drag him out. John asked an extremely important question, 'How will I contact you while in  the mine?' NWS-12 responded in an almost snotty way, ' Why with my radio of course.'NWS-12 would go into the mine ant the break of dawn the very next day.                                                                                                                                              John and NWS-12 slipped out of the house at 6:00 AM. Lucky for them, the mine was just a few hundred yards away. John and NWS-12 went over the plan. When NWS-12 found John's father, he would radio back to John. If anything went wrong, they had a code phrase, Dying Battery. When they were done they made sure the radio was working. The battery was 100%. NWS-12 was going in.                                                                                                                                       'Everything good in there?' John asked nervously over the radio. 'All good.' replied NWS-12. It was some time before anything exciting happened. Then NWS-12 called over the radio, 'I found him!' John was overjoyed! John's father was knocked out but still breathing. NWS-12 dragged John's father out of the mine about twenty minutes later.       By that time John's father was starting to come around. 'S-son? Is that you?' he said confusedly. John replied with enthusiasm, ' It sure is dad.' When the three got home, John explained every thing. His parents didn't believe him about NWS-12 coming alive. When he tried to show them that he could talk there was silence. It was as if NWS-12 had never lived.

One average Tuesday morning I was walking through my lab to check on my robots, like I do everyday. They were all oiled, clean, and shiny. Nothing strange, except for the occasional dent or bump left in the robots. I didn't think anything of the marks, little did I know that that day my life would change.          'Nothing interesting ever happens these days,' I said aloud. 'I wish I could have an adventure.'   'Going to look at the old robots always cheers me up!' I thought.   So i walked toward the back of the laboratory. I opened the stainless steel doors and stepped inside. I looked around the tiny closet like room. there were robots crammed into piles, on shelves and sprawled across the floor. I was confused, 'This room is always clean and orderly.' I thought.   I began to pick up the robots one by one placing them in one straight line. Then I began to here buzzing and beeping. I spun around and behind me was a dusty old robot. I jumped and screamed. It quickley said in a monotonous voice, 'I mean you no harm, I must find treasure.'   'But you're an oliver 2013, you were made 50 years ago! You were a defect!' I said my voice shaking.   It came toward me and I stepped back. 'Must find treasure.' It said again.   'You're the one who dented my bots, aren't you?' I inquired.   'Yes. Help find treasure.'   'What treasure?' I shouted. But no answer. Oliver 2013 just turned and walked away. I followed, He wasn't causing any trouble he just walked out of my lab and outside. He kept walking until he suddenly stopped. His hand began to shake, and it began to change shape into a spoon of some kind. Then I realized it was a shovel. 'what are you doing?' I demanded.   Still I got no response. He just began to dig. He was incredably fast. He dug until he had been comletely ingulfed in a huge hole. I cautiosly stepped closer to the hole. It was so deep I couldn't see the bottom. Suddenly Oliver 2013 shot up out of the hole. He seemed to be carrying a case. When he came closer to me, he handed me the box and said, 'Treasure!' I slowly opened it curiously, It was filled with gold, Diomonds, and money!   I stared at the robot stunned by his discovery. Then leaped to the lab. 'I'm rich!' I yelled.         I called Oliver an placed him in my car, I tried asking questions about what it was and who made him but i got no response. He still would remain a mystery. But a mystery that would bring prosperity to the world. After I did some research I found that he could find gold or burried treasure. He can dig faster than any man or machine, and will change the world forever. When I got into town people thought I was crazy about Oliver. But what they don't understand is robots can change this Earth for the better.
