Ambush and the Science Fair       'Hey mom, Hey dad! I'm home!' I shouted as I walked into my house. I threw my back breaking bag of pads and footballs on the dish washer and continued into my house. The moment I stepped in I could already smell the fresh aroma of freshly baked cookies that have been waiting for me on the kitchen table. The smell pulled me in, closer and closer but I had to pass. Tomorrow was the day of the big science fair and I needed to get my project done. I raced through the hallways and walked down the creaky stairs that entered into the basement, or what my parents called 'Jared's Lab' because of the amount of time I spent down there to finish my project. I heard my brother, Ryan, chatting away on his X-box which made it even harder to want to work on my project. First the cookies and now the urge of me wanting to play X-box! But I promised myself to not have any distractions that could cause me to not finish. There it was, standing under my desk light. It was the robot that I had been working on and my project that I would present. I called it Ambush. The name sounds unhappy, but that just described the way it looked. I have been trying to program it to do and feel what I do- when it is turned on; like a mirror image. I put in the last few screws and pieces until it was finally finished and made a bracelet that would light up if Ambush was turned on. The only problem was I could not test it or see if it works because Ambush can only stay on for a certain amount of time and I didn't want it to burn all of its energy. Who knows- it could only last for about 5 minutes, so I did not want to risk it. I left Ambush where he was and walked back up the basement stairs. It was late now- past 11:00 p.m. I headed to my room and just went straight to bed. I could not get my mind off of Ambush and the science fair. Then my eyes saw the time- it literally seemed like it 'flew.' It was hard to make out the numbers because I didn't  have my glasses on. I did see a very blurry '1' and '2:' but the other numbers I could not see. I just hoped that it wasn't too late to be able to get up and out of bed. I still kept my fingers crossed that Ambush would work for tomorrow.   'AAAAAAWW!' I yawned as I got out of bed. I could here the sounds of chirping birds and the warm sun, beaming in through my bedroom window. 'Wow!' I thought to myself 'I've actually woke up before my alarm clock.' Within a second ,y heart completely dropped. The power had gone out! There was no alarm clock!' I slipped on some shoes and walked across the hallway to wake up my mom, so she could drive me to school. I explained what had happened and she freaked too. The only reason we were so shocked is because I could have missed the science fair. I just don't know what time it starts, but I hoped it was not right now.Once I got downstairs,  I opened the refrigerator to grab some milk. As I lifted it up, I felt that it was warm from the refrigerator not having any power; so cereal wasn't available to eat. I sprinted over to the pantry to get some protein, breakfast bars and stuffed a bunch of them into my pocket to eat in the car. I grabbed my backpack, brushed my teeth, and took off for school.   Immediately, I bolted into the M.P.R, where the held the science fair.   'Mr. Staub! Your turn to present!' One of the judges announced. 'Perfect timing!' I thought to myself. I walked up to the stage to see the many people in the crowd staring right at me. It almost seemed that their eyes were beaming through me. Suddenly, I realized that the one thing I needed was Ambush. I nearly almost fainted, but instead I started to shake. 'Any day now!' One of the judges projected into the room. 'I... I d-don't have my p-project yet s-sir.' I said to the judges, freighted. Then I came up with an excuse to leave. 'M-may I go the... the r-restroom?' They nodded their heads but were not very happy. Once I was in the restroom, I pulled out my cellphone to call my mom. I NEEDED her to bring Ambush. In the middle of the conversation, I noticed something light up. It was my bracelet, meaning Ambush got turned on at my house. I figured it was the maid probably dusting off Ambush and accidentally turned it on. Then an idea hit me. 'Sorry! Gotta go mom. Bye!' If Ambush could really do what I do, I could just walk it to school, but from the bathroom. I would just have to remember all of the twists and turns that I would have to walk in order to get out of my house and into school. The first thing I had to do was remember how to get out of the basement. I started walking side to side, pondering, trying to picture exactly how to get through the garage door. Of course the ring of my cell phone had sounded. 'Hello?' I asked. It was my mom again. 'Ummm Jared- your robot is walking side to side and it shaking the house! Make it stop please.' I stopped walking to see if it would stop too. 'OK. It stopped. Thank you!' she said in relief. 'Uh mom... sorry but I need to walk it out of the house, so there is going to be some stomping until it is outside. I know you won't be able to fit it in your car so I have to walk Ambush to school.' I replied. 'Alright! I'll help you find the door. So walk forward, a little more. Stop! You are about to hit the wall. Go left, OK perfect. Now just walk forward and you will be out side. 'Is Ambush out yet?' I asked. 'Yes. Oh, I have to go take Ryan to basketball practice so you are on your own now. You should know how to get Ambush to school from our house because we live right next door from it.' I heard her yelling for Ryan to get in the car. 'Bye mom!' I said. Then I slipped the phone back in my pocket. I pictured that I was outside of my house and where to turn on the streets. 'So I take a left, right then straight.' I whispered to myself. I began to walk him by going straight and so on.   Within a minute, I could feel the floor shaking rapidly beneath me. Ambush was in the school! I had to get him immediately because he could run out of juice in any second. Before I ran out of the bathroom, I turned Ambush off from my bracelet, so he would not move. I checked the nearest hallway. there he was, with his 'mad' face, just standing in front of the clear door. I opened the door in front of him, allowing Ambush to walk inside. I turned him back on and he walked right beside me until we reached the M.P.R. I was not  nervous anymore, considering I had a gigantic robot by my side. I took a deep breath and then walked inside.   'Sorry it took so long but I had a really bad... uh stomach ache. But I have my project right here.' The judges had all started laughing because when I turned around to point at Ambush, Ambush did the same and pointed to nothing. I joined in the laughter as well, with a tiny giggle, but continued with my speech. 'I have programed him to do what I do, with the control of this bracelet. I pointed to my wrist and showed the audience. He does what ever the person who is wearing this is doing. I have worked very hard on this project, with a total of about a year. So uh, that concludes my presentation, thank you!' They all clapped in amazement and rewarded me with a first place ribbon. Once I received the winner's prize, then I knew that a year of hard work has finally paid off.       'So what did you guys think?' I asked. One of the few people woke up and replied, 'What do you mean?' 'The story I just read to you- did you listen to any of it?' I again asked, but this time more angry. 'Your only job for this whole wiring club thing is to listen to story, and you still didn't pay attention?!' They all nodded their heads 'No.' I just handed my narrative in and headed home from the school library. I hoped that I got a first place ribbon like I did in my story. Maybe this would be something that I won't be able to get off of my mind at night- just like Ambush and the science fair.

This story began at 8:48 p.m on April 12,2013 in Memphis,Tennessee.Our family,the Hutcherson family,were wandering around a toy store to buy new toys.There was Mom and Dad with Annie,my babysister,in the baby dolls section looking at toys for Annie.And then there was me,Jack,looking for awesome looking robots.About 30 minutes later,I find this dirty looking robot behind all of the cleaned looking ones.Its body is painted all black.The fact that shocked me the most was,it's the biggest robot in the toy store.Two yard tall and 1 yard wide.At first,I didn't want to buy it,but then I started feeling bad for the little guy.So,I told Mom and Dad to buy it.          We went back home.Annie was asleep,so Dad had to be careful of carrying her inside their room.After Dad put Annie to bed,they watched a movie in the living room,while I play with the old robot I bought in my room.It looks really cool.He has three buttons in where his stomach is place.I pressed the first button and the robot said,'Your the best friend ever!'I pressed the second button and its legs moved.Then I pressed the last button and its arms moved.While its arms were moving,I started to see this button in the bottom of its right armpit.I don't know if that's really where they're supposed to be but,it seemed like it was hidden in there.          My body started to get this creepy feelings I can't even explain.I started to get cold.Even though I was getting scared of what might happen,I still pressed it.It was just a toy,there's nothing to get scared of.I was wrong.The robot's eyes started glowing.I stepped away,leaving it on the floor laying down.It stood up by itself and started to walk towards me.I wanted to shout but couldn't becuase I was too afraid of what it might do to me.          It stopped walking when it was about 4 yard from me.My body started to feel a little bit less scared,but I still stayed still in the corner of the room.It finally spoke.It said,'Don't be afraid,I am your best friend.'After what the robot said,I didn't feel scared anymore.I started walking toward him.I asked him if he's alive and he responded the word 'YES'.Instead of that making me feel creeped out,it made me feel great.I have a best friend that's a robot,a robot that controls itself.I carried him to my bed and talked to him the whole night.          The next day,I woke up and didn't see him where he was last night.I looked for him and found him cleaning my clothes inside my closet.He was taller though.I told him to come out.He shrunk while he was coming out.Well,that shocked me.He played many games with me in my room.I kept it a secret from my family though.They might get scared and hit him with bats or something.I had to go in and out of my room every hour.       Every morning I wake up,I always see him doing my chores,but I'd always tell him to stop so he could play with me.My parents sometimes comes in to my room with a shocked face.They never found out about my robot best friend untill I told them the next year I bought him.I was very happy they didn't get scared and hit him with bats.I was also happy because he became my best friend.Without him,I wouldn't have a better childhood than what I expected.

DING DING DING! sounded the bell. Finally, school was over! But it was not a very happy moment for all of the members of Mr. Crawford's science class. He assigned us a LOT of homework, and it was all due by the next day. What was the homewwork, you ask? We had to build a robot. A robot! I mean really, we're only in sixth grade, its not like we're engineers! Of course, its not THAT hard. All the robot has to do is move a tennis ball a few feet across the room without us touching the ball or the robot, but still, how are we supposed to build our own robot! 'Luke, aren't you going to leave?' asked Mr.Crawford. 'Wha- oh yeah! Sorry!' I said, snapping back to reality. I grabbed my things and left, thinking that I might as well start working on the robot as soon as I got home, that way I wouldent have to stay up TOO late.                 'MOM! I'M HOME!' I called out into my house after arriving. 'Good honey, welcome back.' Responded my mom. I took off my backpack, and went out to the garage to see what I could use from there to build my robot. I managed to find a bunch of good supplies to work with, and I got to work.                                                         *             *                *             Finally, finished! And it only took me two hours! My robot stood about two feet tall, with some old lightbulbs as the 'eyes', 'legs'made out of an old four wheel scooter, and a plow in the front made out of a broken shovel in the front to move the ball. I made a simple motor by the wheels to move my 'robot', and to be energy efficient, the motor was powered by a solar panel that I put on the robots head. The final thing I had to do was give my robot a name. Tobor was robot backwards, so I decided that that was a good name for it. I put 'Tobor' outside and left him there so he could charge, and then I used the rest of my time that night to watch TV then go to bed.                 BOOM! CRACK! I woke up, startled. I heard a storm brewing outside, so I started to fall back asleep. Then I rememberd Tobor. I jumped out of bed, and ran outside, but it was alredy too late. On my way out, I saw a bolt of lightning streak across the sky and strike Tobor. I figured he was a goner, but then the strangest thing happened. I saw, peering at me where Tobor was just standing, was a pair of glowing lights, about two feet above the ground. 'Thats strange.' I thought. So I carefully walked over and found that the lights where lightbulbs. Familiar looking lightbulbs... Tobor! I ran over and saw, to my surprise, that Tobor was moving towards me. On its own. It stopped right by me, and did a quick spin around as if to say 'Yay! Im alive!' 'I must be dreaming,' I thought.  So I went back to bed.                 Turns out, I wasn't dreaming. Tobor was waiting for me in the kitchen when I walked downstairs. He greeted me with that same spin that he gave before, and followed me everywhere. I took him on the bus with me to school, wich got me a very stange look from everybody on the bus. I brought Tobor with me into science class, where the robot testd were just begining. 'Ah, Luke. Your late. Since you've had so much extera time to work on your robot, why dont you take your turn now?' Said Mr. Crawford with a sneer on his face. 'Sure. Tobor, bring that ball to Mr. Crawford.' I said. Of course, Tobor immediatly drove over, scooped up the ball, and brought it to Mr. Crawford. Mr. Crawford was speechless. 'Wha- what else can it do?' He stammared. 'Anything. For instance: Tobor, go bring me those books on the floor over there.' I responded. Tobor obeyed immidiatly. 'Well done, Luke. You can get some candy from the bag on my desk as a prize.' said Mr. Crawford. Of course, Tobor got that for me too.

It was 12 o'clock, midnight. I had worked on him all evening, and was very tired after a hard day. I was asleep. He sat motionless in the garage, as though he were a lampost. But he couldn't do anything about it. At least, that's what I thought.              I woke with a start. Something banged hard against a wall, but I could not dtermine where the sound was coming from. I was still half asleep when I first heard the noise. There it was agin. What could it be? I thought. I couldn't really process anything. My brain was still tired. I needed more sleep. But I couldn't help but wonder, where was that noise coming from? Could it just be my father, doing some late night work? I had no idea what it was. It wasn't like me to be this curious, but I had to investigate.             I slipped out of bed and put on my bathrobe. I searched my empty floor for my slippers, but could not feel them anywhere. So i went to my doorway and found my flip flops. It was the best I could do. Our whole house was wooded, and very cold on barefeet. I twisted the doorknob slowly and carefully, not wanting to awake anyone near this hallway. I slowly walked out, tip toeing my way to the living room. I heard it again.            BANG! It went. But the sound seemed fainter. I guessed I was headed in the wrong direction. I turned back, heading toward the garage. That was usually where I found my dad finishing up projects late at night. I had just made it to the entry way.                                                                                                    There it was.                     He stood in the middle of the doorway, staring straight ahead. It was him. My creation, my robot.            Did I leave him out? I thought. Maybe I just forgot to put him away. But then it happened. barely noticable, but I saw it. His head tilted, leaving it at an angle. Then slowly, he turned himself to face me.           Was this really happening? What have I done! Then, I took one last glance at him, and ran. Back to my room. I slammed the door.           My mother woke up, and sat with me on my bed. I didnt tell her about anything that I saw. She would never believe me. I told her, 'I was just getting a drink. I got scared because I was alone, and ran back.'                 I woke up late that morning for not having slept at all last night. I went straight to the garage, but the robot was sitting in the middle of the cement, where I had left him yesterday evening. I must have dreampt it. That couldn't really happen, could it? But then it hit me. My brother!           He was only nine, but he loved to pull pranks on people. I'm sure it was him. But what if it wasnt? I would have yelled at him for nothing! I wouldn't accuse him of my dream. And besides, I am prone to sleepwalking!

Shadow Keeper                                                                      It was just another Monday morning on the farm, I got up, ready to check the plants, feed the cows, feed the chickens, feed the horses, check for eggs, water the garden, eat breakfast.  There were so many things to do on the farm, it was overwhelming!  As soon as I finished eating, I made a checklist of things that I need to do.               Checklist           Check plants Feed animals water garden Check for eggs                                         As soon as I finished making the list, I walked down towards the fields.  I inspected the fields and then took off towards the chicken coop.  There were several eggs, so I took one of the baskets that were right there and put them in.  I sprinkled chicken food in the coop snf watched the chickens scramble around.  I darted off to the cow pasture and poured water into the tub and put special grains in the buckets.  I then scurried off to the horse stable and visited each stall, but before I was going to feed them.  Something caught my eye.  In the storage large storage room, the door was open and something was inside.  I backed up and took a better look, but before my mind realized it, the large shadow lurched in my direction.  I screamed and fell over with a thud.  The shadow was right over me.       Before I knew it, I was in a dream.  This was no ordinairy dream, this was a trap.  I was surrounded by darkness, and out of the shadow walls came the shadow.  It's majestic sleek horse-like body glinted in the darkness.  He was tall, and his coat was a purple-black shadow color.  A sudden voice surrounded the area.    'Alice,' it said.       'How do you know my name? And who are you?' I said back.       'Alice, that doesn't matter. But I am Shadow Keeper, keeper of all secrets and shadows,'  he responded.       'Why are you here?' I asked.       ' Because, Alice, I am here to help you get through.  There is a gate opening and you   need to stop it,' he said.       ' But why me?'  I asked.       ' Because, with me and you on a team, we can stop the gate from opening,' he stepped   under a small opening with light shining on his figure.  He was a horse, but not just any horse, a robot horse.       ' Okay,' I said.       With one stomp of his hoof, a swirly portal appeared.       ' I'll meet you back there,' he said.       I leaped through the portal and in a second, I was standing in front of the storage area.  Seconds later, Shadow Keeper appeared right in front of me.  He turned to the side and I hopped onto Shadow Keeper's smooth steel back.  I held onto hid neck as he started into a smooth collected canter.  The wind blew my blonde hair back, and I straightened up and held onto the reins that I hadn't noticed.  The rush of cantering had never felt so good.       When we got to the gate, it was a swirling red and black floating circle. I could'nt see a problem, but if Shadow Keeper said it was, I was going to believe it too.  A sword appeared to my right and together, Shadow Keeper and I moved in unisin.  He lunged towards it and then turned to the left abruptly and I slashed the sword across the gate.  The gate sliced into two pieces and fell apart.       As soon as it was over, I was trrasported back to my room.  It was 8:30pm and it was dark.  I wasn't sure what had happened, but I went out to my balcony and looked into the sky.  A certain star looked like Shadow Keeper, and it glinted, and I heard Shadow Keeper's voice in my head.  It said...       'Alice, I am very proud of you.  Thank you for closing that gate with me.  If you hadn't done that, by now, your world would've probably been destroyed by now.  Thanks again,' he said.       I was happy, and now, it was time to get a good night's sleep.  In my dreams, I couldn't stop thinking about the adventure.

'We should get out of here Kattie!' said my BFF Amanda.  We were at the abandoned junk yard at the end of town, and I loved going to scary places.  Amanda on the other hand, just wanted to go home and forget all about it.  'You know this place is supossed to be haunted' she said for the hundredth time.  'That's exactly why we came here' I replied in annoyence.  ' Now, first thing we gotta do, is climb that fence!'.  Being the gymnast that I am, I cleared the fence in one easy front flip.  Amanda, of course, took about a million hours just to get to the top of the fence.  'I'm stuck!!' she cried.  'Stay there, I'll get you!' I belowed up to her.  I started to climb up the fence, but then she yelled down, 'Kattie, just go without me!'.           'Scaredy cat' I muttered under my breath as I dropped to the ground.  All around me were piles and piles of trash of all kinds.  Old cars, bruised bananas, busted lamps,...and a shiny silver key.  I picked up the key.  It felt smooth and cool in my hand.  A booming noise shook the earth.  Poor Amanda was so startled, that she let go of the fence and fell to the ground.  Luckily she wasn't hurt.  A blinding light filled the sky.  I expected it to start raining, but instead, colors started swirling all around me.  In a burst of pink, blue, and green, I held in my hand a tiny, little robot.           I screamed, Amanda screamed, the robot screamed too.  I dropped the thing and took off.  .......Amanda and I never stopped running until we got home.  Maybe some day we'll go back to the junk yard.  Maybe.

My Day With a Robot   By: Brendon Bussiere                 Hi, I'm Ricky and I'm going to be telling you about my day with a robot.  My dad's an inventor and he's always coming up with new ideas and inventions that usually don't work.  It all started on Saturday morning when I woke up.             It was around 8:00 a.m. when i woke up and got out of bed.  I went down stairs and got a bowl of cereal for breakfast.  My dad was sitting on the couch watching Good Morning America when in came downstairs.  'Good morning' he said 'good morning' I replied.  'You won't believe what I invented this morning' he said 'a robot!' ' does it work' I said ' Uh it needs a little work' he said.  that didn't surprise me.              When i was done my breakfast I went into the garage to see the robot, it wasn't there.  'Dad i called inside 'I don't see your robot' I said ' Oh it's there all right' he said 'You can't miss it.'  I looked around and then out of the corner of my eye saw something move in the corner.  I went over to check it out and when I got there I couldn't believe my eyes I saw a real live working robot!  Then it said in a weird voice 'Hello' I said 'Hi' 'Would you like to go outside' it said' 'Sure' I said.  I went inside and said 'Dad' I'm going outside to play' he said 'OK be back before six' I said 'OK' and that's where my adventure begins.             When i went back into the garage the robot had out a bunch of balls to play with.  we went outside and started to play.  We had a blast we played soccer which he was really good at, basketball, and football.  The ball went over the fence a couple of times because the robot had a great throwing arm.  After that we went out for some ice cream and a walk on the pier.  The robot did not get any ice cream because he could not eat.  Then when we were almost home he said ' I'll race you back' i said 'Sure'.  We raced back, I'd say it was fair but he ended up winning.  We went into the garage and he said that was the best day he would probably ever have.  I turned him off and went inside.  I went and layed down on my bed and did some thinking maybe my dad wasn't so crazy after all.  I decided to name the robot Fred.  Then i thought about how much fun I had and how it was too bad the day was over.  And that's my day with a robot!

'Work. Work! Come alive and do your duty,' It was 7:13 when the mastermind Dr. N. Sane shouted this from his laboratory. His masterpiece rose up from the ground in a cold stony silence. The hulking mass of steel flickered to life like a bear coming out from hibernation. It's chest glowing a very faint blue color and its eyes shaped like bananas opening up with a fiery orange color full of hatred. 'You have come here to seek revenge against the world! 'You will start out as a basic self-driving car, but when the time comes you know what to do.'            As the Dr. said he would, the robot would drive people around carefree. After he finished that job he started to explore volcanoes and collect information for the scientists, but no one knew his true plan. One day when the time was right he used his robotic drill to make a giant hole to let the lava flow out on the surrounding city. He charged into the city with nothing to stop him. Then it struck him and he had a change of heart (actually he had  change of gears).            He decided that pillaging cities and burning down towns wasn't what he wanted, he wanted to help out the kitten shelter and make friends with people and animals like othe robots. But, he sensed a problem, abut he couldn't quite put his finger on it. Then it hit him (not the idea the lava dumbo). He went tumbling down the streets stuck in the lava. He didn't have any idea how to stop the lava. He kept rolling down the streets and eventually rolled out. Having no idea how to stop the lava, he walked over to the water tower to get a drink. He took his drill and drilled a hole in the side of the water tank. He gulped down all the water he wanted to cool himself off. Then he realized that all the water pooring out would solidify the lava. He just sat back and watched the problem solve itself.            The next day when he came back he found almost everything destroyed. When he called out for people no one responded. Then, he sat down and cried. I think we have all learned a lesson here; it is that robots can help scinetists, make friends, and drive cars, but when an evil robot tries to change to these robot ways he ends up burning and suffocating people and a city.

?       My Robot Comes Alive            By: Kelly Meinhart                     It all started one afternoon when I got home from school. I decided to get out my homework and just do it so I wouldn't have to do it later. I opened my binder and started working on my homework. I found the picture of the robot I had doodled at school today. I took it out and decided it wasn't that good after all. I crumpled it up, not wanting anyone to see my robots and threw it in the trash. Then I got started on my homework. I had been working intensively for 1 hour straight, when I heard some weird robot sounds I figured I was probably holusinating from all that hard work I had done. But, no I was wrong, 'BEEP' I heard again. In my mind I figured, nothing wrong with going to check it out. So, I did and you will NEVER believe what I saw.        No this can't be right I thought. Right in front of my eyes was my diasterious robot that I had doodled. My first instinction was to run and go tell my parents, but no they would just think it was all a lie, I had to keep this to myself, no one not even my best friend could know about this. All of a sudden I heard, ' You must save me I amost just died.' I replied back, 'Yeah that was kinda the point.' We then had a whole argument about the trashinh her, and we finally got to the argreement that i would let her stay for 2 days, but then she must go back home, in other words the garbage can.        I then heard the door open, it was my mom, oh no you must hide I thought. I snached the robot ran upstairs and hide her in my closet. I then whispered, 'Don't you dare say a word, we can't let her know you here.' 'Fine then' the robor said sarcastically. I heard the door open, 'Hey is everything okay up her' my mom said anixously. 'Yep' I answered, 'Actually I am just working on a surprise for you.' 'So sweet.' 'Can I just get something from you closet.' 'NO' I screamed, ' I mean that's where your surprise is.'        Finally, it was time to get to sleep, today had been the weirdest day EVER. I really wish that robot had never showed up I thought. Of course I couldn't say anything infront of my sister. I turned of the lights and just imagined that this had never happened. It was impossible though, there is no way I am going to sleep, no way in the world.        Tomarrow morning finally came, I opened my closet door, and nothing was there, but, but, something had been there. I tip toed out to find the robot a step away from my parents bed room. 'Oh no I screamed this can't be happening.' I snached the robot and shoved her out. She told me, 'I must go home? my family needs me.' I tried telling her in the best way possible, 'You are at home.' I then saw billions of robots come out of hiding saying, 'We are here to take over, we are here to take over!' I then screamed, 'NOOOOOO'        I then woke up, my parents had heard me screaming, 'Kelly are you okay?' they asked softly. 'No i'm not these robots were about to take over, and, and.' 'It's okay it as just a dream' they told me calmly.

All of a sudden, Tromlopp heard a noise. Then some whirring and cracking. Then, all of a sudden, he saw two green lights from under a white sheet...        Tromlopp Qupon O'Rustivix McNeper woke up in the morning feeling relaxed and rejuvenated. It was a Saturday morning, and the sun was covered by gray clouds. It was hailing outside. Tromplopp quickly ate breakfast excitedly. There was thunder and lightning. He grabbed his lab coat and hurried to his tool shed. In there was a table with an object under the white sheet.        Tromlopp pressed a button. 'FINALLY!' Tromlopp yelled. He unveiled what was under the white sheet. There lied a robot about the size of a 2-3 year old kid. Tromlopp backed away from the robot and took cover behind a big wall. All of a sudden, lightning shot through the opening of the shed and struck the robot. Tromlopp closed the shed and quickly looked at the robot. Nothing happened. Tromlopp dejectedly walked back to his house. Then, he heard a whirring noise. Then cracking. All of a sudden, Tromlopp saw two green lights turn on from under the white sheet. He ripped the white sheet off the table, and what he saw there changed his life forever.        He put the object on the ground. It was a fully functional and working robot powered by electricity. 'What is your command,' the robot said. Tromlopp was excited. He had big plans. Tromlopp hurried to the United States of America Patent Office. He filed a patent for having the first living robot which is able to follow any command the owner gives it. He was awarded a huge sum of money for his invention. When Tromlopp got home,   he sped to his shed. He asked the robot to do all sorts of things, like make hot dogs, write down pi, teleport to Mars and back. Tromlopp's robot could do anything. Eventually, Tromlopp realized what he could really do with this robot. He renovated his house, made fake money that looked just like real money. Tromlopp was turning evil. The robot would give everything he wanted. When Tromlopp went to the grocery store to find out whether his counterfeit money worked, the store didn't realize a thing.        Suddenly, Tromlopp was going around town buying everything. He bought new land fr his mansion he was going to have built for himself. He bought the local football team (the Washington Redskins) and soon became the richest person in the world and no one knew how fast Tromlopp went from being in poverty to being the richest man in the world.        Then, before Tromlopp could do anything the police burst through the door of his newly built mansion. He was interrogated and was later arrested by Chief of Police Larry Luster. Tromlopp's patent and robot were destroyed and no one knew Tromlopp had created what so many inventors struggled to create.

Ted was in his backyard on gray cloudy day playing with mud and material from the recycling bin. He is connecting the bottles and cans with mud and dirt to create his robot. He finishes his robot with a Gray, square tissue box with a small happy face on the front. There was a loud boom behind Ted and it starts to rain. That night Ted was sitting up in his bedroom looking down at his robot as it starts to turn into a pile of mud and cans. There was a loud crack of lightning as Ted went to sleep.              When Ted woke up the next day he looked out into the sunny backyard to see his robot scorched from  the lightning, but as he kept looking at it he kept looking at it he noticed a slight movement, I'm going crazy, he thought, but as he kept looking at it he realized that it was waving at him. Ted ran downstairs to go look at his robot. ' Where are you going?' his mom asked. But he was already out the door before he could hear her.               When he finally got outside he noticed that the robot's head had turned to metal and the bottle caps had separated into fingers and feet. The robot finally stopped waving, and in a squeaky, metallic voice he said, 'Creator, what is my name?' 'Uh... Your name is Daniel,' said Ted, thinking about his best friend. He was still amazed that a piece of mud and bottle had turned into a working robot. 'Okay! Whatever you say creator,' said Daniel. 'Can you please call me Ted?' asked Ted. After that Ted told Daniel to stay outside while Ted got some breakfast. When Ted got back outside Daniel was still in the same spot where Ted had left him.  'What do you want to do Ted?' asked Daniel. 'We can play dodge ball,' said Ted.                Daniel was amazingly accurate with a dodge ball. Every time he threw it he hit  Ted. His mechanical legs made him turn and run extremely fast. His arms threw the enough force to knock down an elephant. By the time the dodge ball game was over Daniel had one 384 games and Ted had one 16 games. 'That was 400 games total!' Ted exclaimed looking at the ground.                When night came Ted had built a shelter for Daniel on the side of his house. 'Now stay here,' said Ted, pointing at the shelter. As Ted went inside for bed it started to rain and there was lightning. The next morning Ted ran outside to see his shelter burned and a pile of bottle and mud. Ted cried out, 'Why did he have to go!' The sun shone brightly as the day began and even though Ted had only spent a day with Daniel he would remember the day for the rest of his life.

'It was a hot summer day in the city of  Dallas, Texas , and I was working on my newest invention for the science fair, the 'Toy-inator 4000'. It was a small robot that was supposed to play with the you. I was putting the batteries in when the 'toy-inator 4000' came alive! I screamed for my life! I ran down stairs as fast as a cheetah to get a plastic bag so I can throw the thing away, but then it exclaimed ,'Wait! Don't throw me away!I have come alive to help you Sam.' I was in shock. The thing knew my name and I didn't even program it yet! 'Sam, if you throw me away, you wont be able to get the prize for the Dallas City Science Fair' , it told me. 'How do you know me? Where did you come from? Are you an alien?! If so then don't eat me please! There's a leftover hamburger downstairs, it's all yours!' I shouted.'Sam, I will not eat you. You have made me and I am here to serve you. But I still want the hamburger. Last night while you were sleeping, your dad wanted to help you with...well me, so he programed me. He told me everything I had to know. So then today when you put the batteries in, I came alive.' I was trying to take this all in, but I still didn't think it was possible that me and my dad made a robot! 'Okay then. I believe you. Let's go for a test run shall we? Wait. I have to name you because I can't just call you the toy-inator 4000. Its too long. I'll call you Ti.' I replied to him.                Ti and I went to the park to see what special tricks he can do,when we ran into Jamie. 'Oh hey Jamie.' I said in a depressed voice. She was the mean girl who always kissed up to the teacher. 'Hey Sam. What you got there? Is it your little toy? Hahaha what a baby.' she told me. 'No,it's for the city science fair. Ti is my robot that I'm entering.' I replied. 'Greetings Jamie. I had heard you are very mean and-' 'What did that thing just say?!?' she yelled. 'Nothing. He said your dress is nice.' Bye!' I ran home with Ti. 'Why did you say that??' ' The subject was being mean to you. I was defensing you.' 'Okay thanks. But never say that again! Jamie is so mean. Let's just test your tricks in the backyard.' 'Okay dudet.' ' Dont say that.' I replied. 'Hahaha okay sorry.' It said laughing.We tried out all the special tricks that Ti can preform. Turns out he is a good singer, damcer, gymnast, and juggler. I even taught him how to fly. We stayed up all night getting him prepared for tomorrows big contest. My mom even made him a little coat to wear.                    It was the big day and I was very excited. I was setting up my booth when a girl in a pink,flowery dress comes in. It was Jamie. I couldnt believe my eyes! She had a girl version of Ti! She set up her booth right next time. I was as red as a pepper! 'Hi Sam. I didn't see you there.' I didn't replie. It would just make things worse.A little later I told Ti I would turn him off so that when the judges come to our booth, they would see Ti the whole way through. They were at Jamies booth and when I was turning on Ti, he didnt want to turn on! I kept pressing the power button , but he was just sitting there! 'Mom!Ti isn't working!' 'Calm down sweetie.' she told me. ' I brought extra batteries. I figured that he would die out because you kept playing with him all night long.' ' Thanks so much mom. I almost had a heart attack.' The judges came to my table and I turned on Ti. ' Ladies and gentlemen, I present to you Ti. Ti is a homemade robot I made with my wonderful dad.' I told everryone at my booth. Ticonderoga        While I was in my room working on my math homework, a strange thing occurred. Right before my eyes all of my pencils, paper, pens, and other school materials started to connect. As I was looking in awe at the miraculous sight I saw a figure beginning to appear on my desk. What was it and how did it form were the questions I asked myself as I backed away from this creature that was right before my eyes.            I had been studying robots for years and when this 'thing' appeared before my eyes, my research had payed off. 'Would it be like an Agribot picking all of my food, or a Gemini-Scout with his skill in carrying things?'What could this creature do and would it talk? Then I found my answer because of the name that was boarded on the robot, Ticonderoga. This was the pencil brand that helped create this robot, and now it believed that it's name was Ticonderoga. Still though my question was unanswered, what could it do?            As it took out a piece of paper from what I think was its stomach the robot began to write, 'I am Ticonderoga for all your homework needs.' I was in utter shock when I saw this, knowing what this robot's capability was. I began to ask the robot questions like, 'Can you talk?' and 'Are you good at algebra?' The robot named Ticonderoga then began to beep and start blinking with all of his bright lights. 'I am a great mathematician and I do talk' Ticonderoga said in his robot voice. I never thought I would have such an advantage for 'All my homework needs.'               Then a horrible thing happened, my robot began to take all of my homework and shove it into his stomach! I thought he was going to shred it, or much worse destroy it. As time was slow like molasses I waited for Ticonderoga to give me back my homework, in whatever condition it would be. 'Beep' his stomach said and I waited for the paper's that were used as his stomach to unfold and be able to get my homework back.               Then, to my surprise my homework came out in perfect condition. As I took it out of his colored pencil hand I saw writing on it. 'Hooray' I said as I used my calculator to check the answers Ticonderoga had put onto my paper. They were all correct, and in my exact hand-writing! Shocked by this miracle of a robot I had just created I wondered if I could continue to use this robot for my homework.               I came up with a solution because Teacher's Appreciation Week was coming up, and i and not got my teacher a present yet. Would my teacher be helped greatly by this miraculous correcting robot? Of course he would, what teacher wouldn't want a extra hand to correct paper's? While i was saying my good-bye's to the helpful robot named Ticonderoga I put him into a box that said 'Handle with care' and put a pretty red ribbon on the box. Ticonderoga was a great robot, but i hope that my teacher never gives him any papers to hand out, because he will stick those papers into his stomach, and fill them out with all of the correct answers.

The Come Alive Robot                It was a scorching hot day in Lancaster, California, the sun feeling like nothing but a huge ball of fire. My friends, Anette, and America, decided to check out the new museum that opened in town just yesterday! We were all tired and without any energy, but we were desperately wanting to check out that new museum.            As we arrived at the 'Robot Museum', we noticed robots EVERYWHERE!!! Robots awaiting at the front door. robots on the roof, robots wandering helplessly around the museum, everywhere!!! As we came through the sliding glass doors of the museum, we felt a cold blast of air that rejuvenated us, but we were all still tired. We all decided to take the elevator to the second level were robots are believed to come alive. We exited the elevator and we all saw a fascinating robot with tons and tons of buttons, pushing them out of curiosity, but still tired and gloomy. America pushed a big red button, and it started to make a strange beeping noise!!! Beep-beep-boom-beep-beep-boom went the strange button. Out of the blue, green smoke started to come out of the robot, and we all started to fell as tired as ever.            After that little mishap, we realized that the robot with the big red button on it was alive, and rolling around as excited as ever. I got startled and started to panic, finding out that the robot can speak!!!!! 'How do you do?' said the robot. 'Ugh............, um............., were fine?' we all said to the robot.'' My name is Bob and i am a robot who can do whatever you wish.'' ' OK first of all, where are we and what are we doing here?'Your in Robot ville where everything you see are robots,' said Bob. 'O, about what you said, you can do whatever you want huh?' said Anette. 'Certainly, whatever you would like, in fact my middle name is Dowatever!!!' 'Well then, please take us out of....... what the city name.......oh, Robot ville, and return us to Lancaster, PLEASE!!! ' said America. 'Ok then, dipity-doo-dipity-daa, take these girls to Lancaster, yaaaa!!!!!!!!!!!!!!'            We suddenly realized that we were back in Lancaster, in the freshened museum. Anette wanted to return to the house and just have a nice lemonade iced tea, and we all agreed. As we exited the museum, we realized it was night time, and that we had only been in Robot ville for 15 minutes. It got me to thinking, and I realized we fell asleep on the museum floor, and that this was all just a dream.

Bad To Good                   On a cold windy night there was a little boy sitting in his room thinking and thinking about his dream. That little boy was Max. Max would dream about robots over and over again. Untill one day he had decided to make a robot himself. 'I'm going to make a robot that could give me unlimited wishes' he said to his parents. But his parents didnt have the care in the world to pay attention. 'Yeah yeah' his dad would say. 'Go play in your room' shouted his mother. He knew he could make them proud so when his parents went to eat dinner, he stayed up working on his invention.              It took all night but he had finally created the robot of his dreams, The Wishbot 3000. He wanted to try it out so he plugged the wires together but it didnt work. He tried to do everything he could but it was impossible. After half an hour he finally gave up and went to bed. Whir! Whir! He heard something coming from the living room. Whir! Whir! He quickly went out to bed and dashed for the living room. There stood next to the couch was a miricle. It  was The Wishbot 3000. Tears of joy were rolling down his face. finally his parents came home and nearly fainted. Now tears of sadness rolled down his cheeks. His parents still didnt care. They went straight to their rooms without a care in the world as always.             After spending a week with Wishbot and making wishes to help the world he didnt care what his parents think anymore.Weeks passed and some bad news went by. 'I'm here to take over the world' said Wish Bot. I've had a lot of fun with you but I have to complete my mission. Max was on the floor crying his eyes out. Wish Bot needed to do what he come for. So he left the house, leaving Max behind. Months had passed and Max would never forget the time he had with Wishbot. Knock! Knock! Who could it be? There standing on the porch was the one and only Wishbot. Wishbot had never forgotten the time they had together either. Max was crying tears, tears of joy. As the years passed by they have stayed together no matter what.

I think it looks pretty cool. We used the construction paper to cover the cardboard for my robots face. We used the aluminum foil for his body coverings. I hope my art teacher thinks its as cool as I do!                   Sunday has passed. It's Monday. My robot is finished and my art teacher loved it. The thing is, we have to present it. 'Mollie! You're next', said my art teacher, Mr.Davis. Here goes nothing. I started with some facts about robots. 'Robots can be hard-working, and they can be playful. They also can be both, which is exactly what mine is.' Okay, I'm off to a good start. 'Some robots work in hospitals (Mr.Gower), and some work in mines (Gemini-scout). My robot is not real, but a design of the robot Mr.Gower. I have her designed as a nurse and I hooked up a recording in the back that says 'your delivery Is here, just like the actual Mr.Gower.' I took off my cover and everyone was amazed! Some nerd in my art class, Jeffery, asked 'Why didn't you make it real?' My response was 'I didn't have enough time.' I think we know that's true. Thank goodness that was over with.                  When I got home, my parents asked me how it went. I told them it went pretty good and took my robot upstairs. It was late when I got home, so I just went straight to bed. Tried to, anyway. Every half-hour, someone from my school called me. I got the same question EVERY time: Why wasn't your robot real? I was ready to throw the phone! 'I wish it as real, so I could sleep in peace without people calling me every 30 minutes!',I screamed. Right after I said that, something strange happened. I heard a loud noise and it was coming from my robot. I got up and approached it slowly. It started talking. It didn't say what was on the recording, it said 'You didn't want your friends, so now you have none.' I thought I was dreaming at first, so I ran into the door. Shouldn't have done that. Now I have a black eye. So I guess it's not a dream, after all.                  I didn't know what to say. When I got to school, nobody but the teachers were there. I was worried so I called my big sister, because I knew my parents were working. It said there was no phone with that number, so I called my parents and asked them where my sister was, and they said what sister, I was an only child!!! I was even more worried now. What do I do?                 I went home and talked to my robot. She said after what I said last night, she wanted to help me because I was her creator, and she thought I meant I didn't want my friends, at ALL! I talked with my robot for a long time! She said she was sorry and that she would try to reverse it. She said all she needed was pictures of me and my friends from before they, kind of, like, disappeared! I had a bunch, so it went by fast. I just hope I get my friends and my sister back! I miss them so much. Guess what? It worked.              The only thing is that they don't know about what happened. They think they've been here the whole time, and I'm okay to think that, as long as I have my friends.

In the year 3000 there was a robot named Magage was wondering what it would be like if there were humans on her planet, Hemon. Just then it was announced that there was a group of robots being gathered for training t go to Earth, the planet of the humans. Magage was excited. She wanted to go to Earth and play with the humans. She hurried to the Command Center to check the list posted on the entrance and sure enough her name was the first one there. She went inside of the vast building and down the steep ramp to the CCPR (Command Center Program Room). She was welcomed in and ushered into a room across the hall and plugged into a machine. She woke two hours later in a Launch Room with her other 'launchees.' She was assigned to a number, 123456741852963, and put into a room and shut off.            She woke and looked out of the window to see space, space, space, Earth! They would be landing soon.            When they landed the robots were split into groups of three. The names of the other robots in her group were Joam and Derlk. They were launched out into space together and instructed to go to a country in Earth call America. They did as they were told, went to America. Magage, Joam, and Derlk split up to gather the most information. Joam went to New York, Derlk to Texas, and Magage went to Michigan. Magage was too absorbed with the buildings, flying vehicles, and the people to gather information. The people oh the people were lovely! She was following a person called Jen when she was shot. She immedietly sent a distress message to the CCP to warn the others when the radio filled with them. Oh no! Magage thought. They are attacking us! This is terrible! Someone picked her up and carried her into a building. The person sat Magage down and looked at her. It was Jen! Magage thought. She thought this untill she exploded. All of her parts flew around the room. Jen jumped back and ran away. Back at the CCPR there was maddness, everyone speeding around trying to warn the robots that haven't been exploded. Out of the 150 robots sent to Earth only one made it out. His name was Gerge. He was sent back to Earth. While he was there a child chopped him in half with an ax. It was now clear to the CCPR that the humans didn't like robots.

Fiction                Have  you ever heard those stories, the ones that begin with 'Once upon a time' and end with 'Happily ever after?' Well my story is nothing like that. My story begins with something rather different. It goes like this.               'Mavis! How many times have I told you! You can not get another pet! Isn't one cat enough?' My mom yelled. 'But mom, Raelina is really old!' I said. I was going to say something else but my mom interrupted me before I could. 'Honey, Rae Rae isn't that old.' she said calmer. 'Yes she is! I got her when I was two when I got her. Now I'm twelve!' I yelled. ' But...' Before she could say anything else I ran out the door and slammed it behind me.               'Hi, Mavis! What's wrong?' said my best friend, Sophie. 'Nothing.' I muttered. ' I know something is wrong, you only go up in that tree when some thing is really bothering you.' Sophie knew everything about me. ' I just need some alone time.' I don't mind when she talks to me, but right now is not the time for any one to be by me. ' Well you can never be alone with that book around you, you always have your face stuffed in it. Besides, don't you have something to be doing right now?' 'What?' 'Didn't you hear the news, about  the meteorite hitting Julius Park?' 'Lets go!' I hopped out of the tree and on to the ground.              The meteor was huge! Almost the whole park was destroyed! 'Lets go closer!' 'We can't.' 'Yes we can!' Sophie was starting to get annoying. 'Fine, but then we are coming right back here!'                It took a while to get through the crowd, but we got through. There was something metal sticking out through the rock. They were trying to get it open, but could not.                It was getting dark when they finally gave up. Every body had to leave, and everybody did. Except me and Sophie. We ran to the meteor. There was something moving inside of it! Before we could get a closer look, whatever was inside of it burst out of it!                 It was a robot! I had an amazing thought. Maybe if my mom won't let me have another live pet, maybe she would let me have a robot! I was really exited!                 As me and Sophie walked home with the robot, which I had named Marley, Sophie stopped she ran away in fear, i wondered why she did. I tried to stop her, but she wouldn't, so I kept walking. I turned around and Marley was slowing down. I wondered why. Then Marley darted at me and before I could run away she jumped on me. I closed my eyes and waited to die. Then something weird happened, something was licking my face. It was Raelina. Yes, I finally woke up!

In the year 2458, there a brilliant man named Ulfred. He lived in the richest part of his town, and was known for making remarkable robots. The only thing wrong with them was that they never functioned correctly. The designs and mechanics were remerkable, though what good is that when the robot doesn't even turn on. Everyone from around came to see Ulfred's fantastic work. The robots were all different. They were different sizes, colors, heights, and weights. Though one day, Ulfred made a different robot. This robot was unlike anything anyone had ever seen before. Ulfred made this robot special. He used a new power core that has never been used until now. He used the legendary blue lyrium ore, and after that day, everything changed forever.                      'There, it's finally finished!' Ulfred had just finished making his brand new model of a robot. 'Alright then, all I have to do now is add the lyrium core and I should be done,' he said with delight. At that remark, Ulfred ran over to the freezer where the lyrium was being held. Carefully, he took the frozen lyrium core over to the lifeless robot. Though before Ulfred placed the core into the robot's head, a thought occured to him. 'Wait a minute,' Ulfred said aloud. 'I have to give this little guy a name. I've got it! Z5T3! Now, let's put this core in the robot.' Ulfred carefully places the core in the robot's head. Then, suddenly something happens that Ulfred did not expect. The robot started to glow a bright blue, and then started making beeping noises. Within just a few seconds the robot was on! It was fully functional and everything. Ulfred couldn't believe it.                     After a few minutes, the Z5T3 actually said something! 'Hello,' it said . 'My name is the Z5T3. Pleased to meet you.' 'It's nice to meet you to,' Ulfred said excitedly.'Now, I have an idea that you may like.' 'I'm listening,' the Z5T3 said. 'Well, I was thinking how I created you. I built you to be able to withstand extreme heat temperatures, have super strength and to be able to gather useful information. It might be a good idea if you could respond to any calls for help in the area.' 'That sounds like a great idea,' the Z5T3 said. 'Great, well let's just get a few things...' BEEP BEEP BEEP!!! An alarm rings nearby. 'Attention all citizens, there is a roaring fire ablaze in the city, please evacuate ASAP!' The radio blared through the speaker. 'Well, are you ready for your first test?' Ulfred asked excitedly. 'Of course,' the robot responded. And with that, the Z5T3 rolled out to the nearby fire.                      Once the Z5T3 reached the fire he was ready for some action. The excited robot rushed into the building to check if anyone was trapped inside. One he got up the fourth floor, the Z5T3 heard crying to his left. The robot rolled around until he found the source of the wails. It was a baby, no older than a couple of months old. The Z5T3 took the child outside, then raced back inside the ablaze building. Again, the Z5T3 was checking for any trapped citizens. Once he reached the eighth floor, the robot listened and heard really loud screaming up ahead of him. The fearless robot bolted for the sound, and then found the source of the screaming. An old lady was trapped under a wardrobe, and very close to the fire around her. Quickly, the Z5T3 lifted the wardrobe with ease. He then helped the old lady get outside safely. The robot searched the rest of the building but could find no one else. So, after completing his task, the Z5T3 went back to Ulfred's lab. 'You did it!' Ulfred rn across the room and congradulated the happy robot. 'Z5T3, I think this is going to be a longlasting partnership of successful business

The Mushroom Robots                   One day in The Brown Mushroom Rebel Base (BMRB) they were working on an experiment in the underground laboratory and were making a rebel robot so strong it would destroy the rein of King Barry (The evil red spotted mushroom) and his army of evil squids. As they were working the leader of the experiment, Triston Mushberg, came in and asked where they were in the project. 'Not so far sir'. Said John Mushinham the junior scientist. 'King Jeffery III ,leader of the BMRB, is requesting a medicine robot for the mini hospital down the hall.' Said Triston Mushberg.         Meanwhile at the Red Spotted Mushroom Base (RSMB) they are making robots of their own. King Barry is planning on making an animal robot like an ocelot or something to scare the Brown Mushroom Rebels. His son Prince Eggbert I disagrees with his fathers evil plan to enslave all of the Mushroomians. His scientists then start designing a high tech ocelot that will scare the BMRB to peices. When it was done they tested it out on Bob Van Stinklaberg (Their testing dummy). Let's just say his service was a week from then, R.I.P..Then they locked it up in a cage and left it there until they needed it.          Back at BMRB  there was a new rebel. Her name was Zoey but she was not a mushroom she was a human. She got accepted because of she was a smart girl, she was a scientist, mushroom enthusiest and an alchemist but the brown mushroom rebels didn't know about the alchemist part, they frown upon alchemy. They beleived she could help construct the robots so she accepted the challenge and got to work on the Rebel Robot and Medical Bot.           At the RSMB they were doing completely nothing and King Barry was bored so he just slept all day and when he woke up he realized he only slept for a half n' hour. So he got out of his bed and went to the laboratory they were working on a mobile that can drive its self. It was nothing that King Barry has ever seen before. Mostly because it wasn't done. So now the RSMB was just waiting for something to happen.              Now we are back at the BMRB and Zoey has finished creating the Rebel Robot and the Medicine bot. She says their technical names are Rebel Robot: Prototype 4593 code blue nick named Johnny Iron. Medicine bot: Prototype 555 code red nick named Red Five. They were done and King Jeffery III was happy with the girl and expected higher quality work from then on. He then asked her to construct a super computer in the bases only abandoned room. She then tried to find a way out of it and tried running away but a gaurd named Teep (The Mute Dinosaur) caught her and locked her in prison she then formed a band with the other inmates and became 'famous' for her song 'The mushroom prison blues'. One of the inmates was a robot named John he was made to look like a human but the scientists failed and John went bezerk and is wrapped in his robes in prison. She then escaped with a conveinent lock pick on her prison bed and got everyone else out too. She then went and hid in the secret part of her living quarters and wrote in her online diary. She had to go. She started her escape plan and then got to it. She dug her way out through the secret room in her living quarters. She escaped and lived at her friends house for the rest of her life.           King Barry was bored so he planned an attack against the brown mushroom rebels. He got his squid army their robotic suits so they could survive on dry land. He then led his army their and when King Jeffery saw his army coming he went out there with a peice treedy and King Barry refused to sign it but his son, Prince Eggbert, turned the army against his father and then King Barry signed it.            All was well in the land of mushrooms after this point. they all happily lived in the mushroom land where they raised cows and pigs and even grew farms with melons and pumpkins and wheat. King Jeffery and King Barry actually got along after that they would golf and all sorts of things. All of the scientists , not including Zoey, got together and built a car that drives itself. They called it the VroomShroom. The End.

Meet the Hugo       By: Sharon Wu           My dad once said to me robots are might to be treat kindly and be respect. Ben Smith, my dad was the number one robot builder. He became famous by building the world's smartest   robot, Mert. Mert was sell for billions and billions of dollars. He made so many robots rapidly, he won the Noble Peace Prize. In his twenties, he marry to my mother, Linda and he was the happiest man on the face of Earth.When I was 1 years old, my dad die and no one knows what happen. The world's face is now the saddest thing in the universe.He left a present that wasn't finished, the Hugo, for me.            Now I'm 12 and decide it was my duty to finished the Hugo. The Hugo look like it was half done and also broke. I thought to myself ' Sharon, you can do this, it was the only thing your dad left you'. While studying the Hugo, I found a dusty paper that was wrap up like it was top secret. As I open the paper, I found a letter that was written for me! The Gemini-Scout is a remote-controlled robot that does search-and-rescue work in mines and under the ground. The robot is less than two feet tall and has wheels. It can even roll through water. The robot is small,but it is strong. Gemini-Scout carries food,water,and other supplies. It can even drag hurt people to safety. So that one is helpful for many things just for man's they cant roll through water and its not that big but it is strong. It can even drag hurt people to safety.           The Dante 2 is a robot with an interesting job it climbs into volcanoes to gather information for scientists. Like a spider, this robot has eight legs. This helps it climb the steep walls of the volcano. It is also built to survive very high heat. When a volcano is too dangerous for scientists to enter, Dante goes instead. Dante 2 looks for vents, or holes, in the crater. Then the robot collects information about gases that come out of the vents. In the past, scientists could not learn as much about volcanoes, but Dante 2 is changing that. Now scientists can study volcanoes.                                              Mr.Gower is a robot that works in the hospitals, helping doctors and nurses bring medicine to patients. Mr.Grower looks like a small cabinet on wheels. The body of the robot is a stack of locked drawers that store medicine. Nurses and doctors can unlock the drawers when the medicine is needed. Mr.Grower can go anywhere in the hospital. It can ride elevators,steer through hallways, and move around things that get in the way.            An agribot is a robot that picks fruit. It might pick berries,oranges,grapes,or apples. Agribots are not yet widely used, but farmers are very interested in what these robots can do. Because picking a strawberry is different that picking an apple,agribots come in all shapes and sizes. Some have giant arms that are towed behind trucks.Others are able to move around on their own. In Japan, there is a strawberry-picking robot that can sense the color of the berries this helps the robot know when each berry is ripe.But when a robot senses that a tomato is ripe, it uses a mechanical arm to pick the tomato. Agribots may seem unusual now, but one day they nay be common farms.

He approached the building cautiously, for the door was cracked open and he did not know who or what could be in it. When he got to the door he slowly and quietly opened it just enough so that he could see inside. Inside he saw all kinds of tools, pieces of metal and robotic parts. So as our back plan we went to the pool. The pool was open Monday-Saturday.   A old, creepy, mean guy owned it, he was always up to no good.       But we'd never ever ever thought he would do this.       As Samantha and I were splashing around and having a good time we heard a loud   crash in the man's shed, (right near the pool).     I got up and told Sam we should go see what it was.       We peeked around the corner. I almost screamed! DU DU DUNNNN!!!!        In the shed, large rows of Gemini-Scouts were lined up and the man was looking them over.              Gemini-scouts were helping robots why would the mean, old man be helping?          I walked in no longer afraid. Sam tried to stop me but I kept going.       'Hello', I called. He spun around fast. 'What are you doing here!!!'   'We can to see what the big crash was about.'           'Nothing now get out!!!' 'O-k, jees!'         We left and Sam had to go home. I saw the robots from earlier! they were coming and invading!!!!          I had to stop it. The man must have trained them to break things!        I remembered from the book I read about them the always helped a injured person i had to pretend to be hurt. It was a Saturday and he had no plans for that day.  Then he started thinking about the robot.            'Mom,' Bill asked, 'can I have a robot?'            'A robot!'  Bill's mom answered.  'In what world could we afford a robot?  We can barely keep the house heated!'            'Maybe I could make one!'  Bill exclaimed.  'Please mom, can I, PLEASE!'            'What would you use to make one?'  Bill's mom asked.            'Easy, I could use my old toys and some scrap metal in the shed!'  Bill said.             'Alright, Bill's mom answered.  'But you have to pay for allof it!'             Billy got so excited, he only ate half his breakfast, and then ran to his room to find his useless toys.  He thought to himself, 'I'll use all of my legos, my army men, and my robotic dog.  Bill got all of the scrap metal in his back yard and went to work.  At first, he had to decided what to make the body out of.  He chose the scrap metal.  The body would be 4 feet in diameter.  It would have a compartment in it for anything he wanted.  He also made the legs and the arms out of scrap metal.  they could move around very easily.  He made the hands and feet out of plastic from the legos and army men.  He melted them so he could mold them.  He added wiring throught the arms and legs to the hands and feet so he could move around and pick up stuff.  Finally, he made the head.  He use scrap metal for that, but he put the battery from the robotic dog in it to act as a brain.             Bill added extra acceseries.  He added a plug inj for the battery in the back of the body.  He made a face and gave him a tie.  He added a milk shake maker inside the compartment.  It made what ever flavor you could ask for.  He added a jetpack so it could fly.  Ofcourse Bill would need to add a strap so he could hold onto it and they could fly around together.  Finally, he nemed him Terry, after their town's name, and engraved it into the top of his body.  Then he plugged him in so he would charge.            3 hour later, Bill went to turn him on.  He wouldn't move.  The robot was frozen.  'I should of known that this wouldn't work!!!!'  He yelled.  He went to bed that night.  before he went to sleep he made a wish.             'I wish that my robot would come to life!  I spent all day making it.'             The next day, Bill woke up to the sound af a weird voice.  It was his robot!!  He ran down to the shed tosee him.  His mother had already beat him there.             'Oh my Lord!'  Bill's mother yelled.  'What in the world is this?'             'It's the robot I made,' Bill answered.  'His name is Terry.  I thought he would never come to life!'             Bill became best friends.  The next day at school, he brought his robot.  He was amazed at how differently people treated him.  They were drooling over Terry.              'I want it!'  Yelled just about every kid there.  Of couse Bill would never give up his new best friend.  They were going to work together to do his homework, and to try to get other friends.  The teachers even let him into the classroom.  Bill started getting all A's in class, that they let him out of school early.  He wouldn't have to come back to school all year.            Bill would fly around with Terry and they would got to the top of skyscrapers, the mountains, pretty much where ever they wanted.  The only bad part was that every night, he would have to charge.  Bill eventually upgraded Terry and gave him wheels.  He could go as fast as 567 mph.  They entered him in races and they got rich!  Bill and his family moved out of their small house and into a mansion.             'Bill, you have made us rich!'  Bill's mom said.  'We can never thank you enough.'            'For now on, you get what ever you want!'  Bill's fathere said.            'No need for that, Terry made all of the money,' Bill said.  'You shouldn't give me special treatment.  Terry should be getting what ever he wants!'            'Beep, I Love You,' Terry said.  'You can do whatever you want with that money, besides, you made me.'            Bill kept upgrading Terry.  Soon he could dive under water, explore space, and he ran on solar power so they wouldn's need to charge him.  The family's power was out of control.  They could do whatever htey wanted.  They bought a castle, and had their own army!  Soon, they could be the richest family in the world.            Terry started to do more jobs, like taking people under water to where no submurine could ever go.  Scientists hired him for research.  Bill and Terry were getting split apart.  Bill's parents were so power crazed, that they didn's care about Bill and Terry having fun.  They just wanted money.  Soon Bill said 'Enough!'  He hid Terry in his room, where his parents wouldn't find him.  He spent all his time with him.  Whenever his parents asked where he was, Bill just didn't answer.              Every night, Terry would take bill on an exciting adventure.  One time, when they were going int space, Terry's solar panel's were hit by a meteorite.  He lost all power immedietly.  Bill was trapped in space with his best friend broken.  He was still alive, but could barely talk.  He knew he needed to get him in a charger right away.  He didn't even think about himself sufficating.             Bill kept trying to fix his solar panel, but it never worked.  He eventually started getting light headed.  Hepulled Terry back to Earth as fast as he could.  He knew if he took to long, he would die.  He made it into the atmosphere three sceonds before he ran out of air.  It was a long fall, but he landed in his swimming pool.  Bill got Terry on a charger and he came back to life.  He never wanted to go into space again.             Bill hid Terry in his closet, and because Terry wasn't doing any jobs, his parents kept moving into smaller houses because they couldn't afford the ones they were in.  Within three years, they were moved back into their house that thy lived in at the beginning, and his parents took their jobs back.  Everything was back to normal, and Bill and Terry were best friend for the rest of his life.                                                                                                   The End

'Kevin! You hovercraft is here!'       'Just a minute mom! I have to pack my schoolpad!'       Kevin McFanter really wasn't packing his schoolpad, which gave him all his notebooks and textbooks that you would probably use in the 2000's. He wasn't eating his breakfast either, which happened to be a milkshake that gave you the strength of the world strongest man and the speed of the world's fastest man. What Kevin was REALLY doing was adding the finishing touches to his new robot, which was a combination of Wall-E and R2-D2; meaning Wall-2D2.   The only reason he even knew about those old stories form centuries ago was because of his grandfather, who had inherited pictures of the two fictional robots from his grandfather, who inherited the pictures for his father, a fellow named George Lucas.   Along with those picture there were blueprints on how to make a actual version of the robots, which Kevin obviously used.   'There, finished!' exclaimed Kevin. Wall-2D2 was done and ready to roll all around the house.  It had a head with two mechanical eyes that had windshield wipers, a dome body that was blue and white and resembled the head and torso of R2-D2, arms that could extend to almost 5 feet long with hands that resembled those of a Lego mini figure, treads for feet, and a whole lot of mini gadgets that Kevin added to the design. It had a cup holder, DVD and CD player, coffee maker, mini fridge full of meal milkshakes, a holographic picture device, rockets hands and, in case of emergency, a self control mode where you can get inside of Wall-2D2 and control it to your liking. It was as if nothing else was needed at all.   'Kevin, come on!' Yelled his mom, Kathy McFanter'You're going to miss the school hovercraft!'   'Coming mom!' replied Kevin, adding the 55 gigawatt batteries to Wall-2D2.   All of a sudden light comes out of Wall-2D2's eyes. The Kevin hears a voice.   'System Start Up initiated. Please adjust settings to liking of owner.'   'Wow!' yelled Kevin'That was sooooo cool!' Then Wall-2D2 says' Hello valued master. My names is Wall-2D2. Please insert you name into the touch screen on my back.' Kevin types his name in using the keyboard. ' Thank you Kevin. Would you like me to take you to school?'    'No thanks' replies Kevin. ' I should really take my hovercraft.'   'You missed it.' says Wall-2D2 'I can tell because of my data scan of a 26 mile radius of the surrounding area. I suggest you hold on to my arms'        Kevin did as he said. 'Wait I forgot my school paaaaaaaaaaddddddddddd!'   In 3.24 seconds, they were out the door and off to Kevin's school.   'Don't worry Kevin. My touch screen has all your data on it. Just pop it off my back and you will be ready for you classes.'       'How did you get all of my notes and all my textbooks on your back pad?'   '26 mile data scan remember?'       And so, Kevin went off to school, which was only two hours long because of all those intelligence chips that they have in those Thinking Caps, and went home from school with Wall-2D2 and had fun for the rest of the school year and summer.
