The Nitro 360            In the year of 2094, a girl named Aurora went up to her bedroom after her tenth birthday party to put all of her new presents that she got from family and friends, away. What she didn't know while going up the long pathway of stairs was that, sitting at the foot of her bed in her bedroom, was one more present from her parents. When she saw how big it was, she gasped. She hurried to put all of her presents away then went to the foot of her bed to open her last present of the day. She tore off the bright red wrapping paper. It was a new robot. One that she had been wanting since she was about 5 years old.       She screamed in excitement. She took it out of the box and put the given batteries into Nitro 360 and tried to turn it on. It wouldn't turn on. She tried and tried but it just wouldn't turn on. She went downstairs to the kitchen to tell her mom and dad that the present that they had bought for her had not been working. Her dad went up to her room to find out what was wrong with the new robot, but couldn't find out what the problem was.        That night Aurora went to sleep disappointed. But while she was asleep, in the darkness of the cold night, there was a loud sound coming from her room. The robot had turned on. Aurora woke up surprised, scared, but also excited. 'Hello. I am Nitro 360. What may I do for you?' it asked, staring straight towards her. She hesitated on saying what she wanted. She just sat in her bed staring right back at the robot for what felt to her like forever. 'Well, can I have a glass of water? I am thirsty.         She watched as the Nitro 360 suddenly shook, creating a loud buzzing sound that reminded Aurora of a bee. In just a second, the giant robot held a cold glass of water with ice cubes out to her.          She was fascinated. She drank the water then went to sleep. Soon enough, Aurora and the robot became friends. Aurora was thankful to have received such a wonderful birthday present from her parents. Aurora enjoys having the best birthday present she has ever received, the Nitro 360.

There was a town in Nevada called Robotown but surprisingly, they had no functional robots. People came excited to Robotown but left unhappily, probably because they expected to find robots everywhere, but found none. The city was constantly trying to make functional robots, but only succeeded in making toys. Their problem was that they had no small sources of power.            But one day a young boy named Ethan was playing with his toy robot, which he named R9-27J, and accidentally made him touch the power box. There was a bright flash and a loud ZZZZZZZ!    'Whoa. What happened?' Ethan exclaimed.   'Ethan, what are you doing?' called his older brother Zachary.   'Nothing!' replied Ethan.   'Hmm... No you're up to something!' said Zachary. Ethan went to barricade the door but Zachary was much stronger than him until.....            'Beep, Beep!' beeped a voice, 'whirrrrr.' Suddenly the door started to close! It was just then when Ethan realized that a robot was helping barricade the door.   'Ahh!' cried Ethan, jumping back from the door.   'Do not worry, I will not hurt you.' said R9-27J. But Ethan was   still afraid of the now-alive robot.   'Worry not little master, I will get rid of this other being.'said   R9-27J. R9-27J made some more beeping and whirring noises and suddenly, Ethan didn't hear his brother outside the door.   'What did you do with Zachary?' asked Ethan.   'Simple. I teleported him.' replied R9-27J.   'Oh tele-wait what did you do!?' yelled Ethan.           'I told you, I teleported him.' replied R9-27J. R9-27J was obviously very futuristic, but TELEPORTING PEOPLE!           'Ok, let me get this straight, you are a robot that came to life from my power box?' said Ethan.   'Yeah, that pretty much sums it up.' said R9-27J.   'So, where is my robot?' said Ethan.           'I am your robot! What would I be if not your robot?' asked R9-27J.           ' Uhh....' said Ethan.           'See? YOU DON'T EVEN HAVE ANY IDEAS!!!!!!!!!' yelled R9-27J.           'Okay,okay,okay. I said OKAY!' yelled Ethan as his robot started to do the things he liked making him do.   ' Anyways, where is Zachary?' asked Ethan.   'Who is Zachary?' asked R9-27J.   ' The 'other being', the person you teleported!'           ' Oh, he is in South America on one of the jagged rocks in the Strait of Magellan.'   'WHAT!!!!!'   ' I said-'           'No, what meaning.... WHY DID YOU TELEPORT HIM THERE OF ALL PLACES!!!!!' yelled Ethan.           'Fine. now he is in a bear's cave in the Appalachian Mountains.'   'No.'   ' Now in the ruins of the ancient city Jericho.'   'Gah!'   'There is no place called 'Gah'.'   'Bring him back to Nevada.'   'Okay, he is back.'    'Where?'   'Lake Tahoe, Nevada.'           ' Fine. Robotown, Nevada. 9497 Turbo Street. In the foyer of the house.'           ' Request granted, very specific request granted.' R9-27J chuckled.           'Can you teleport me and you anywhere in the world?' asked Ethan.           'Yes.'           'Then teleport us to F.R.C., Colorado. The Failing Robot Center, that won't be failing anymore!'           'Request....granted.'

Gemini-Scout's Mine Adventure                                 The mine was cold and quiet. The rocky walls and floor glimmered slightly from jems and minerals hidden within the rocks. It was quiet and serene, save for the constant 'drip,drip' sound of a trickle of water hitting a small rock. Suddenly there was movement in a far corner of the cave. A silver robot crawled out from under a pile of rubble. Amazingly, there wasn't any damage done to it by the rocks, except for a couple minor scratches. The words,'Gemini-Scout' were engraved on it. The rather small robot looked around.' Where am I?' It asked itself.          Gemini-Scout realized it was in a large mine. However,it did not remember how it got there. 'Maybe if I escape, I can find someone to help me.' it thought. Gemini-Scout turned and realized it had food,water, bandages, and a rope tied to it. 'That will be useful.' It said. With that, it wheeled further into the mine.             The robot traveled for three days, and still had not escaped. It seemed as if Gemini-Scout would never escape the mine. It had spent some time mining though, and it now held jewels and minerals (and a lot of plain rocks). Suddenly, Gemini Scout heard a sound. It sounded like a mixture of a screech and a squeak. Quickly it wheeled toward the noise.         In a few minutes it had found the source of the noise. A small bat had hurt itself by accidentaly flying into a stalagmite, and it was trying to call for help. Gemini-Scout took out the bandages it hadn't used and helped the bat. Soon it was better,but it could not fly. It had a broken wing that needed time to heal. 'Do you know where I can exit this mine?' Gemini-Scout asked the bat. The bat surprisingly understood and started to hop in the direction of a chamber. Gemini-Scout followed.        The chamber the bat had led the robot to was very bright. The jewels sparkled and shimmered, and the rocks seemed to be brighter than the sun. Gemini-Scout was confused. It had been in this chamber before and hadn't found an exit. 'I don't understand.' It told the bat. The bat shook it's head and pointed with its wing (the one that wasn't broken) to a hole in the roof of the chamber. The hole was the source of the light. Sunlight from it streamed in and bounced off of rocks and jems, making them appear to be sparkling. Gemini Scout launched a rope up to the hole,then it hoisted itself up. The bat decided to stay in the mine, but it seemed to wave goodbye to Gemini-Scout.       When Gemini-Scout got out of the mine,it was as if it was in a whole other world. There was green grass, and the sky was a bright blue. A city appeared in the distance. Gemini-Scout noticed a dirt road leading towards the city. It started to wheel down it. Gemini-Scout wasn't sure what it would find when it arrived at the city. 'I hope I can find someone who knows where I am.' It said. Would Gemini-Scout's hopes come true? Was this the end of his adventure? Or was it only the beginning?

Roberto the Robot           'Kylie!' screamed Elliot. 'What?' answered Kylie. Kylie was Elliot's older sister and she had to watch him while their dad was at work. 'Roberto isn't here, I saw him here yesterday.' 'Maybe, you should look harder!' shouted Kylie. Roberto was a robot Elliot tried to create with his mother. The robot was supposed to do  chores, care for people, and talk.       Elliot worked hard everyday to try and finish the robot. It was difficult for him, sometimes his dad or sister helped, but that was rarely. He wanted to finish the robot and make it a memory of his mother. Their mother had passed away in a car crash a few months ago.       Elliot was always having a hard time since she passed. He always thought that maybe the robot would help him. His dad and sister were no help. His dad was always at work because he had two jobs and they needed money, but when he was home, all he did was yell at Elliot and Kylie. Kylie always was in her room, probably on the phone or something because she was fifteen and was older that him by three years. She sometimes made him food when he was hungry, but he could tell she was also struggling without their mom.       Elliot was still looking for the robot and heard a noise. There was a thumping in the bathroom. 'Thump, thump thump.' He was afraid, but kept going toward the sound. He opened the door and was so surprised. There was the robot, standing two feet tall cleaning the bathroom. Roberto turned around and said,'Hehloo, Elliiiot. ' Elliot didn't answer, but just stood there staring at Roberto. Roberto did the same.       Elliot finally talked to Roberto. Roberto was very smart. He knew things from the past which Elliot had created him to do. When Elliot was sad because of his mother, Roberto always comforted him. Roberto did most of Elliot chores and cooked for his sister, his dad, and Elliot. The robot became Elliot's best friend.       Roberto helped Elliot through all of his difficult times. After three years had passed, Elliot didn't get as sad anymore. His father became more supportive and quit his jobs to work in one he liked and they paid him more, and his sister came out of her room a lot more. Elliot also could tell that she liked the robot because it made Elliot happy and she didn't have to cook anymore. The robot was a good memory their mother.

One day, I was in school during science when our teacher, Mr. Rick, told us that we were going to be crafting a home-made robot. Half of the class shrugged, and some did a silent cheer. I was not sure about my feelings about this, but I knew I had to get to work quickly. 'Class is dismissed.' said Mr. Rick. I was still thinking about our assignment and was beginning to get stresse out about it. The rest of the day went by quickly; we ate lunch, had Physical Education class, and then went home. When I got home, I told my mom to take me to a store called Home Depot. It's a really handy store that has everything you need. When we got there, I went into the building isle, with all the nuts and screws and stuff. I picked out all the tools and working materials that I needed to build this robot and went home. Since it was already late, I decided to build the robot later and went to bed. I had slight butterflies in my stomach, wondering how I will complete this big project. Wanting to get away from it all, I closed my eyes and went to sleep.       I woke up to the sound of my annoying alarm clock. The sun was just above the hills, and the sky was blue with a few clouds. I did the usual morning routine and headed to school. When I got there, my friends were standing in front of the gate and talking. Noticing me, they ran up and all asked the same question, 'Did you begin on your robot?' They all had baggy eyes and an expressionless face. I shook my head with grief. When the bell rang, we quickly went to class and began the lesson. It was another stressful day, but I survived it. When I got home, I began on my robot right away. It took all night to make, but it was definitely worth it. The finishing product looked like a short, colorful unicorn.

Dan was planing to make a robot that talks,moves,and helps people with their homework. His main focus was to get it done by the 19th of June,that way he could get it to the teacher for his project and it wont be late. That would give him at least two days to get it done. Before he went to bed, he wanted to make sure all his plans we secure. As the morning came, he stared working on the robot. He graded his bolts, screws, and tools. Finally he was done. He named his robot Nancy.                         He went to bed when all his work was finished. The only thing he didn't do was put the motor and speaker in. That night his mother went down stairs to put everything up, and take a quick look at the robot. She was amazed at what he had done. She put his motor and speaker on the robot and went up stairs for bed. That night he woke up and heard glass breaking and doors slamming. He went down stairs,and he saw his robot in full action. He ran up stairs and got his mother. He asked 'Why is my robot moving and talking!' 'All I did was put your stuff away, and put your motor and speaker next to your robot.' his mother said. 'Did you put it next to my robot or on it.' he said calmly. 'I put it on it.' his mother said getting out of bed and running down stairs. As they were trying to stop the robot, Dan realized that he put an on and off switch on the robot. 'Distract Nancy while I turn her off.' His mom was distracting Nancey. Dan turned her off. He didn't know that once he turned her off he would never be able to turn her on again.                                              As he was going to school, he was thinking of a good way to tell the teacher what happened. He walked into the classroom, and he was the only one without a robot. He went up to the teacher and said,'My robot broke it turned on,and broke everything on ascendent.' 'Well all I have left to do is give you a zero.' his teacher said. Dan walked away with disappointment. He got called up to the office. When he was there Mrs.Taylor handed him a huge thing that had a sheet over it. He was walking back to his class. When he got there he pulled the sheet off of the huge thing. It was the robot, Nancy. He went up to his teacher and showed him the robot. He told Dan to present it to the class. He was scared that it might not turn on and it might mess up like it did at his house. As he turned the switch to on excitement filled the room. It turned on! He continued on with presentation. Luckly he got a 100%.

It all started at the science lab with the rookie scientists. They were sitting in their chairs ready to experiment with the new robot their boss had created. The robot was not meant to come alive. All he was meant to do was sit there and look good for the Museum of Science and Industry in Chicago, Illinois.             Okay, back to the story. So there were these rookie scientists who had no clue how to work with robots. They were just supposed to fix up the nooks and crannies in the robot's outside frame. Those were the directions from the head scientist, Lenny.             Lenny was the meanest guy you could ever meet. He was only about five feet tall with a beard taller than he was. He only had one tooth but he was the best living scientist. He was in the newspaper even in Djibouti.             The rookie scientists had no idea what to do with this robot so........ they started playing with it. They laughed because they were actually having fun. They pretended that the robot was alive. They pretended that the robot was a puppet and they had a puppet show (he was the only character in the puppet show). And, they may or may not have pressed a few buttons.......           'What is all that racket,' Lenny asked as he scurried in to the lab.           'N-n-nothing sir,' said Billy (one of the scientists).           'Yep, absolutely nothing!' Exclaimed Bob (the other scientist)           'Alrighty then. You guys get your butts back to work, or I'll whip y'all,' Lenny remarked.          'YES SIR!!!!' Screamed Billy and Bob synchronized.          Lenny bobbled out of the room on his short and stubbly legs and walked and walked down the pin strait hallway until his shadow vanished.          Billy and Bob started to close up when they heard a strange noise coming from where the robot was sitting on the table.         'Did you hear that?' asked Billy.         'Well I sure did,' responded Bob         They shuffled over to the table but everything was just normal. They checked the electrical wires all over the robot. Everything was just fine. They checked the outside of the robot. Just fine. They even took the whole robot apart to check the 'brain' of the robot (like I mentioned before, these scientists are just rookies so they have no idea what to do). Everything was just fine.         'Well Billy, I don't see nothing wrong with this robot here, but I do know that we better get a move on. It's gettin' really late'        'I agree, lets get out of here'          They turned around and left the building safe and sound, and as quiet as a mouse. Well, not quite....           Not quite.           As soon as that door slammed shut behind Billy and Bob, everything started to get BAD.          Bad.        The robot that was sitting on the table right next to the window sprung up from the table and started, well, he kind of started dancing. He looked like he belonged in a boogie parlor. He did every possible dance move there was.... from the sprinkler to the worm. He was having a lot of fun. He danced and danced and danced until the morning when the rookie scientists came into work.....          Their mouths dropped open.          They went crazy when they saw the robot. Billy dropped to the floor and started crying because he knew he had done something wrong and that he was going to get in A LOT  of trouble. Bob just started dancing with the robot as if he didin't have a care in the world.          Just then, Lenny came running in....        'WHAT IN THE NAME OF SAM HILL ARE YOU WEIRDOS DOING!!!!!!!!!!'        Nobody said a word. They all just stood there in silence.       'WELL, IF NONE OF Y'ALL ARE GONNA SAY SOMETHING, I'M GONNA HAVE TO EXECUTE THIS ROBOT!!!' Screamed Lenny.              'No Lenny No! Please don't hurt him, he's our friend!' Said Bob.        'Ok, but whatever this thing is doing, it better be gettin' outta' here soon!' protested Lenny.        'That will be just fine' said Billy.       'Okay nerdheads, you may take him home,' said Lenny.         From that day on, Billy and Bob still have the Robot in their house doing normal people things. They all lived happily ever after.

The Helping Robots                           Are you interested in the fascinating details of mechanical robots? In my opinion I just adore the idea of robots. After you put the parts together you have to make it work and turn on. Our future as we speak is getting harder and harder by the minute. If you think your job is challenging imagine thousands of robots all over the world doing the job that millions of people do! While people are relaxing and taking the day off robots are working as hard as they can trying to please you. We can even give them names so that we can make them fell better. The better you are to the robots the better they are to you. The perfect name for the robots would be the NSS national saving service. With every robot you have you get to chose their name like Tom,Kaylee,Mike, or any name you want.              If you want a search and rescue kind of robot the robot you'd want would be the Gemini-Scout. The Gemini-Scout is a remote-controlled robot that does search and rescue work in mines under the ground. The robot is less than two feet tall and has wheels. It can go up and down stairs and make tight turns, and it can ever roll through water. The robot is small but it is strong. Gemini-Scout carries food, water, and other supplies. It can even drag hurt people to safety.             If you want a smarty pants robot then you would want Dante 2. Dante 2 is a robot with an interesting job it climbs into volcanoes to gather information for scientists. Like a spider, this robot has eight legs. This helps it climb the steep walls of the volcano. If you are interested in a robot that works in a hospital then Mr. Gower is the robot for you. Mr. Gower is a robot that works in hospitals, helping doctors and nurses bring medicine to patients. Nurses and doctors can unlock the drawers when the medicine is needed.                 If you want a robot that picks fruit then an agribot is the robot for you. Because picking a strawberry is different than picking an apple, agribots come in all shapes and sizes. Some have giant arms that are towed behind trucks.Others are able to move around on therie own. In the Diamond Miners Mining company, there was an employee named Bill. Bill was just a miner like the others, but Bill had a robot arm. Bills robot arm got him the nickname Cyber. Cyber was mining in the Marcelline Mines, a mine rumored to have diamonds and rubies in it's depths, and got a call from the head of the Diamond Miners Mining Company, Mr. Gremlin.'Cyber,' Mr. Gremlin said,'I have a proposal for you and I need you down here quickly.' So Cyber went quickly to the Diamond Miners building and found Mr. Gremlin's office. 'Sit down Cyber,' Mr. Gremlin said, 'I was wondering if you wanted to have a promotion.' Cyber replied,' Yes please sir, but what is this promotion?' Mr. Gremlin stared out the tall glass window of his office. 'We need you to deep into Turnover Mines.'               'The Turnover Mines!' Cyber exclaimed, Those mines are the most fragile mines in the world!' Mr. Gremlin sighed, 'I know, but we need a group of people to go into the mines to search for gold to fund the company.' Cyber thought for a moment and replied, 'Whats in it for me?' Mr. Gremlin was quick to reply, 'Five percent of the treasure you find is yours.' 'I'm in.' Cyber said, and then Cyber left the office to go home and rest for his big day tomorrow.                  The next day Cyber went to the Turnover mines with ten other miners. Mr. Gremlin wished them good luck and they went down deep into the mines. On there way down, they saw a rusty Gemini Scout 1.9. Two of the miners were looking at it when it sprung to life. Unprepared, the two miners jumped backward, knocking over a large boulder. 'No!' Cyber and the other miners exclaimed as the boulders crushed the two miners an blocked their way back.                 The remaining miners sat in a circle wondering what to do when they heard a small electrical hum. The Gemini Scout! The robot, everyone knew, had a built in radio that could be used to contact the outside! The Gemini Scout had also brought a rock tumbling down. Cyber quickly grabbed the Gemini Scout and ran deeper into the mines. Cyber ran until he couldn't run anymore. When he looked around he saw a miner collapsed on the floor. 'Are you okay?' Cyber asked. The miner didn't respond, he was dead. Cyber quickly turned on the radio said one word, 'Help.' The Gemini scout watched Cyber collapse. Cyber was still breathing, but unconscious. Cyber awoke suddenly and looked around. He was in a hospital. 'About time you woke up' Mr. Gremlin said,'good work.' Cyber looked at him in a confused look and Mr. Gremlin said, 'That Gemini Scout of yours not only brought you to safety, but brought up two million dollars worth of gold. Cyber and his Gemini Scout were on the news and newspapers for three months. Cyber still got promoted and went into dangerous mines. Cyber always brought that Gemini Scout with him for the rest of his life.

Humans and Chris       In the spring of the year of 2396 A.D. on an uncharted planet, a science experiment has gone dreadfully wrong and no one civilian will risk taking chances with the destruction of this disaster. All the universe is in jeopardy, in jeopardy of a robot named Tootles. Who will be the valiant hero of all and all within?       It all started one day when a young boy of the age of twelve went to school. Chris disliked school and often skipped class or made lame excuses about illness. But today was different, his mom made him attend school and he couldn't come up with any severe, hospital worthy disease. Chris picked up his worn tattered book bag and went to the bus stop, his mother keeping an eye on him. Finally when the bus arrived, Chris got on and sat as close to the back of the bus as he could.       They arrived at another stop and two large boys with sun glasses and 'gold' necklaces around their necks got on the bus and sat beside Chris. It was Harry and David, the meanest kids ever (at Chris's knowledge) to attend St. Carmichael's. Whenever Chris did go to school, these two would always pick on him. For some strange reason, for the rest of the bus rode, they didn't do anything rude or selfish to Chris.       Once they got to school and they disembarked the hunk of yellow metal, Harry and David put their arms around Chris and said,'Chris, we realized that we have been bullying you for a while now and we want to apologize. We also decided to make you our friend.' At this Chris was scared but thought about what they said, and decided that it would be OK. But this decision of Chris's was unintelligent for he hadn't developed a sense of sarcasm due to the large amount of school skipping he had done over the years. So when Chris agreed to what they said, David mentioned to Harry something Chris didn't hear. Harry said,' Sure David. Hey Chris, since you're our friend now, you need to go through a test that proves your worthiness of our friendship.' Again Chris thought and agreed to it. They picked him up, and carried him off to an unused janitors closet. They then tied him up and threw him on an overturned bucket. They both shouted in unison,'See ya lata' sucka',' shut the door and left! And then Chris thought,'Dang it!'       While Chris was insulting himself for being such a numskull, a huge hole suddenly opened in the floor. All of his bindings flew upward as he fell down in the bright tunnel. It went straight down. Chris was just falling, falling, falling, falling, and falling. The drop never ended. It might have been easily an hour before he slowed down a lot it seemed and the tunnel curved out to the side. A flap opened and he tumbled out of the tunnel, and onto the hard land before him.       Then there was a huge explosion in front of him, a rock disintegrated, then another, then another. No, he was just imagining, his hard fall made him woozy. Chris gathered his bearings and observed his surroundings. Flat dusty land stretched on forever it seemed. Sharp jagged rocks stuck out of the ground. In the distance there was a tall tower that seemed futuristic almost and so did the landscape. Nothing could have been to weird though, it was only the winter of 2396, or was it?       Immediately he made a plan to head to the tower, for that was the first sign of civilization. Hours later he arrived at the tower and before he entered, he heard a kind of wincing, he walked over and saw a creature with red liquid coming out of one of its ligaments. Chris reached his arm out to touch it and it was soft, like human flesh. Chris had just broken the number one rule of artificial intelligence robotic humans, DO NOT TOUCH HUMANS OR HUMAN BELONGINGS. Chris felt his code glitch up. The human was wounded, his body juices were low, according to his sensors. He assisted the human. Once the human was recovered fully, he pulled out what seemed to be a weapon of some sorts and hit Chris with it.       Everything went black, he couldn't see....hear....,'my world is gone,' he thought,'goodbye.'

The Robot in the Attic                   We lived in a village.We live in a big house with four rooms.I live with my mom Julie, my dad Mark, my big sister Clara, my little sister Mya.My mom and dad have a room to share with a bathroom, big bed, desk, and a tv.I sleep in a room with both of my sisters.we have a bathroom, desk, 1 bunkbed and a big bed for my big sister.I have to sleep on the bottom and my little sister sleeps on the top.I woke up this morning before anybody else.I made my bed and went to the kitchen.I opened the cabinet and screamed really loud.My family came down and they all said ''What's wrong Lea?''Well i opened the cabinet and i went to graba bowl and there was a robotic arm in there.My mom grabbed it and gave it to dad and whipered something in his ear and he just left.I was wondering why my dad and mom have been acting strange ever since we got this house.So i followed dad after they went back to bed.He was up in the attic putting something away ina box.When he turned around i ran to my room and got in the bed a pretended i was sleeping.After he got in the bed i got my sisters up and made them come look what was up there.When we got up there we saw a big box like thing with a blanket over it.My big sister walked over to it and pulled the blanket off.My little sister ran to her room and it was just Clara and me.When she pulled it off sure enough it wasn't a box, it was a robot.It looked really old but cool.My sister turned it on and the eyes turned yellow and it said ''Greetings.''Clara and i both ran to our rooms and got under the blanket.I dont ever think i have been that scared before.A little later in the day Clara and i went back up to see if it shut down, but sure enough it was still on.My dad and mom were at work so we were alone.The robot rolled to us and said '' May i assist you in any way?''Well let me tell you something, me and clara weren't gonna let that go by so my sister said ''Go get me a drink, orange juice please.'' Sure enough, 5 minutes later, he came back with orage juice and handed it to my sister, then said ''How can i assist you again?''I asked him to go get me a snack like crakers.He came back with my favorite crakers.''How did you know these are my favorite snacks?''He said my dad and mom told him what we like and everything.I was suprized.Why did my dad and mom not tell us we had a robot?When mom and dad got home and i told my little sister to not say anything about the robot to mom and dad.We hugged them and asked how was your day and all.When we were eating dinner my little sister asked ''Why is there a robot in the attic?''We all froze and mom said ''What do you mean a robot in the attic?''My sister just ran off to our room and started to play with her dolls.I said what all happened and stuff and they just sat there staring at me and my sister.My mom looked at my dad and said ''i think it is time to tell them the truth, they are old enough now.''I said ''Tell us what?'' My dad looked at us with his guilty look and said ''Girls, me and your mom haven't said anything about where i really worked.'' ''I worked at a Machine and Repair center and i built robots, well when i built my first one i didn't ship off i took it to my house, but after awhile i got bored with it so i sold it to a man named John Marcus.'' ''I got a lot of money and i didn't spend it on you girls, i spent it on a tv. i was very selfish with the money im sorry girls.''

I've got a question for you. Have you ever been so bored with no one to do anything with. Your parents are busy. Your friend won't answer the phone and you don't have a sibling to play with. What are you going to do? That's the thought that little Jake had. What am I going to do? He thought.           'MOM!' Jake yelled.           'WHAT!' she yelled back.           'I'm bored!'           She handed him a cardboard box and some markers. ' Use your imagination.'           He looked at the box like it was brussels sprouts. What am I supposed to do with this? He sat on his bed and glared at the box. He layed back and looked at the posters on his walls. He saw a picture Yosaine Bolt running. He saw Le'bron James dunking a basketball. Then he saw the rover on Mars. He studied the rover then looked at the box. He went into the kitchen and grabbed the scissors. He ripped the poster off the wall and put it on the floor to use at an example. Then he started cutting and coloring and cutting and coloring until he was finished.            The box was transformed into a cardboard robot. It had blue arms and green hands. It's body and head was bright red. It's big square cross-eyes were black. He had an antennae that was orange and a big 'J' on his chest.            'Jake 2' he smiled. Jake spent the whole afternoon playing with Jake 2. When dinner rolled around, Jake brought Jake 2 to the dinner table. They played until bedtime. Jake got a pillow and a blanket from the hall closet an tucked Jake 2 in. Then he climbed in bed himself.            'Goodnight.'            The next morning Jake woke to a beeping sound. He opened his eyes to see a tray with scrambled eggs, toast, butter, juice, an orange slice and 3 slices of bacon laying next to him. He smiled.            'Thanks Mom!' he yelled.            'For what?'            That's when he noticed that Jake 2 wasn't under the covers where he left him last night. He got worried. Had Mom thrown him away? Then he screamed. Not a scream that you might hear coming out of someone on a roller coaster, not a scream that you might hear when someone wins the lottery. This scream was a terrifying scream. It was a scream that sounded like feedback from a amplifier. This was a scream that hurt your ears.             Jake 2 was under the tray of food. Suddenly Jake noticed his little green hands under the tray. Jake lifted the tray and Jake 2's little body was alive. His eyes were adorable. They were big and black.             'Can I help you, Jake?' he beeped, 'Would you like to play?'             'Wow', Jake smiled, 'Yes, you can help me. I would like you to get me my laptop. And some chocolate chips. I will eat my breakfast while you read to me. Then, and only then, will we play.'             'Yay.' Jake 2 beeped, emotionless, 'What book would you like me to read to you?'             'How about One Foot, Two Foot, Red Foot, Blue Foot by Dr. Seuss.'             'I shall go get that for you, Master',  and he rolled out of the room.             'Master!' Jake whispered, 'Cool!'             After breakfast and reading Jake and Jake 2 finally played. They played until lunch. Mom came in and saw that Jake 2 was alive.             'Aaaaaaaaaaaaaahhhhhhhhhhhhhhhh!' she screamed, 'How.......what......JAKE!' she was baffled.           'It's okay, Mom. He's only alive.' Jake acted like it was the most normal thing on the planet.             'No! It is not 'okay'! This is a very impossible thing! I'm calling the police department! Or whoever will take this....thing..... away!' she stormed out of the room.             'When Mom is set on something, she won't give up. It's no use trying to stop her,' Jake thought to himself.             'I guess this is it, buddy.' Jake cried, hugging the metal bot.             When the department came to take Jake 2 away, Jake clung every limb to the robot.             'No! I won't let you take him!'             Mom pried Jake off and embraced him in a lock-hug, so he couldn't run for the bot.             'This is for your own good. This was not a normal event, what happened today. It'll be okay later.'             'No! It won't! He was my best friend and you called the police on us!' Jake screamed. He ran inside sobbing.             Mom sighed, 'Let me have him', she said.              'But Mrs. Carigon, we can't let you just have him. He could be greatly used in studies and saving lives.'              'Let me have him', Mom sneered, giving the police officer a deadly look.              After a few seconds of the 'death look', the police officer said, 'Give him over.'              She brought him inside, looked at those big, black, rectangular eyes, and apologized.              'It's okay.' Jake 2 said.              Jake ran into the living room, 'You saved him! Thank you!' He grabbed Jake 2's metal hand and started dragging him back to his room.              'Ahh ahh ahh.' Mom said, moving her first finger from side to side, 'It's my turn to play with him.' She said.              'Ugh, fine.' Jake said shuffling back to his room.              'So, Jake 2, how are you with painting toe nails?' Mom asked Jake 2, escorting him into the kitchen.              Jake heard this and smiled.

Alive       by Jonathan Lee           The year was 3033. A scientist just finished his latest creation. It was a play-bot. It just so happened that the lightning had struck Pixel. It looked like   something was happening. Pixel's eyes were starting to glow bright green. He started to move his limbs. He got up and looked around. 'Where am I? ', he thought to himself. He scanned his surroundings. 'No plant or animal life found.' , his sub computer, H.A.L, told him.            He yelled as loud as he could, 'HELLO!... IS ANYBODY THERE! ' Of course nobody answered. After that,  the first thing he did was build himself a shelter out of the debris that the meteorite made so he wouldn't   rust. 'As soon as this storm is over, I'll go search for living creatures.            A couple of days later, the storm had stopped. Pixel noticed this right away as eager as he was to get out of his little shack. He went outside and activated his flight mechanisms. He flew away towards the west. He asked his father if he could help him,but his father had to work and his mom had to take care of his little sister. Jonathan went to his room got the stuff he had gotten from his garage.He was working on it and he thought it was going pretty well, then he checked his watch and saw that it was already 11:30.He freaked out and said,'Its late I should be in bed!' Jonathan then went to bed.                    The next morning, Jonathan woke up. He looked tired;he went downstairs and ate breakfeast. Jonathan went to school while his mother was watching his little sister. After school, Jonathan went home and went straight to his room. Once he got to his room, he was working on the robot.Then, he finished. He tried to turn it on so it could work,but it didn't turn on. Jonathan said,'Man I give up! I can never build anything!' He started to do his homework, Jonathan checked his watch,it late again! this time it wasn't 11:30 P.M, it was  12:00 P.M.                    Jonathan went downstairs, he told his mom he didn't feel like eating today either. She asked,'Why?' He just left to school without telling is mother about the robot. He came back from school, did his homework,and then ate dinner. Jonathan thought it would be good for him if he went outside. While he was outside he told himself,'Playing outside is a good idea.' He checked his watch it was already 8:30 P.M. He went upstairs went to bed and wished that his robot worked because he missed it.                      'Today is Saturday.', Jonathan said with a sigh of relief. Jonathan checked on his robot and turned it on. It was walking he was so happy he told his dad, mom, and sister. They congradulated him and they spent the whole day playing with it.

Khrystianna Edwards                                           5-23-2013   The Special One                        Sally was a very bored and dull girl. She thought she had nothing to do with her life. She had no friends and would sit by herself at school. She never wanted to do anything. Once she did one thing she wanted to stop and change the activity.                               One day when Sally came home she saw a mysterious package in her room with her name on it.                               ' What is this? It has my name on it, but I dont want to open it. Well I have nothing else to do.' Sally said as she tiredly walked over to the package.                     When Sally opened it a human shaped figure pushed its way out the top of the box.Sally started to scream as she was frightened.                     'My gosh i have been in that box forever!' The human like figure said in robot language while Sally was screaming.                      'Who are you and what are you doing in my room?'                      ' I am a robot and my name is Tundra.' Tundra said as she made her way out of the box.                     As Tundra gazed around the room, Sally was on her bed slightly underneath a pillow. Tundra seemed nice to Sally after a couple of minutes so Sally asked her alot of questions.  Tundra ansered all of her questions and they very soon became good friends.                     Two months later Tundra and Sally were doing everything together. Playing sports, exploring caves, driving to places in the area, and even doing farm work with eachother. The activities they did seemed like it went on forever.                    Everybody in town knew about Tndra. She was one of the nicest person of all. Even scientist knew about her, but a new scientist planned to steal Tundra away from Sally.                    Dr. Smith was the new scientist in the lab. He had recently read about Tundra on the front cover of the news paper.                    ' Thats quite a robot we got in town,'Dr. smith thought aloud,'I must get it.'                    On a beautiful Tuesday afternoon the two friends were playing baseball outside. Dr. Smith was driving by, examining the robot. He took notes and pictures. He finally parked his car and headed out for the robot and the girl. He asked questions, but Tundra was unsure so they decided to go inside.                    'Sally, may i speak to you please?' Dr. smith asked                    'Yes?' Sally said as she went back over to him.                     Dr. Smith bribed Sally with money for the robot, but she said it was her best friend and no amount of money can replace her. So the scientist understood and drove back to the lab.                    In the lab, Dr. Smith called court and negotiated about why a young girl as Sally shouldn't need a professional robot like Tundra.                   'She could be very useful here in the lab.' Dr.smith said                    The court agreed for the lab to take the robot. Dr. Smith planned to take the robot sooner than later.                       The very next day Dr. Smith went to the court, got a signed paper saying he can take the robot. He drove to Sally's house and showed her parents the signed paper.                    ' Sally!' Her dad yelled upstairs,' the Scientist are here to take Tundra.'                    The next couple of minutes were the worst for Sally. Her best friend was just tooken out of her life. How could she go on? The good news is that she did.                    Sally had later accomplished many things that Tundra tought her and she became a scientist . she went to the same lab Tundra was taken to and the two of the lived the rest of their happy lives together.                                          THE END
